{ Hello everyone, welcome to another study! This study will be about the King's Gambit. The King's Gambit is one of the oldest recorded chess openings in history and was one of the most popular openings until the late 19th century. It is very aggressive and leads to many tactical positions.

Even today the King's Gambit is still being played regularly by some of the world's best grandmasters.

Feel free to use the engine and the Lichess database, and don't forget to look at the variations :)

Let's start!

play 1.e4 }
1. e4 e5 { Can you find a way to sacrifice a pawn? } 2. f4 { This is the beginning of the King's Gambit! Black has two options:
1. Accept the gambit by taking f4
2. Decline it by playing something else
I have divided this study into these two sections.
There are many defenses for black, but hopefully I have covered most of them :)
Note: my lines will not always be the absolute top engine move, they are rather based on which one is more comfortable to play as a human and have a decent winrate.
KGA = King's Gambit Accepted
KGD = King's Gambit Declined
LSB = Light squared bishop
DSB = Dark squared bishop
Go to the next chapter! :) } *


