2... exf4 3. Nf3 Nc6?! { This is the MacLeod Defense, it is the most popular move at under-2000 level. It's not great because it allows white to gain the center with 4. d4! } 4. d4! { These pawns control a lot of squares! Also f4 is left undefended. } { [%csl Gc5,Gd5,Ge5,Gf5,Rf4][%cal Gd4c5,Ge4d5,Gd4e5,Ge4f5] } 4... d5 { The most popular move from black. } (4... g5 { Protecting f4. } { [%csl Gf4][%cal Gg5f4] } 5. h4! { [%csl Gg5][%cal Gh4g5] } 5... g4 (5... f6?? { A common beginner mistake. } 6. Nxg5! { Opening up the diagonal for the queen. } { [%csl Gh5][%cal Gd1h5] } 6... fxg5 7. Qh5+ Ke7 8. Qxg5+ Nf6 (8... Ke8 9. Qh5+ Ke7 10. Bxf4 { With lot's of compensation for white. The engine gives +4.2. } { [%csl Gh5,Gf4,Re7,Ge4,Gd4] }) 9. e5 $18 { the engine gives +2.4 } { [%csl Gf6][%cal Ge5f6] }) 6. Ne5 Nxe5 7. dxe5 $10 { It's equal. White will pick up some pawns later on. } { [%csl Rf4,Rg4][%cal Bb1c3,Bf1c4] }) 5. exd5 Qxd5 { White can now gain tempo by kicking the queen away. } 6. Nc3! { [%csl Gd5][%cal Gc3d5] } 6... Bb4 { Black pins the knight so that that the queen is no longer under attack. } { [%csl Re1,Rc3][%cal Rb4e1] } (6... Qe6+? { The most popular move. This is no problem for us, white wants to castle anyway. } 7. Be2! { We can castle on the next move, most of black's pieces haven't even left the 8th rank. Surprisingly, 70% blunders the basic fork tactic :) } { [%csl Bg1,Rf8,Rg8,Rh8,Re8,Rc8][%cal Be1g1] } 7... Qf6 (7... Bb4?? 8. d5 { We win a free piece! } { [%cal Gd5e6,Gd5c6] }) (7... Nf6?? 8. d5 { Same thing! }) (7... Bd6?? 8. d5 { And again! }) 8. O-O { White is almost fully developed, meanwhile black's king is still in the center, queen is awkwardly placed, and most pieces are undeveloped. The engine gives +1.7 } { [%csl Gf1,Ge2,Gf3,Gd1,Gc3,Rf6,Rf8,Rg8,Rh8,Re8] }) 7. Bd3! { Getting ready to castle. } { [%csl Bg1][%cal Be1g1] } 7... Bg4 (7... Nxd4?? { Another common beginner mistake, we can go ahead and happily take it. } 8. Nxd4! Qxd4 9. Bb5+! { Giving a check and now the black queen is left undefended. We can grab it on the next move. } { [%csl Yd4,Ge8][%cal Yd1d4,Gb5e8] }) 8. O-O $16 { White is a bit better, Stockfish gives +0.9 for white. } { [%csl Rf4,Gg1,Gf3,Gc3,Gd3] } *


