4... Nf6 { This is the Abbazia Defense, black doesn't immediately recapture the d pawn, instead continues developing, and our d pawn is still hanging. It's very easy to go wrong here for white. } 5. Bc4 { This is the most popular move at master level. Preparing to castle. } { [%csl Bg1][%cal Be1g1] } 5... Nxd5 6. O-O { [%csl Gg1] } 6... Be6 (6... Be7 7. d4 { Striking the center. } 7... O-O 8. Bxd5 { Removing the defender of the f pawn. } 8... Qxd5 9. Bxf4 $10) 7. Bb3 { Bringing the bishop to a safer square, where it's protected. } { [%cal Ga2b3] } 7... Bd6 { [%csl Bg8][%cal Be8g8] } 8. c4 { Gaining space in the center. } 8... Nf6 9. d4 { [%csl Gd4,Gc4] } 9... O-O 10. Nc3 $10 { It's an equal game with chances for either side. } { [%csl Gf3,Gc3,Gc4,Gd4,Gg1,Gf1] } *


