2... exf4 3. Nf3 Nf6! { This is the Schallopp Defense. It's one of the better options for black. } 4. e5 { Kicking away the horse. } 4... Nh5 (4... Nd5? 5. Nc3! Nxc3 6. dxc3 { Opening up the d file and freeing the DSB. } { [%csl Bc1,Bd1] } 6... d5 7. Bxf4 Be7 8. Qd2 O-O 9. O-O-O $14 { Material is equal, our king is safe, and 2 pieces are developed. Next up is to start a pawn storm on the kingside with h4. } { [%csl Gd2,Gd1,Gf4,Gf3,Ge5,Rc8,Rb8,Ra8] }) (4... Ne4? 5. d3 { [%csl Ge4][%cal Gd3e4] } 5... Nc5 (5... Ng5 6. Bxf4 Nxf3+ 7. Qxf3 $14 { [%csl Bc3,Bc1][%cal Bb1c3,Be1c1] }) 6. d4 { Supporting the e pawn and hitting the knight. } { [%csl Ge5,Gd4][%cal Gd4e5] } 6... Ne4 7. Bd3 $16 { [%csl Bg1,Rf4,Re4,Gd4,Ge5,Gf3][%cal Be1g1] }) (4... Qe7? { black pins the pawn. } 5. Qe2! { Breaking the pin. } 5... Nd5 6. c4 Nb4 7. d4 $16 { We control the center. White has a +1.4 advantage. } { [%csl Rf4,Rb4,Gc4,Gd4,Ge5][%cal Ba2a3,Bb1c3] }) (4... Ng4? 5. h3! { [%csl Gg4][%cal Gh3g4] } 5... Nh6 6. d4 $16 { [%csl Gd4,Ge5,Gf3,Rf4,Rh6,Rf8,Re8,Rd8,Rc8,Rb8,Ra8,Rh8] }) 5. Qe2 Be7 6. d4 { Taking the center. } { [%csl Ge5,Gd4][%cal Gd4e5] } 6... O-O 7. Bd2 d6 8. Nc3 Bg4 9. O-O-O $15 { White castles queenside, securing the king's safety. Stockfish says black is slightly better, but both sides have chances. It 's still a double edged position. You can't always get the advantage every time \('-')/. } *


[Event "King's Gambit | Full Repertoire: KGA: Cunningham Defense 3...Be7"]
