2... exf4 3. Nf3 h6!? { This is the Becker Defense. The idea of 3...h6 is to prepare for g5. } { [%csl Bg5][%cal Bg7g5,Bh6g5] } 4. Nc3 { Simply developing and supporting e4. } { [%csl Ge4][%cal Gc3e4] } 4... g5 5. d4 { Taking the center and freeing up the bishop. } { [%csl Gd4,Ge4] } 5... Bg7 { The bishop is most active here. } { [%csl Gg7] } (5... g4? 6. Bxf4! { The top engine move! } 6... gxf3 7. Qxf3 { White has more than enough compensation for the knight. Stockfish give +2.6 for white. } { [%csl Gf3,Gf4,Ge4,Gd4,Gc3,Gf1,Bc1,Ra8,Rb8,Rc8,Re8,Rd8,Rf8,Rg8,Rh8][%cal Be1c1,Bf1c4] }) 6. g3! { Trying to get rid of black's annoying f pawn. } 6... fxg3 { Here we're gonna play a much rarer move: } (6... g4 { Black absolutely doesn't want to trade the f4 pawn. This is no problem, we just move away. } 7. Nh4! { Rerouting to f5 } { [%csl Bf5][%cal Bh4f5] } 7... f3 8. Nf5 $16 { White has pawns in the center and 2 well placed knights. Black has 2 overextended pawns, and only a bishop developed. Stockfish gives +1.2 for white. } { [%csl Gf5,Gc3,Bf4,Gd4,Ge4,Rg4,Rf3][%cal Bc1f4] }) 7. Qe2! { There is no need to take the pawn right away, development comes first! } 7... gxh2 8. Be3! { Again, just keep developing. We can grab h2 any time we want. } 8... d6 9. O-O-O $13 { White is fully developed (except the LSB, but we can develop that soon enough), All of black's pieces are still on the 8th rank except the bishop. It's about equal with perfect play. } { [%csl Gc1,Gd4,Ge4,Gf3,Gc3,Ge3,Ge2,Rg7,Rh2,Rh6,Rg5,Ra8,Rb8,Rc8,Rd8,Re8,Rg8,Rh8] } *


