2... exf4 3. Nf3 h5?! { This is the Wagenbach Defense. You'll probably never face this, but I included it anyway. :) } 4. d4 { Taking control of the center. } { [%csl Gf5,Ge5,Gd5,Gc5][%cal Ge4f5,Gd4e5,Ge4d5,Gd4c5] } 4... g5 { Gaining space on the kingside. } 5. h4 { Challenging the g pawn. } 5... g4 { [%cal Rg4f3] } 6. Ng5 { You might think; Wait, black traps the knight after f6!, and yes, you are correct, but we'll get some compensation for it. } 6... f6 { [%csl Rg5][%cal Rf6g5] } 7. Bxf4! { This is the King's Gambit, sacrifices are normal ;)
This is the top engine move. White will get enough compensation for it. } 7... fxg5 8. Bxg5 Be7 (8... Ne7 9. Nc3 d6 10. Bc4 $16 { Mr. Fish gives +2.4 for white. Next we'll castle and black will have HUGE problems along the f file. } { [%csl Re8,Rf7,Rf8,Rd8,Ra8,Rb8,Rc8,Re7,Rh8,Gg5,Gc4,Gc3][%cal Be1g1] }) 9. Qd2! { The only move that keeps the advantage, white supports the bishop on g5. } 9... Bxg5 10. hxg5 { We're down material, we don't want to take the queens off the board. } { [%csl Gh1] } 10... d6 11. Nc3 Nc6 (11... Be6 12. Bd3 Ne7 13. O-O-O $16 { The next step is to break through the center with d5 or e5. Stockfish gives black a +1.5 advantage. } { [%csl Gd1,Gc1,Gd2,Gd3,Gc3,Gd4,Ge4,Gh1,Gg5] } 13... Qd7 14. d5 Bf7 15. e5 dxe5 16. Qe3) 12. Bc4 { Next up is O-O and black will have HUGE problems along the f file! It's +2.2 for white! } { [%csl Rf7][%cal Be1g1] } *


