2... exf4 3. Nf3 g5 { The pawns advance, and the battle for space begins. This is called the Classical Variation from the KGA. It's the most popular move. } 4. h4 { Challenging the g pawn. } 4... d5! { Black begins to open files and challenge the center. } 5. exd5 g4 { Gaining space on the kingside. } 6. Ne5 Qxd5 7. d4 { Supporting the knight and opening up the DSB. } 7... Nc6 8. Nxc6 Qxc6 9. Bxf4 { Finally recapturing. } 9... Bf5 10. Qd2 $10 { White plans to castle queenside. Note: white isn't giving away the c pawn, black's will be hanging too. The position is equal. } { [%cal Bb1c3,Be1c1] } *


