3. Nf3! g5 4. h4 f6?? { A VERYYY common blunder, made over 120,000 times! :D
It's good to be prepared for this, because you'll probably face this from time to time. Now white has a nice move: } 5. Nxg5! { Clearing the way for the queen. } { [%csl Yh5][%cal Yd1h5] } 5... fxg5 6. Qh5+ { Forcing the king to bongloud } { [%csl Ge8][%cal Gh5e8] } 6... Ke7 $7 { The only move } 7. Qxg5+ { just keep checking! } 7... Ke8? { It's now +10 already! } (7... Nf6 8. e5 $18 { This is very winning for white, the engine gives +5.2 }) 8. Qh5+! { The only move that secures the win } 8... Ke7 9. Qe5+ { Now we just want to bring the black king closer to us. } { [%csl Gh8,Ge8,Ge7][%cal Ge5h8,Ge5e8] } 9... Kf7 $7 10. Bc4+! { There's no need to grab the rook, we just bring the king closer to us. } 10... Kg6 11. h5+ Kh6 $7 { the only move } 12. Qxf4+ Qg5 (12... Kg7 13. h6+ Nxh6 14. Qxh6# { [%csl Gf8,Gg7,Gf6,Bg8,Bf7,Rh8,Rh7,Gg6,Yh6][%cal Gh6f8,Gh6f6,Bc4g8,Yh1h6] }) 13. Qxf8+ Qg7 $7 14. d4# { Checkmate! } { [%csl Gh6,Gg5,Yg6,Rh7,Rg7][%cal Gc1h6,Yh5g6,Bf8h6] } *


