5... h5 { This variation of the Kieseritzsky Gambit is called the "Long Whip" :)
Black defends the g pawn. } 6. Bc4 Nh6 { Black protects f7. } (6... Rh7 { Another way to protect f7. } 7. d4 { Taking the center. } 7... d6 8. Bxf7+! { It's ok, to sacrifice 2 pieces for the rook, usually don't do it, but this position is an exception, because black gets a weaker king. } 8... Rxf7 9. Nxf7 Kxf7 10. Bxf4 $13 { It's equal, but white has a 65% winrate! } { [%csl Ra8,Rb8,Rc8,Rd8,Rf8,Rg8,Rf7,Ge4,Gd4,Gf4][%cal Be1g1,Bb1c3] }) 7. d4 { Taking the center. } { [%csl Ge5][%cal Gd4e5] } 7... d6 8. Nd3 $14 { Retreating the knight. It's well placed here. We'll win back the sacrificed pawn on the next move, white is slightly better. } { [%csl Gd3,Rf4][%cal Be1g1] } *


