4. Bc4 g4 5. O-O! gxf3 { There goes the first piece! } 6. Qxf3 Qf6 7. e5 Qxe5 8. Bxf7+!! { ...the second! } 8... Kxf7 9. d4! Qxd4+?! 10. Be3 { We can't always play a "Triple Muzio Gambit". It's not really sacrificing a third piece because we win the queen back. } 10... Qg7! { We can now grab the free f pawn. } 11. Qxf4+ Nf6 12. Nc3 { Bringing an extra piece into action. } 12... Rg8?! { Threatening checkmate on g2. } { [%csl Rg2][%cal Rg8g2] } (12... Be7 13. Nd5! d6 14. Nxc7 Nc6 15. Qc4+ Kf8 16. Nxa8 $13) 13. Qe4! { Defending g2. } 13... d6 14. Rxf6+! { The third!....but we win the queen now. } 14... Qxf6 15. Rf1 { A skewer. } { [%csl Rf6,Rf7][%cal Bf1f7] } 15... Qxf1+ 16. Kxf1 $13 { Black is still up 4 points of material, but because of black's weak king and undeveloped army, it's almost equal. } { [%csl Ra8,Rb8,Rc8,Rg8,Rf8,Rf7,Ge4,Ge3,Gc3] } *


