4. Bc4 d6?! { The third most popular move. } 5. h4! { The only good move!, we now get something very similar to the Wagenbach Defense. } 5... g4 6. Ng5 { Double attacking f7. } 6... Nh6 { The only way to protect f7. } 7. d4 { Taking the center. Although this does allow black to trap our knight, but that's okay :) } 7... f6? 8. Bxf4!! { The only good move! We get more than enough compensation. } 8... fxg5 9. Bxg5 Qd7 (9... Be7 10. Bxh6 Bxh4+ 11. Ke2!! { The only move that keeps most of the advantage! We keep the f file open. Kd2?? would be met with Qf6, which is really annoying }) 10. O-O $18 { Black gets lots of problems along the f file, so it's really hard to develop. White has a +3.6 advantage and a 69% winrate. :D } *


