{ Alexei Shirov is a Latvian and Spanish chess player. Shirov was ranked number two in the world in 1994. }
1. e4 e5 2. f4 exf4 3. Nf3 g5 4. Bc4 g4 5. O-O! gxf3 6. Qxf3 Qf6 7. e5!? Qxe5 8. Bxf7+! Kxf7 9. d4! Qxd4+?! { Inaccuracy. Qf5 was best. } 10. Be3 Qf6 11. Bxf4 Ke8?! { Inaccuracy. Ne7 was best. } (11... Ne7 12. Nc3) 12. Nc3 Nc6?? { Blunder. Ne7 was best. } (12... Ne7 13. Rae1) 13. Nd5! Qg6 14. Rae1+? { Mistake. Bg3 was best. } (14. Bg3) 14... Be7?? { Blunder. Nge7 was best. } (14... Nge7 15. Qc3 (15. Bxc7 d6 16. Nf6+ Kf7 17. Nd7+ Ke8 18. Nf6+) 15... Bg7 16. Qxc6!! dxc6 17. Rxe7+ Kf8 18. Bh6+ Bf5 19. Bxg7+ Qxg7 20. Rxf5+ Kg8 21. Nf6+ Kf8 22. Nd5+ Kg8 23. Nf6+) 15. Bd6!! Kd8?? { Checkmate is now unavoidable. Nf6 was best. } (15... Nf6 16. Bxe7 Nxe7 17. Nxe7 Qf7 18. Ng6+ Kd8 19. Nxh8 Qf8 20. Qxf6+ Qxf6 21. Rxf6 c6 22. Nf7+) 16. Qf8+!! Bxf8 17. Bxc7# { 1-0 White wins by checkmate. } { In this breathtaking game, Alexei Shirov showcases the power of sacrifice and aggression in the King's Gambit. The battle unfolds with tactical fireworks, culminating in a brilliant checkmate. A true masterpiece! } { [%csl Gd8,Yc7,Be8,Be7,Rc8,Rd7][%cal Gc7d8,Yd5c7,Be1e8] } 1-0


