3. exd5 c6!? { This something King's Gambit players struggle with a LOT. The winrates for black are insane. Example: fxe5 loses on the spot because of Qh4+ - Qe4 fork. This is called the Nimzowitsch-Marshall countergambit. } 4. Qe2! { The only move that keeps the advantage! } 4... cxd5 5. fxe5 { We can safely grab the e pawn. Qh4+ is nothing to worry about anymore because our queen controls the e4 square. } 5... Nc6 6. Nf3! Bg4 7. Nc3 Nd4? { The most popular move. But it doesn't do anything. } (7... Bc5? 8. Qb5 Bxf3 (8... Bb6 9. Qxd5 Bxf3 10. Qxf3 $16) 9. Qxc5 Qh4+ (9... d4 10. gxf3 Qh4+ 11. Kd1 dxc3 12. Ba6! $18) 10. Qf2 $18) (7... d4 8. Ne4 Qd5 9. c4! { [%csl Gd5][%cal Gc4d5] } 9... dxc3 10. bxc3 $16 Nxe5 11. d4 Nxf3+ 12. gxf3 Be6 13. Rb1 $16 { [%cal Gb1b8] }) (7... a6 { the top engine move. } 8. Qf2! { Getting out of the pin and controlling d4. The plan now is to try to castle queenside. }) 8. Qd3! Nxf3+ 9. gxf3 Qh4+ 10. Kd1 { We just move over. } 10... Be6 11. Qb5+ { [%csl Gb7,Ge8][%cal Gb5b7,Gb5e8] } 11... Bd7 12. Qxb7 { White is up 2 pawns. } *


