2... d6 { Another popular option for solid players. } 3. d3 { Building a solid pawn chain. } { [%csl Ge4,Gd3,Gc2][%cal Gd3e4,Gc2d3] } 3... Nc6 4. Nf3 { We just continue developing. } 4... Bg4 (4... f5 5. Nc3 Nf6 6. g3 g6 7. Bg2 Bg7 8. O-O $10 { It's an equal game, with chances for either side. }) (4... Nf6 5. Nc3 g6 6. Be2 Bg7 7. O-O O-O 8. Qe1! { [%csl Bh4,Bg3][%cal Be1g3,Bg3h4] }) 5. Be2 { Breaking the pin. } { [%csl Gf3][%cal Ge2f3] } 5... Nf6 6. O-O Be7 7. Nc3 O-O 8. Kh1! { Preparing to get some activity along the g file. White can later try something like h3 followed by g4, and then bring the rook over to g1. White has a 59% winrate :) } { [%cal Bh2h3,Bg2g4,Bf1g1] } *


