2... Nf6!? { The Petrov's Defense, putting pressure on the e4 pawn early on. This move aims to create imbalances and disturb White's initial plans. } 3. fxe5! Nxe4 4. Nf3 { [%csl Ge5][%cal Gf3e5] } 4... Be7 { Preparing to castle. } (4... d5?! 5. d3 Nc5 6. d4 Ne6 7. Nc3 $16 { White gets a good game. Next up is Bd3 and O-O and white gets some activity along the f file. } { [%cal Bf1d3,Be1g1] }) (4... Bc5? { This allows white to gain tempo with d4. } 5. d4! { [%csl Gd4,Ge5] } 5... Bb6 6. Bd3 $16 { [%csl Bg1][%cal Be1g1] }) 5. d3 { Kicking the knight around. } { [%csl Ge4,Gc1][%cal Gd3e4] } 5... Ng5 6. d4 { Solidifying the center. } { [%csl Ge5,Gd4][%cal Gd4e5] } 6... O-O { Black responds by castling kingside, securing the king's safety. } (6... Nxf3+ 7. Qxf3 O-O 8. Bd3 $14 { White controls the center. } { [%csl Gd4,Ge5][%cal Be1g1,Bc2c3,Bc1f4,Bb1d2] }) 7. Bd3 Nxf3+ 8. Qxf3 d6 9. Bf4 $10 { It's an equal game. } { [%cal Be1g1,Bb1d2,Bc2c3] } *


