2... Qf6?! { The Nordewalde Variation. Black maximizes pressure on f4. Make sure not to take e5! } { [%csl Rf4] } 3. Nf3! $10 { Attacking e5. } { [%csl Ge5] } (3. fxe5?? { An immediate throw. } 3... Qh4+! { [%csl Re4][%cal Rh4e4] } 4. g3 Qxe4+ $19 { Black picks up a full rook. } { [%csl Gh1,Ge1][%cal Ge4h1,Ge4e1] }) 3... Qxf4 4. Nc3 Bb4?? { By far the most popular move, it leads to a really cool line! } (4... Qf6 5. Bc4 $18 { Next up is O-O and white gets a great game. Black just has an akward queen on f6 chilling. } { [%csl Bg1,Gc3,Gf3,Gc4,Ge4,Rf6,Ra8,Rb8,Rc8,Re8,Rf8,Rg8,Rh8][%cal Be1g1] }) (4... Qg4 5. Bc4 Qxg2 6. Rg1 Qh3 7. Bxf7+!! Kxf7 (7... Kd8 8. Rg3 Qh6 9. d4 $18) 8. Ng5+ { [%csl Gf7,Gh3][%cal Gg5f7,Gg5h3] }) 5. Bc4! { The absolute best move. } 5... Bxc3 6. O-O!! { The only good move! Every other move results in black gaining the advantage. White lines the rook up with the queen and the bishop is still under attack. } { [%csl Rf4,Rc3,Rf7] } 6... Ba5?? { Black thinks he just picked up a free piece, but blacks up for a disappointment. It's +5.5 for white btw. Here's a cool sample game played by two masters: https://lichess.org/IZLPqeyQ#40 } (6... Bd4+ { This move just gives the piece back and lets white get an amazing position. } 7. Nxd4 { Simply picking up the free piece. Also black attacks both the queen and f7. } { [%csl Gd4,Gf4,Rf7] } 7... Qxe4 8. Bxf7+ Kd8 9. Nf5 $18 { A completely dominating position. } { [%csl Rg7,Rd8,Re4,Re5,Gf7,Gf5,Gf1] }) (6... Qxe4? 7. Bxf7+! Kxf7 (7... Kd8 8. dxc3 $18 { [%csl Gf3,Gf7,Gf1,Gd1] }) 8. Ng5+ { [%csl Ge4,Gf7][%cal Gg5e4,Gg5f7] }) 7. d4! { The only move that wins. White frees up the bishop. } { [%csl Gc1,Rf4] } 7... Qxe4 8. Bxf7+!! Kxf7 (8... Kd8 9. Bxg8 { Getting rid of the knight. We can now play Bg5+, and black can't block the check with the knight. } 9... Rxg8 10. Bg5+! Ke8 11. Nxe5 { There's way to much threats for black to stop. It's +6 for white. } { [%csl Gg5,Ye5,Rh5,Bf1][%cal Rd1h5,Bc2c3,Ba1e1] }) 9. Ng5+ { A royal fork. } { [%csl Ge4,Gf7][%cal Gg5e4,Gg5f7] } 9... Ke8 10. Nxe4 $18 { White has a great position, it's +7 :D } { [%csl Gf1,Gd1,Gc1,Ge4] } *


