2... c6! { This move is actually really good, it has been popularized by GM Daniel Naroditsky. This opening doesn't actually have a name (correct me if I'm wrong), so I'll just name it the Naroditsky Defense for now. I first heard of this opening from this study: https://lichess.org/study/Ql5bksBa } 3. Nc3 exf4 (3... d6 4. d4 exd4 5. Qxd4 Nf6 6. Be3 $16 { White gets a good game. } { [%csl Bc1][%cal Be1c1] }) 4. Qf3! { The top-engine move! It's really rare. } 4... g5? { The most popular move, but it's bad because of the following move: } (4... d5 5. d4 dxe4 6. Qxe4+ Qe7 7. Bxf4 Qxe4+ 8. Nxe4 { It's an equal game. } { [%cal Be1c1,Bf1c4,Bg1f3] }) 5. h4! { Challenging g5. } 5... h6 (5... f6?? 6. Qh5+! { Forcing the king to bongcloud. } 6... Ke7 7. hxg5 $18 { We win the pawn back. }) (5... h5 { [%csl Gd4] } 6. d4 $16 { Black has some trouble keeping those kingside pawns intact. White should just keep developing now. } { [%csl Ge4,Gd4,Rg5,Rf4][%cal Bf1c4,Bc1d2,Be1c1] }) (5... gxh4 6. d4 $16 { Black has double h pawns and we're about to grab f4. } { [%csl Rf7,Rf4,Rh4,Rh7][%cal Bc1f4,Bf3f4,Bf1d3] }) 6. hxg5 Qxg5 7. d4 { Freeing up the bishop and taking the center. } { [%csl Ge4,Gd4,Rf4] } 7... Qg3+ 8. Qxg3 fxg3 9. Bf4 $16 { g3 is undefended, we got an open rook, and the king's ready to castle. } { [%csl Gh1][%cal Be1c1,Bf4g3,Bf1c4,Bg1e2] } *


