5. d5 exd5 6. exd5 Qe7+? { Also quite popular, being played over 20% of the time. The point is to allow Black to play Ne5 on the next move, since retreating feels so passive. } 7. Be2 { Simply blocking the check. We're one step closer to castling now. } { [%cal Be1g1] } 7... Ne5 8. O-O! { Simply continuing development. Remember the "To Take is a Mistake" rule. Nxe5 doesn't benefit us in any way whatsoever, Black just gets a menacing queen on e5. } 8... Nxf3+ (8... d6 { Black wants to keep his central knight. } { [%cal Gd6e5] } 9. Bb2! { Any developing move here is good. Bb2, Re1, Nbd2, a3 are all perfectly fine. } 9... Nf6 10. Re1 Qc7 11. Nbd2 { Just developing. } 11... Nxf3+ 12. Bxf3+ { Taking with the knight is fine too, but in this case we immediately get an well placed bishop and the rook becomes active. } { [%csl Gf3][%cal Ge1e8] } 12... Be7 13. Qe2 $16 { Everything is perfect for White. From here the idea is a3 opening up the a-file for the rook to get involved and getting rid of the annoying b-pawn, allowing c4. } { [%csl Re7,Re8,Rh8,Rc8,Rc7,Ra8,Ge2,Ge1,Gd2,Gf3][%cal Bc2c4,Ba2a3] }) 9. Bxf3 { Threatening to skewer the queen with Re1. } { [%csl Gg1,Gf3,Gd5,Re8,Re7,Rf8,Rg8,Rh8,Rc8,Ra8][%cal Bf1e1] } 9... Qd6 { Acting as a blockade, not allowing our pawn to move forward. } { [%csl Yd6][%cal Bd5d6] } (9... Qf6 10. Re1+ Be7 11. d6 { [%csl Re7,Ge1][%cal Rd6e7] } 11... Qxa1 12. Bf4 Qxa2 13. Qd4 $18 { It's +4.5. Despite the +7 points in material Black can't stop our attack against the weak king. All out pieces are placed in a perfect attacking position. } { [%csl Rg7,Rf7,Re8,Re7,Rg8,Rh8,Rc8,Ra8,Ra2,Gf4,Gf3,Gd4,Ge1][%cal Bf3d5,Bd6e7,Be1e7] }) 10. Re1+! { Controlling the e-file. From here there are plenty of good ways to continue, but I'll share, in my opinion, the most simplest straightforward one. } { [%cal Ge1e8] } 10... Be7 11. a3! { What we want to do now is play Ba3, skewering Black. But this isn't possible yet, so we have to clear the way. } { [%csl Rd6,Re7][%cal Bc1a3,Ba3e7] } 11... Nf6 (11... bxa3 12. Bxa3 Qf6 13. Nd2 { Getting a new piece in the game. Black is completely stuck here, it's only a matter of time before White crushes in, it's +5.1. } { [%csl Rg8,Rh8,Re7,Rc8,Ra8,Rf6,Ga3,Gf3,Ge1][%cal Bd2e4,Be4d6] }) 12. axb4 { [%cal Bb4b5,Bc1a3] } 12... O-O (12... Qxb4 13. Ba3 { Skewer. } { [%csl Rb4,Ye7][%cal Ra3e7,Be1e7] }) 13. b5 $18 { White wins material in all lines. It's +3.8. } { [%csl Rf8,Re7,Rd6][%cal Bc1a3,Ra3f8] } *


