{ So, as we’ve seen in the previous chapters, Black can go wrong very easily. In this chapter, we’ll look at the best move, tho luckily for us, it only gets played 4% of the time. }
5... Qf6! { Yes, this is Black’s best move, counterattacking our rook. But don’t panic if you see the 61% win rate for Black, if you know what to do, you’ll be fine. } { [%csl Ra1][%cal Rf6a1] } 6. c3! { The only way to keep our rook safe. } (6. dxc6?? Qxa1 $17 { There really isn't any continuation for us. The queen can escape and the king is completely safe. } { [%cal Ga1b1,Ga1a2] }) 6... Ne5! { This is the top engine line, stuff pretty much never played by humans. } (6... bxc3?! { The most popular move. With the idea of playing c2, double attacking our rook and queen. The position is now equal according the engine. We've still got some traps in this line. } 7. dxc6 { We'll sacrifice the exchange, we'll get plenty of compensation for it. } 7... c2 { Discovered attack. } { [%cal Rf6a1,Rc2d1] } 8. Qxc2 Qxa1 9. e5! { The tables have flipped! White's winrate is now at 60%. The point of e5 is it cuts off the queen’s escape route, we're not letting her return to f6! Our plan now is simple: Bc4, protecting the a2 pawn, followed by Bb2, completely trapping the queen. } { [%csl Ge5,Ba2,Ra1][%cal Gc2b1,Bf1c4,Bc4a2,Yc1b2,Yb2a1] } 9... Bb4+ 10. Kd1 dxc6 (10... bxc6?? 11. Bc4 $18 { Same thing. }) 11. Bc4 { [%csl Ya2][%cal Yc4a2,Rc1b2] } 11... b5 12. Bb3 Ne7 13. Bb2 Qxb2 14. Qxb2 $18 { It's a rook + 2 pawns vs our queen, we're better here. } { [%csl Ra8,Rh8] }) (6... exd5?! 7. exd5 { We transpose to a line somewhere in chapter 12. }) 7. Be2 { Not getting doubled pawns. } { [%cal Ge2f3] } 7... Bc5 8. O-O Nxf3+ 9. Bxf3 Ne7 10. Bb2 $15 { Black is slightly better according to the engine, but White still has plenty of fighting here with the great fianchettoed DSB that can come to life soon. Although it's probably still slightly easier to play as Black here. The winrates aren't accurate here because the position has almost never been reached in human games. } { [%csl Rc8,Gc5,Gf3,Gb2,Ge7][%cal Bd1d2,Bd1b3,Bf1e1,Bb1c3,Be7g6,Be8g8] } *


