Ok, let's see if you remember the starting moves. }
1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. b4 cxb4 4. d4 { Nice! I'm glad you remembered how to get to this point. :) } 4... d6?! { Black plays d6, a very passive move, it doesn't do anything to deal with our d5 threat and simply lets us kick the knight around. It still gets played quite often tho, and surprisingly players with White don't really know how to deal with this according to the database. It's still equal tho played perfectly. We'll look at this move in the upcoming chapters marked with📘. } *


