3... Nxb4 4. c3 Nc6 5. d4 d5 { We've seen cxd4 transposes to our lines, but instead Black decides to counterstrike the center. He's not afraid to bring the queen out, since we don't have Nc3 kicking it away. } 6. exd5 Qxd5 7. Na3! { Usually you don't want to put your knight on the rim, but in this case it has a good purpose there. It controls c4, allowing us to place our bishop there. } { [%csl Rc4][%cal Bf1c4] } 7... Bg4 { A dangerous looking pin, but it's nothing to worry about. We continue with our intended move. } (7... cxd4? 8. Nb5! { Threatening a royal family fork. } { [%csl Gd5,Ga8,Ge8,Yc7][%cal Rb5c7,Rc7d5,Rc7e8,Rc7a8] } 8... Qd8 9. Bf4! { Developing with tempo! } { [%csl Rc7] } 9... e5 { Black can't cover c7 with any piece, so he has to sacrifice a pawn. } 10. Nxe5 Qe7 { Pinning the knight. } { [%csl Re5][%cal Ge8e1] } 11. Qe2 { Simply unpinning it. } 11... a6?? (11... d3 12. Nxd3 $18 { [%csl Rc7][%cal Rb5c7] }) (11... Nxe5 12. Qxe5 Qxe5+ 13. Bxe5 Kd8 14. Nc7 Rb8 15. O-O-O $18 { Notice how all Black's pieces are on the backrank. } { [%csl Gd1,Rd4,Rd8,Rc8,Rb8,Rf8,Rg8,Rh8,Ge5,Gc7][%cal Bf1b5,Bh1e1] }) 12. Nc7+! Qxc7 13. Nxc6+ { Discovered check! We win an immense amount of material. } { [%csl Re8,Gc6,Gf4,Rc7,Re7][%cal Ye2e8] }) 8. Bc4! { [%csl Rd5][%cal Rc4d5] } 8... Qe4+ (8... Bxf3 9. gxf3! Qd7 (9... Qh5 10. Qb3 Qxf3 (10... Rb8 11. Bf4 { [%csl Rb8][%cal Rf4b8] } 11... e5 12. dxe5 $18 { [%csl Rf7,Rh5,Rb8,Gb3,Gc4][%cal Be1c1,Be5e6,Rf4b8] }) 11. Bd5 Qf5 12. Qxb7 $18) 10. d5 $18 { After the knight leaves we have Bb5 pinning the queen. } { [%csl Rc6,Rd7][%cal Rd5c6,Bc4b5,Bb5e8] }) 9. Be2! { [%cal Be1g1] } 9... cxd4 10. O-O! { King safety comes first! } 10... dxc3 11. Nb5! { A fork. Threatening Nc7# and Nxc3 winning back our pawn. } { [%csl Bc7,Gc3][%cal Bb5c7,Yb5c3] } 11... Rc8 { Covering c7. } { [%csl Rc7][%cal Rc8c7] } (11... c2?? { Counterattacking our queen. } { [%csl Rd1][%cal Rc2d1] } 12. Nc7#! { Surprise! It's actually checkmate. :) }) 12. Nxc3 $16 { The game goes on. Despite being down two pawns, we have plenty of compensation for it; a safe king, open files for our rooks, and almost all our pieces are developed. Black's whole kingside is still on the backrank. Stockfish says +0.8. } { [%csl Ge4,Bb1,Be1,Re8,Rf8,Rg8,Rh8,Rc8][%cal Gc3e4,Ba1b1,Bf1e1] } *


