[ChapterMode "gamebook"]

{ Let’s move on to the medium puzzles! This one is going to be a fun one. It’s from an online blitz game played between the two Norwegian GMs, Jon Ludvig Hammer and Magnus Carlsen. Magnus is up a knight, and his king looks safe... or is it?

Can you find the only winning move in this position? } { [%csl Gh7,Rd8] }
24. Rxh5+!! { Sacrificing the ROOOK! We open the king’s cover to expose it further checks. } 24... gxh5 { ...Bh6 2. Rxh6+ Kg7 3. Rdxh8 and R6h7# is unstoppable. How do we get a checkmate from here? } (24... Bh6 25. Rxh6+ Kg7 26. Rdxh8 { [%csl Rh7][%cal Rh6h7] }) 25. Be4+! { Checking the king! He has no squares to move to, so he can only block. } { [%csl Rh6,Bg8,Rh8,Rg7,Ge4][%cal Rg5h6,Bd8g8] } 25... f5 { Now what? } 26. exf6#!! { Yes! En passant! This is checkmate! GM Hammer just en passant checkmated the highest-rated player of all time! What an incredible achievement, this must be the highest honors in chess you could get. Congratulations to GM Hammer, and kudos to Magnus for letting him play it on the board!! } { [%csl Rh8,Bh6,Yg6,Yh7,Rg7,Gg8][%cal Bg5h6,Ye4h7,Gd8h8] } (26. gxf6+?? { NOO! The king can now just escape to h6. } 26... Kh6) *


