{ Here’s another Magnus Carlsen game, played when he was just 12 years old. Can you find the move played in the game? } { [%csl Gc2,Gc1,Gg3,Gh6,Gh4,Rg5,Rg6,Rh7,Rf6,Gf1] }
35. Nh5+! { Yes! Breaking open Black's pawn wall, exposing the king. } 35... gxh5 { If ...Kxh6 then 2. Nxf6+ discovered check, Kg7 3. Bxg5 and Black gets checkmated soon. If Kh8 or Kf8 then 2. Bxg5 fxg5 3. Qg3 is very dangerous for Black, White will win soon. gxh6 was played in the game. Can you find the continuation? } (35... Kxh6 36. Nxf6+ Kg7 37. Bxg5) (35... Kh8 36. Bxg5 fxg5 37. Qg3) 36. Qxg5+!! { Sacrificing the QUEEEN! Magnus opens the f-file for his rook to come join the action. } { [%csl Gf7][%cal Gf1f7] } 36... fxg5 { Kh8-Nf7#, and Kf8-Qg8#. } { [%csl Gf7][%cal Gf1f7,Yc2h7,Bc1h6] } 37. Rf7+! Kxh6 38. Rxh7# { A stunning checkmate whilst being down 13 points in material! } { [%csl Gh7,Gg6,Bh6,Bg7,Rh5,Rg5][%cal Gc2h7,Bh7h6,Bh7g7] } *


