{ This puzzle is from a game from William Steinitz, the first World Champion. } { [%csl Ra8,Rh8][%cal Rg7f6] }
1. Rd8+!! { Yes! A deflection! We want our queen on e6, but Black’s queen is controlling the square. We deflect it away, allowing our queen to move there. } 1... Qxd8 { 1...Kh7 2. Rxh6+ gxh6 3. Qe7+ Kg6 4. h5# } (1... Kh7 2. Rxh6+ gxh6 3. Qe7+ Kg6 4. h5#) 2. Qe6+ { [%csl Ge6] } 2... Kh7 $7 { The king runs behind his pawns. How can we continue? } 3. Rxh6+!! { Sacrificing the second rook! White breaks open Black's shield of pawns! } 3... gxh6 $7 { Now finish the game! } 4. Qf7#! { A beautiful Epaulette mate! Black's own pieces prevent the king from escaping. :) } { [%csl Bh7,Gg8,Gg6,Gg7,Rh8,Rh6][%cal Gg7h7,Gf7h7,Gf7g8,Gf7g6] } *


