{ We've now reached the "HARD" section. This puzzle is actually my personal favorite from the entire collection. Can you find the only winning move? }
23... Bxg2+! { Bringing the king out. } 24. Kxg2 $7 { You’ve found the first move of the sequence, but now what? There’s again only one move that wins. } 24... Qh3+!! { Yes! Luring the king to a square where he’ll be accessible to our knights. 3. Kh1 leads to g2#. } { [%csl Gg6,Gh7][%cal Bh7g5] } 25. Kxh3 Ng5+! { Bringing our knight into the action, forcing the king back into his corner. } { [%cal Bh3g2,Bg2h1] } 26. Kg2 Nh4+! 27. Kh1 { The final blow! :D } 27... g2# { Black checkmates the king in the corner with the pawn while being down 12 points in material! :O } { [%csl Bh1,Rg1,Rh2][%cal Bg2h1] } *


