[UTCTime "05:44:02"]
[ChapterMode "gamebook"]

{ Here we have a very attacking position for White, but it's actually still tricky. The e5-knight is attacking our queen, so a discovered check by moving the bishop doesn't work yet. And Kh7 is a threat because it would extinguish our attack.

Again, there’s only one winning move here. Can you find it? } { [%csl Rg4,Gg7,Gf5][%cal Re5g4,Rg8h7] }
28. Ne7+! { A type of deflection! If Bxe7, we can get a discovered check with Bxe5+, which leads to a checkmate soon. } 28... Kh7 { Black isn't forced to capture the knight! Instead the king moves out of the file of our queen. What's our follow-up? } (28... Bxe7 29. Bxe5+) 29. Qg6+!! { Sacrificing the queen! White forces open the h-file so the rook can join the attack. Black can capture in 3 different ways, but the result is the same. } { [%cal Rh5g6] } 29... fxg6 (29... Nxg6 30. hxg6+ Kxg7 31. Rh7#) (29... Qxg6 30. hxg6+ Kxg7 31. Rh7#) 30. hxg6+ { [%csl Gh1] } 30... Kxg7 31. Rh7#! { Checkmate! } { [%csl Bh7,Rf6,Rf8,Gg6,Gg8,Yf7,Yg7,Yh8][%cal Bg6h7,Ge7g6,Ge7g8,Yh7f7,Yh7h8] } *


