[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/Bosburp"]
[FEN "3q4/k1p2br1/1pQ5/p2pR3/P2P4/1P1B4/K1P5/8 w - - 0 39"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2024.12.17"]
[UTCTime "05:44:02"]
[ChapterMode "gamebook"]

{ This position is from a famous game between two strong GMs: Fabiano Caruana, World No. 2, and Ruslan Ponomariov, rated 2723 at the time. This was the most critical moment of the game. many moves would lead to a draw, but Caruana finds a brilliant combination.

Can you find what was played in the game? }
39. Re7!! { Caruana sacrifices the rook! If Black doesn't take it, White can play Rxc7. If Black does take it (which is what happened in the game), I won't reveal the next move just yet. :) } { [%csl Rc7][%cal Re7c7] } 39... Qxe7 40. Ba6!! { Yes! Another empty square sacrifice. Caruana places the bishop right next to the king, threatening Qb7#. And if the king captures the bishop... } { [%csl Rb7][%cal Rc6b7] } 40... Kxa6 41. Qa8#! { Checkmate! This is why Re7 was played; to deflect the queen from the 8th rank, leaving the a8 square undefended for the final blow. } { [%csl Bb5,Rb6,Ra5,Ga6,Gb7,Ga7][%cal Ba4b5,Ga8a6,Ga8b7,Ga8a7] } *


