[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/Bosburp"]
[FEN "4rrk1/1bpR1p2/1pq1pQp1/p3P2p/P1PR3P/5N2/2P2PP1/6K1 w - - 0 31"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2025.07.13"]
[UTCTime "10:49:30"]

{ Full game: https://www.chessgames.com/perl/chessgame?gid=1124533 }
31. Kh2!! { Kh2! an absolutely brilliant idea. White’s pieces are placed in a nice attacking position, but there’s no immediate breakthrough. The queen cannot deliver checkmate by her own strength. So what piece steps in to finish the job? THE KING! He walks up to h6 unbothered because Black cannot do anything to stop him, Timman's pieces are trapped on the other side of the board! } 31... Rc8 32. Kg3 Rce8 { Shuffling, there's nothing Black can do. } 33. Kf4 Bc8 34. Kg5 { Timman resigned here because checkmate is unstoppable.
In my opinion, what adds to the beauty to this game is that there’s no sacrifice or fancy tactics. Short sees a clear idea, and however absurd it looks, using the king as an attacker in the middlegame, plays it and it works.
This is not only funny but also highly instructive as it reminds as that we must be willing to think outside the box, and use some creativity. :) } { [%csl Rg7,Gh6][%cal Bh2g3,Bg3f4,Bf4g5,Bg5h6,Rf6g7] } *


