{ Full game: https://www.chessgames.com/perl/chessgame?gid=1259009
It is good to note that this game was not played by Emanuel Lasker, the second World Chess Champion. White is Edward Lasker, an IM, a cousin of Emanuel Lasker. }
11. Qxh7+!! { The king hunt begins. It's good to note that the entire kingwalk is forced. Lasker calculated everything from here. } 11... Kxh7 12. Nxf6+! { Making sure the king does not escape backward. White must force him to White's kingside. The following moves won't really require explanations. } { [%csl Rg8][%cal Rf6g8] } 12... Kh6 13. Neg4+ Kg5 $7 14. h4+ (14. f4+ { Also possible, but not as beautiful. } 14... Kxf4 (14... Kh4 15. g3+ Kh3 16. Bf1+ Bg2 17. Nf2#) 15. g3+ Kg5 16. h4#) 14... Kf4 15. g3+ Kf3 16. Be2+ Kg2 17. Rh2+ Kg1 { The king has been kidnapped all the way to g1! Very funny, considering this is where White's king stands when castling kingside. :) } { [%csl Gg1] } 18. Kd2#! { Played in the game. Many would prefer it if Lasker had played 0-0-0. But Kd2, might also be considered more elegant, moving just one piece. There's a huge debate on this. } (18. O-O-O#!) *


