12. Nxf7 O-O!! 13. Nxd8 Bf2+ 14. Kh3 d6+ 15. e6 Nf4+ 16. Kg4 Nxe6 17. Nxe6 Bxe6+ 18. Kg5 Rf5+ 19. Kg4 h5+ (19... Re5+ { Also possible, but in the game h5+ was played. }) 20. Kh3 Rf3# *


[Event "Pure Brilliancy: Volume I: Hoffmann vs Petrov - Notes"]
[Date "2025.07.13"]
[White "F Alexander Hoffmann"]
[Black "Alexander Petrov"]
[Result "*"]
[Variant "Standard"]
[ECO "?"]
[Opening "?"]
[StudyName "Pure Brilliancy: Volume I"]
[ChapterName "Hoffmann vs Petrov - Notes"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/dRde5aVj/ME5hqpj5"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/Bosburp"]
[FEN "r1bqk2r/pppp1ppp/8/2bnP1N1/8/6K1/PB4PP/RN1Q3R w kq - 0 12"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2025.07.13"]
[UTCTime "10:49:30"]

{ Full game: https://www.chessgames.com/perl/chessgame?gid=1257910

White's knight is attacked and the d5 knight is being attacked. If Qxd5, Black will capture White's knight with check, which leads to a mating attack. That's why he comes up with; } { [%csl Rg5,Rd5] }
12. Nxf7!? { If Black now takes the knight, White will capture d5 with check, forking the king and bishop. If not, WHite grabs one of the forked pieces. But, Petrov has an idea of his own... } (12. Qxd5?? Qxg5+ $19) (12. h4 { Would have still put White in the game. } 12... Ne3 13. Qf3 O-O $17) 12... O-O!! { Absolutely brilliant! Petrov calculated the whole mating sequence from here. } (12... Kxf7?? 13. Qxd5+ Ke8 14. Qxc5 $10 { It's an equal position. White is up a knight, but Black will get counterplay with Qg5+-b6-Rf8-Bb7 moves. }) 13. Nxd8 { The king has been cut off from the f-file. } { [%cal Gf8f1] } (13. Rf1 Rxf7 14. Rxf7 { No no, don't take the rook. White plays Qxd5 with check. } 14... Qg5+ (14... Kxf7?? 15. Qxd5+ Ke8 16. Qxc5 $16) 15. Qg4 Qxg4+ 16. Kxg4 Kxf7 { Now it's safe. Black is up 5 points in material. }) 13... Bf2+! { Must be forcing! Black cannot give White time to play Qxd5+ or create an escape route with a move like h3. } 14. Kh3 d6+ { Discovered check! Bringing another piece into the mating attack. } { [%csl Gc8][%cal Rc8h3] } 15. e6 Nf4+! { Forking the king and pawn. The LSB must come to life. } { [%csl Re6,Rh3][%cal Rf4e6,Rf4h3] } 16. Kg4 $7 Nxe6 { White is not in check, but he doesn't have any defensive moves. A discovered check is coming up. } { [%csl Rg4][%cal Gc8g4,Be6d4,Be6d8,Be6c5] } 17. Nxe6 (17. Nf7 { Would have prolonged the mate a bit. } 17... Rxf7 18. g3 Nd4+ 19. Kh5 Rf5+ 20. Kh4 Rf4+ 21. Kh5 g6+ 22. Kh6 Be3 23. gxf4 (23. Qb3+ Nxb3 24. Kg5 Rg4+ 25. Kf6 Bg5#) 23... Bxf4#) 17... Bxe6+ 18. Kh5 Rf5+ 19. Kg4 h5+ (19... Re5+ { An alternative move. Forcing the king to the f-file, and then bringing the a8 rook to f8. } { [%csl Bf8][%cal Ba8f8] } 20. Kf3 Rf8# { [%csl Rf2,Rf3,Be2,Be3,Be4,Gg3,Gg4,Rf4,Yg2][%cal Rf8f2,Be5e2,Gf2g3,Ge6g4] }) 20. Kh3 Rf3# { A discovered double-check checkmate! } { [%csl Yh4,Rh3,Bg4][%cal Yf2h4,Ge6h3,Rf3h3,Bh5g4] } *


