[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/D2rO6Ufn/YzxomLQn"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/Bosburp"]
[FEN "rnbk1bnr/pp3ppp/2p5/4p3/4P3/3B1N2/PPP2PPP/RNB1K2R b KQ - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2025.08.23"]
[UTCTime "11:49:40"]
[ChapterMode "gamebook"]

{ Mistake #9: Giving Random Checks for Literally No Reason

Many players, when they see a check, just have to give it. Of course, there are many of positions where you must give a check, like in a mating attack or as part of a tactic. But often checks get made in these type of positions. }
1... Bb4+? { Mmh, ok... it’s check. How do you, a skilled player, respond? 😉 } 2. c3! $16 { Simply kicking the bishop. Thanks for the free tempo. Black's check was completely useless, he wasted a move. 😏
So, what can we learn here? If you’re not gaining anything from the check, such as winning material, forcing the king to a bad square, a defensive resource, gaining a positional advantage, etc, don’t play it. You’re just helping out your opponent.
⚔ There's still work to be done. Practice more: https://go.noctie.ai/random-checks ⚔ } { [%csl Rb4][%cal Rc3b4,Bb1d2,Bd2c4,Be1g1,Bc1e3] } *


