[Opening "?"]
[StudyName "Top Mistakes: Part 2"]
[ChapterName "🎓 Not Learning From Your Games"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/ieCOdimW/XCMnsB7i"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/Bosburp"]
[FEN "8/8/8/8/8/8/8/8 b - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2025.06.29"]
[UTCTime "11:54:31"]
[ChapterMode "gamebook"]

{ Mistake #10 (Finally!!): Not Learning From Your Games

Wait... why aren't there any pieces on the board?! Because the next mistake isn't on the board, it's in your mind.

Often we never take time to analyze our games, or only analyze the games we win. But as the saying goes: “I never lose. I either win or learn.”

By analyzing your games, you'll learn a lot: what to focus on, where it went wrong, what went right, maybe you’re doing the same mistake over and over, etc. Explore variations, use the database and engine to help you.

It’s kinda insane that we can all analyze as many games as we want 100% free here on lichess, so not using that tool would be a huge waste.

You’ll improve much faster if you take some time to learn from your games instead of just binge playing. :) }
 *


