[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/Bosburp"]
[FEN "r3r3/p2n1p2/2qpp2k/1p5n/3PN2p/1PPQ1P2/P1B2P2/6RK b - - 1 27"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2025.07.28"]
[UTCTime "13:29:11"]

{ Full game: https://www.chessgames.com/perl/chessgame?gid=1053943
The game was awarded the "Best Combination" prize in the 1988 Chess Olympiad. White is down 5 points in material, but has a ton of compensation for it. Black's king is very vulnerable, White's queen just has to infiltrate. Qe6+ is a serious threat, see variation below. } { [%csl Rh6,Gg1,Gd3,Gc2][%cal Gg1g8,Yc2h7,Rd3e3] }
27... f5 { Not actually with the idea of attacking the knight (as capturing it would be losing). Instead, now Qe3+ can be reacted with f4, not allowing the queen to infiltrate. } { [%cal Rf5f4] } (27... a6 { Just to show the threat. } 28. Qe3+! Kh7 { The king walks into the LSB's line of fire. } 29. Nf6+ Kh8 30. Qh6#) 28. Qe3+! { White plays it anyway, he has an idea in mind. } 28... f4 { Likely, Black was thinking he gets a comfortable position from here on with his 5 point material advantage, as retreating the queen gives Black a winning position. } { [%csl Re3][%cal Rf4e3] } 29. Nxd6!! { Sacrificing the queen! If Black takes here, Nf7 is checkmate. Now the b1-h7 diagonal has been opened, bringing the LSB to life. Black's king is now paralyzed. } { [%csl Rf7,Yh7][%cal Rd6f7,Yc2h7] } (29. Qe2?? Rg8 $19 { White's attack is pretty much dead, as the f4 pawn acts as a blockade to prevent any pieces from infiltrating. } { [%csl Rf4] }) 29... Qxd6 { Quite forced to stop mate. } (29... fxe3 30. Nf7#) 30. Qd3! { Forming a battery, threatening Qh7#. } { [%csl Rh7] } (30. Qe4! { Leads to the same thing. } { [%csl Gh7][%cal Gc2h7] }) 30... Nf8 { Black covers the square, but... } { [%csl Rh7][%cal Rf8h7] } (30... Ng3+ { Wouldn't have led to an immediate mate, but it's completely losing too. } 31. Rxg3! Nf8 { [%csl Rh7] } 32. Rg6+ Kh5 33. Rg8 $18 { Rxf8 ideas are unavoidable. } { [%csl Rf8,Bh7][%cal Rg8f8,Bd3h7] }) 31. Qh7+!! { White plays it anyway! } 31... Nxh7 32. Rg6# { Checkmate while being down 16 points in material! } { [%csl Rh5,Rh7,Gh6][%cal Gg6h6,Yc2g6] } *


[Event "Pure Brilliancy: Volume II: Caruana vs Ponomariov - 2014"]
[Date "2025.07.28"]
[White "Fabiano Caruana"]
[Black "Ruslan Ponomariov"]
[Result "*"]
[Variant "Standard"]
[ECO "?"]
[Opening "?"]
