[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/Bosburp"]
[FEN "5rk1/4Qp2/bpB3p1/p6p/7R/1P2R1P1/P3PPKP/q2r4 b - - 0 28"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2025.07.28"]
[UTCTime "13:29:11"]

{ Full game: https://www.chessgames.com/perl/chessgame?gid=1929825
This starting position is a draw (maybe slightly better for Black). But Black will make a serious blunder as we will see which leads to Persson finding a brilliant sequence. }
28... Rg1+ { Black's playing aggressively, bringing the king out of his shield of pawns. } 29. Kf3 (29. Kh3?? Qf1+ 30. Bg2 Qxg2#) 29... Qf1 { Black puts pressure on the f pawn. Qg2+ a skewer is a serious threat. } { [%csl Rf2] } (29... Rf1 { A better move. tying the king down to the f pawn. The queen can flexibly move along it's diagonal. Now the idea is Bc8-Bg4. } { [%cal Ra6c8,Rc8g4] }) 30. Kf4!! { The king marches forward! Sacrificing the f pawn! He has a brilliant idea in mind. } 30... Qxf2+?? { Black takes the free pawn and continues attacking the king. This greediness however sealed Black's faith. } 31. Kg5!! { Wait a minute, who's actually attacking here? Suddenly, White's the attacker! The king wants to march over to h6, taking away g7 and h7 from the Black king. Then White has various mating ideas like Qxf8+!! Kxf8, Re8#. } { [%cal Bg2f3,Bf3f4,Bf4g5,Rg5h6] } 31... Kg7 { Black begins to see the idea, and defends by taking away the h6 square. But it's already to late. } (31... Rf1 { To show the threat. } 32. Kh6 Rg1 33. Qxf8+ Kxf8 34. Re8#) (31... Rc1 { Black's best try. Attacking the bishop. } 32. Rf4 { If Black retreats the queen White has time for Bd5 overloading the f pawn. } { [%cal Rf4f2,Bc6d5] } 32... Qxe3 33. Qxe3 Rxc6 $18 { White's better, but the game can continue. }) (31... Qf5+ { Quite funny, as it looks like this lead to mate, but White's actually getting helped in achieving his goal. } 32. Kh6 Qc5 { Remember Qxe8 ideas. Now Black covers it, but WHite moves on to his other idea. } 33. Qf6!! { [%csl Rg7][%cal Rf6g7] } 33... Qxe3+ 34. Rf4 $18 { Black can't stop the mate. }) 32. Rf4 { Hitting the queen and stopping it's control over f6. } { [%csl Rf2][%cal Rf4f2] } 32... Qxh2 { Black can't stop all the threats. } 33. Qf6+ Kh7 { Kg8 leads to Kh6-Qg7#. } { [%csl Rh6][%cal Rh7h6] } 34. Qxg6+!! { Sacrificing the queen to open the 7th rank. } { [%cal Be3e7] } 34... Kh8 { Black decline it. } (34... fxg6 35. Re7+ Kg8 36. Bd5+ Kh8 37. Rxf8#) 35. Kh6!! { The final flourish! Leaving the queen hanging as taking it leads to Rxf8#. Not taking it leads to Qh7#! What a wonderful husband and wife duo!
Laurusas resigned here. Persson likely was inspired from the infamous Short - Timman game. But I'd say this is a much more in-dept version from it. } { [%csl Yh6,Yg6] } *


