{ Full game: https://www.chessgames.com/perl/chessgame?gid=1998278 This game was actually played online between Luis Paulo Supi and non other than Magnus Carlsen.

Thanks for still being here! You're about halfway through the study! I hope you're learning something useful! I know it took you a few minutes to get to this chapter, but it took me many hours to annotate, investigate, and find these positions. So, if you’re enjoying the study, please leave a heart, it really helps me keep creating these! I appreciate it! :) }
16... Qf5 { Magnus attacks the DSB. } { [%csl Rf4][%cal Rf5f4] } 17. Rfa1! { A theme I often mention in my studies. React to a threat by creating a counter threat! Threatening Ra8#. } { [%csl Ra8][%cal Ra2a8] } 17... Kc8 { The king moves over to his air hole. } { [%cal Bc8d7] } 18. Qc6!! { White sacrifices the queen! This forcefully closes Black's air hole. } { [%csl Rd7][%cal Rc6d7] } 18... bxc6 19. bxc6 { Ra8# is unstoppable. Magnus resigned here, but we can see the mate. } { [%csl Rd7,Rb7,Ba8][%cal Rc6d7,Rc6b7,Ba2a8] } 19... d3 20. Ra8# { Checkmate! Playing this against the WC must have felt so satisfying! } *


