[StudyName "Pure Brilliancy: Volume II"]
[ChapterName "Ftacnik vs Cvitan - Notes"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/JQKJOhPn/EdsDqqsU"]
[FEN "r5k1/ppP2rbn/3P2n1/P3p2p/2N1Pp1q/2N2Ppb/4B1PP/R2Q1RBK b - - 0 23"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2025.07.28"]
[UTCTime "13:29:11"]

{ Full game: https://www.chessgames.com/perl/chessgame?gid=1046655 Not as deep as the previous one, but definitely very beautiful. }
23... Bxg2+! { Bringing the king out. Cvitan already saw the following forcing sequence. } 24. Kxg2 $7 Qh3+!! { Black lures the king to a square where he’ll be accessible to the knights. Kh1 leads to g2#. } { [%csl Gg6,Gh7][%cal Bh7g5] } 25. Kxh3 (25. Kh1 g2#) 25... Ng5+! { Now forcing the king back into his corner. } { [%cal Bh3g2,Bg2h1] } 26. Kg2 $7 Nh4+! 27. Kh1 $7 g2# { A beautiful pawn checkmate while being down 12 points in material! } { [%csl Bh1,Rg1,Rh2][%cal Bg2h1] } *


