[Event "Pure Brilliancy: Volume II: Canal vs Horvath - Notes"]
[Date "2025.07.28"]
[White "Esteban Canal"]
[Black "Horvath"]
[Result "*"]
[Variant "Standard"]
[ECO "?"]
[Opening "?"]
[StudyName "Pure Brilliancy: Volume II"]
[ChapterName "Canal vs Horvath - Notes"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/JQKJOhPn/jI2G9m7q"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/Bosburp"]
[FEN "r3k1nr/pp1n1ppp/2p1p3/q7/1b1P1B2/P1N2Q1P/1PP1BPP1/R3K2R b KQkq - 0 10"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2025.07.28"]
[UTCTime "13:29:11"]

{ Full game: https://www.chessgames.com/perl/chessgame?gid=1264050 One of the most beautiful miniatures out there. This game was played in a simul. }
10... O-O-O?? { This seemingly natural move, bringing the king to "safety", is a losing blunder, but only if Canal finds the following 4 move sequence, which he does. } 11. axb4!! { The first pattern, the double-rook sacrifice, luring the queen away from the queenside. } 11... Qxa1+ (11... Qb6 12. b5 $18 { White will break through in a few moves. It's +6.2. White's pieces are perfectly placed for a slaughter. } { [%csl Gc3,Gf4,Gf3,Ga1,Ge2] }) 12. Kd2! { White must gain tempo! You should already be familiar with this tactic if you've seen my "Sacrifice Like a Pro!" course. } { [%csl Gh1,Ra1] } 12... Qxh1 { Now the queen's away from any defense, the second pattern can begin. } (12... Qxb2 { Same thing actually. } 13. Qxc6+ bxc6 14. Ba6#) 13. Qxc6+!! bxc6 14. Ba6# { The Boden's mate! A reminder that tactics are crucially important to learn, they can come anytime. We're only on move 14! } *


