A study by https://lichess.org/@/Bosburp

Hello fellow chess enthusiasts! 🌟 Welcome to my latest study! In this study, we're diving into the epic games of the one and only Mikhail Tal. 🏆 Get ready for a wild ride through the mind of this fearless chess wizard!

Mikhail Tal, aka the "Magician from Riga," lit up the chess world with his daring moves and jaw-dropping sacrifices. As the 8th World Chess Champion, he made history with his unique style.

This study is beneficial for players of all skill levels; there's always something to learn from Tal's games. I've highly annotated and analyzed each game. Additionally, I've organized this study into two sections: games where Tal played as White and games where Tal played as Black.

Feel free to use the engine and the Lichess database! 🕵

