{ Hello, welcome!

This study is created by @UDITORIUM, @Alpieren_aquin, and @Bosburp. Together, we've dug through over 100 games from the tournaments we’ve hosted in our Study Creators & Friends community collaborated with Noctie.ai, the GRAND Noctie Prize Swisses with 325 euros worth of prizes.

We've analyzed all the games and picked the best puzzle positions for you. These aren’t titled player puzzles, they’re from real games from normal players like us. This means that the patterns and ideas you'll see here are exactly the types of things that appear in everyday games. (except if you’re a master 😉)

We've tried our best to make this as educational as we could, explaining the moves, adding variations, and giving general tips. This was a huge project, so if you enjoy it, we would really appreciate it if you'd leave a heart. ❤

The puzzles are sorted quite randomly, just like positions which come up in real games. But we've added a color to indicate difficulty. This might be subjective, so I recommend you don't pay much attention to it.

Chapters 2-21 created by https://lichess.org/@/bosburp

Chapters 23-29 created by https://lichess.org/@/Alpieren_aquin

Chapters 30-47 created by https://lichess.org/@/UDITORIUM

Also, join our team for more awesome studies: https://lichess.org/team/study-creators--friends

Let's dive right in! Happy solving! :) }
