[ChapterMode "gamebook"]

12. dxc5?? { A common mistake! Taking for the sake of taking. But this doesn't improve White's position in any way. In this case, it's even fully losing. Can you see why? } 12... d4! { Attacking the pinned knight! } { [%csl Rc3][%cal Rd4c3] } 13. a3 { In the game Bd3 was played and Black ended up winning quickly. Let's look at this line. Black must still be careful. } (13. Bd3 dxc3 14. bxc3 Bxc5 { Match link: https://lichess.org/RgYbCVvM }) 13... Ba5! { Don't take immediately! After White trades queens, Black's bishop remains hanging. } 14. b4 { Attacking the bishop again, and breaking the pin. } { [%cal Rb4a5] } 14... dxc3! { Now taking is fine, we'll see why on the next move. } { [%csl Gd8][%cal Ra5d8,Bc3d2] } 15. Qxd8 Bxd8 $19 { Now the Bishop can recapture and no pieces are hanging anymore. Black's up a clean piece. Match link: https://lichess.org/RgYbCVvM } *


