[UTCTime "11:19:41"]
[ChapterMode "gamebook"]

{ Here White is up a queen for rook. It's a fully winning position. But here a serious blunder gets made. }
39. Nxd6+?? { White takes the "free" pawn and wants to trade off some material to simplify into a winning endgame. But is this pawn really free? } 39... Bxd6! { Recapture! The king was in check. Here White realizes his blunder. If White's queen captures the bishop, Black has Rb8+! Kf2, and Rf1#. the king is surprisingly trapped! If he tries to escape with Kh2, there's Rh8+ Kg1 Rh1+ Rf2 Rf1#.
White is up 3 points material, but Black's king is safe, and Rg8 is too big a threat. Neither side can make good progress. } 40. Qa7+ Kg6! { The only correct square. Kf6 allows Qh7, controlling h8 and b1. Moving backward traps the king on the last rank. } 41. Be4+!? { An interesting move to take away the knight from trapping the king. Is it safe to take? } 41... Nxe4! { Yes taking is the only move. Material is now equal. } 42. Qd7 { Threatening the serious Qf4+ a fork. What's the only move here? } { [%csl Rd6,Rf5] } 42... Rb1+! { Forcing the king to h2 where it will be trapped. In the game, Black played Kg5?? and lost the game. } { [%csl Rf2] } (42... Kg5??) 43. Kh2 Ng3! { Sacrificing the bishop! Fully trapping the king. Rh1 would be checkmate. The only thing White can do is perpetual check the king. } { [%csl Rh1] } (43... Re1! { Also possible, but delays the idea. Better to play it right away. } 44. Qe8+ Kf6 45. Qh8+ Kg6) 44. Qxd6+ Kh7! $10 { Only move! Not allowing the queen to take e5 with check. Now the queen will keep checking the king in order to not give Black time to play Rh1#. Black's king will shuffle along h7-g8. It's a draw.
Match link: https://lichess.org/UEqsZ7xR } { [%csl Rh1][%cal Rb1h1,Bh7g8] } (44... Kg5) *


