13... a5? { Now, white can win the advantage } 14. Bxh7+!! { The greek gift!! } 14... Kxh7 15. Rh3+ Kg8 16. Qh5 { threatening Qh7/8# } { [%csl Gh7,Gh8][%cal Gh5h7,Gh7h8,Gh3h7,Gh3h8] } 16... f5 { then only saving move for black } 17. Qh7+! (17. Qh8+ { this makes no difference, but you just play 2 more moves... } 17... Kf7 18. Qh5+ Kg8 19. Qh7+) 17... Kf7 18. Rg3!! { threatening Qg6 with a mate in 2 } { [%csl Gg6][%cal Gg3g6,Gh7g6] } 18... Rg8 { Makes f8 free for the king! } (18... b5 19. Qg6+ Kg8 20. Qxg7#) 19. Qg6+ { We play it anyway! } 19... Kf8 20. Qxe6 { And we take the free pawn!! } 20... Bc8 21. Qxf5+ { and you equalized your material and have a much better position! That means, you control the f-file, your queen and your rook are super active, while blacks figures are just till the 7th file!
You can aktivate you knight with Nf3, Ng5, aktivate your rook with Rf1...
I won't give you the game link, I send it to you in the next chapter } { [%csl Gg8,Bf1,Gf8,Gc3,Gh3,Gh7,Gh5,Ge6,Bf3,Bg5][%cal Gg3g8,Ba1f1,Gf1f8,Gg3c3,Gg3h3,Gf5h7,Gf5h5,Gf5e6,Bd2f3,Bf3g5] } *


