{ This game was played by https://lichess.org/@/Mj05091388 with white against https://lichess.org/@/ArcendW with black.
This position came after the 11th move from white, 0-0-0
Here, https://lichess.org/@/ArcendW blundered, but it is really hard to punish the blunder } { [%csl Gc1,Gd1][%cal Ge1c1,Ga1d1] }
11... c5?? { At the first look, it don't look like a blunder. Black tries to fight about the centre, attacking the d-pawn, with his c-pawn! But can you find the sequence, which will kill black?? } 12. Nxf6+! { An important zwischenzug!!!!
Every moves here were also played in the game ( always stockfish favourites)
You see it, if you found the next move!! } (12. d5 Nxd5) 12... gxf6 { (I want to mention it, here are many moves right, we play the moves, which was played in the game) } (12... Nxf6 13. Bb5+ Nd7 { We just bring the knight back!! } 14. d5 { [%csl Re6][%cal Gd5e6,Ye2e8] } 14... e5 15. Qxe5+ { and we have a pawn more, we will win this game!! }) 13. d5!! { Now you can see, why it was important to trade the knights!!!
If blacks knight stands on f6, we couldn't play this move!!
May you ask: What would happened if the knight took back?
Look at the analysis board!! } { [%csl Gd5,Ye8,Gf6][%cal Gf6d5,Ye2e8,Re6d5] } 13... e5 { Black tries to get his pawn safe... } (13... Nb6 14. Bb5+ Ke7 15. d6+ Kxd6 16. Bf4+) 14. f4 { But we don't care about it!!!
We just attack the pawn again!! } { [%csl Ge5,Ye8,Rf4][%cal Gf4e5,Ye2e8,Re5f4] } 14... a6?! { Black tries to avoid Bb5 with pinning the knight, so he is playing this, but this move lose one temptation, but black will lose anyway, so it isn't a big blunder!! } 15. fxe5 { We just trade!! } (15. Bf5) 15... fxe5 16. Bf5! { That is the reason why a6 was useless!!!
The knight is pinned, and we develop our bishop onto a dangerous field!! } { [%csl Bc8,Rd7][%cal Bf5c8] } 16... Qc7 (16... Nf6) 17. Bxd7+ { We love trading!!!! } 17... Kxd7 { Definetily the better move!!
If Qxd7, than we could take the e5pawn with attacking the king and the rook!! } 18. Qg4+! { Important check, we are gaining spce with that!! } { [%csl Yg8,Ya4,Yc8,Yg1,Yd1][%cal Yg4g8,Yg4a4,Yg4c8,Yg4g1,Yg4d1] } 18... Kd8?! { Little inacurarity (how to write this word???????)
Now we can develop another figure } 19. Bg5+ { Yes, I meant the bishop!!
We don't lose any temptation!!
Just look how we are controling the chess board!!
We have equal material, but we have more active!!
Keep playing! } { [%csl Ya4,Yg1,Yc8,Bc1,Rd8,Rh1,Rd1,Gc4,Gd6,Gf4][%cal Yg4a4,Yg4d1,Yg4g1,Yg4c8,Bg5d8,Bg5c1,Rd1d8,Rd1h1,Gc2c4,Gd5d6,Gf2f4] } 19... Ke8 20. Bf6!! { Whooooops, the rook is trapped!!
Sadly, black has one good counter move!!!!!! } { [%csl Bh8,Yg8,Rh7,Rf8][%cal Bf6h8,Yg4g8] } 20... h5!! { Counterattack!!
A really good move! The rook can escape now to a7/6, and we have to move our queen to another field! } { [%csl Gg4,Rh7,Rh6][%cal Gh5g4,Rh8h7,Rh7h6,Rh8h6] } 21. Qa4+ { Yes, we still make a check!!
Sometimes they are just good...
But, I think we have to move our queen again!! } (21. Qe4 Rg8 (21... Bh6+ 22. Kb1 Rg8 23. d6 Qb6 24. d7+ Kf8) 22. d6) 21... b5?! { You see, why this move was bad for black and important for us the next chapter!!
Play Qe4 now!
(All moves was played in the game, and all moves from white where stockfish favourite) } { [%csl Ye4][%cal Ya4e4] } 22. Qe4 Bh6+ { Black tries to survive longer
But it is even a mistake!
Obvious what we play now!! } 23. Kb1 { As you can see, white is leading here with +5, because of the space you have!!!
Black will make now a deadly blunder, which costs him the game!!
Go to the next chapter } { [%csl Yh4,Yh7,Ye1,Yc2,Ya4,Be5,Bh8,Rd5,Rh1,Rd1,Gd6,Gd7,Gd8,Gc4,Gb3][%cal Ye4h4,Ye4h7,Ye4h1,Ye4e1,Ye4c2,Ye4a4,Bf6e5,Bf6h8,Rd1d5,Rd1h1,Rh1d1,Gd5d6,Gd6d7,Gd7d8,Gc2c4,Gb2b3,Gf2f4] } *


