[ChapterName "📘 Clearance Sacrifice | Example #1"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/q22lMoJU/c1q1clLh"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/Bosburp"]
[FEN "r1r4k/2n2Rbp/4Q1p1/p5N1/PpB5/1P6/6PP/3R3K w - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2024.11.02"]
[UTCTime "09:47:54"]

{ Next, we've arrived at the Clearance Sacrifice! A clearance sacrifice is a tactical sacrifice where a player sacrifices a piece to clear a specific square, file, or diagonal for another piece to exploit. This can lead to a decisive advantage or even checkmate. Here I have a perfect example that I found on Wikipedia: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clearance_sacrifice In this postion White has a incredibly beautiful forced checkmate in 3. Now if there weren't a rook on f7, White could play Qg8+!! followed by Nf7#, a smothered mate, so now we want to clear the f7 square so that our queen can move there. }
1. Rf8+!! { We sacrifice a full rook to clear the way for our queen! The rook can be captured 2 ways, but neither of them work. } { [%csl Gg8,Gf7][%cal Be6g8] } 1... Rxf8 { Black is forced to take, since he's in check. } (1... Bxf8 { Now the bishop blocks the rook from controlling the g8 square. } { [%csl Gg8,Rf8][%cal Rc8f8] } 2. Qg8# { Checkmate! }) 2. Qg8+! { Another clearance sacrifice, we now vacate the f7 square for the knight. } { [%csl Gf7][%cal Bg5f7] } 2... Rxg8 $7 { [%csl Gf7] } 3. Nf7#! { A classic smothered mate! If you're not familiarized with this pattern, I highly recommend that you go practice it! You never know when you'll get one of these in your games! https://lichess.org/practice/checkmates/checkmate-patterns-i/fE4k21MW/WV2JxGhI } { [%csl Gh8,Rg8,Rg7,Rh7][%cal Gf7h8] } *


