[ChapterMode "gamebook"]

{ I can't cover every positional sacrifice because there are so many, and their effectiveness really depends on the specific position. Learning to recognize when to make a positional sacrifice comes with experience and understanding the nuances of the game. You'll develop a sense for it as you study more examples and practice in your own games. For now, I'll leave it with these chapters, as they highlight some common key ideas you'll likely encounter in your games often.

We've arrived at the last section (finally🎉), Endgame "sacrifices". These sacrifices are often made to promote a pawn, force a favorable exchange, or even force a draw. In endgames, every move counts, and the right sacrifice can transform a seemingly equal or losing position into a winning one. Mastering these techniques can help you turn the tide of the game and achieve victory in surprising ways. We'll look at these in the following chapters. 🚀 }
 *


[Event "Sacrifice like a PRO! | Free Course!: 📗 Pawn Breakthrough | Example #1"]
[Date "2024.11.02"]
[White "Bosburp"]
[Black "Jisu101"]
[Result "*"]
[Variant "Standard"]
[ECO "?"]
[Opening "?"]
[StudyName "Sacrifice like a PRO! | Free Course!"]
[ChapterName "📗 Pawn Breakthrough | Example #1"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/q22lMoJU/jyzxTphz"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/Bosburp"]
[FEN "8/1p3kpp/pP2p3/P4r2/1P6/8/6PP/5RK1 w - - 3 31"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2024.11.02"]
[UTCTime "09:47:54"]

{ Let's start with the pawn-breakthrough. I won't go too in-dept into this, but I'll give you a few examples. As the name suggests, we literally break through with our pawns. Here's an example from one of my games against my friend, @jisu101. As you can see, the material is still equal. } { [%csl Yb4,Yb6] }
31. Rxf5+! { I'm keeping things simple, first I'm simplifying the position by getting the rooks of the board. } 31... exf5 { Now, you might notice I have doubled b-pawns, that's bad right? No, they can sometimes be very advantageous. In this case, they led me to win the game! } { [%csl Gb4,Gb6] } 32. b5! { The pawn-breakthrough! The black a-pawn was blocking my a-pawn, and now I'm clearing the way. } { [%cal Ba5a6] } 32... axb5 (32... g6 { If Black plays something else randomly, the b-pawn can take a6 and promote. } { [%cal Bb5a6] } 33. bxa6 bxa6 34. b7 { [%cal Bb7b8] }) 33. a6! { Sacrificing another pawn to advance further up the board. } { [%cal Ba6a7,Bb6b7,Bb7b8] } 33... bxa6 { And now finally, my pawn can go to it's promoting square without getting blocked. } { [%cal Bb6b7,Bb7b8] } (33... Kg6 34. axb7 { [%cal Bb7b8] }) 34. b7 { The pawn will promote to a queen on the next move. } { [%csl Gb8][%cal Bb7b8] } *


[Event "Sacrifice like a PRO! | Free Course!: 📗 Pawn Breakthrough | Example #2"]
[Date "2024.11.02"]
