1. c4 { Hello everyone, welcome to this study! I haven't made a study for quite a long time (2 months). So I decided to make one about the English opening (for black and white). Lets start! } 1... e5 { The English opening always starts with 1.c4
It opening is used by some of the world's best players. } 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. Nf3 g6 { black plans to fianchetto his bishop } { [%csl Gg7][%cal Gf8g7] } 4. d4 exd4 5. Nd5 Bg7 6. Bg5 { [%csl Rd8][%cal Rg5d8] } 6... Nge7?? (6... f6 7. Bf4 { [%csl Gc7][%cal Gf4c7,Gd5c7] } 7... d6 8. Nxd4 { [%csl Gc4,Gd4,Gd5] }) 7. Nxd4 Bxd4?? (7... Nxd4 8. Bxe7 Qxe7 9. Nxe7 Kxe7) 8. Qxd4!! { White sacrifices his queen, but will checkmate black soon } 8... Nxd4?? (8... f6 9. Nxf6+ Kf7 10. Qf4) 9. Nf6+ Kf8 10. Bh6# { Checkmate! } *


