1. c4 { This trap is also know as the Tiger Trap } 1... e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. g3 Nc6 4. Nf3 Bb4 5. Nd5 { [%csl Gb4][%cal Gd5b4] } 5... Nxd5 6. cxd5 { [%csl Rc6][%cal Rd5c6] } 6... e4?? { black wants to attack white back, but this is a big mistake... } { [%csl Rf3][%cal Re4f3] } 7. dxc6 exf3 8. Qb3! { white attacks the bishop and the pawn. } { [%csl Gf3,Gb4][%cal Gb3b4,Gb3f3] } 8... fxe2 { [%cal Re2f1] } 9. Bxe2 Bd6 (9... a5?? 10. a3 Bd6 11. cxb7 Rb8 12. Qe3+ Kf8 13. bxc8=R) (9... Be7?? 10. cxb7 Rb8 11. bxc8=R Qxc8 (11... Rxb3 12. Rxd8+ Kxd8 13. axb3) 12. Qd1) (9... Qe7 10. a3 Bc5 11. cxb7) 10. cxb7 Rb8 11. Qe3+ { [%csl Ge8][%cal Ge3e8] } 11... Qe7 12. bxc8=Q+ Rxc8 13. Qxe7+ Bxe7 { white is up a bishop and has a very comfortable position. } *


