3... dxe4 4. Nxe4 Nf6 { This is the most popular move, and most intermediate and advanced players will go for it. Black doesn’t mind getting doubled pawns after Nxf6, as they'll simply recapture with the e-pawn, freeing up the dark-squared bishop. In fact, the doubled pawns can become useful later on. This variation is sometimes referred to as the 'Tarkatower Variation.' We’ll explore 4...Nf6 in the upcoming chapters marked 📕. } { [%csl Re4][%cal Rf6e4] } *


