7... Nd5 { This is the best response from Black, simply blocking our light-squared bishop. From here, we can proceed with standard development and castle. } { [%csl Gd5] } 8. d4 { Freeing the DSB and taking control of the center. } { [%csl Gd4,Gc1] } 8... Be7 9. O-O O-O 10. Bd3 { The light-squared bishop isn't as effective on the a2-g8 diagonal anymore, so placing it on d3 will be much more active. It supports potential attacks on the kingside. } { [%csl Gd3] } 10... h6 11. Ne4 $14 { We have a very flexible position here with many options. The e5 square could serve as a strong outpost, and playing f4 might be a future plan. The dark-squared bishop can be fianchettoed on b2, and there's potential for expansion on the queenside. The position is quite equal, but White has maintained their initial edge. } { [%csl Gd3,Ge4,Gf3,Ge2,Gg8,Gd5,Rc8][%cal Bf3e5,Bf2f4,Bc2c3,Bc3c4,Ba2a3,Bb2b3,Bf1e1,Ba3a4,Bc1b2] } *


