{ We’ve covered most of the important lines following 3...dxe4. Now, let’s move on to exploring the other options Black might play on the third move. }
3... Nf6?! { Black decides to play aggressively by immediately bringing out his knight and attacking our pawn. But this isn't that great because it allows us to kick the knight away. } { [%cal Rf6e4] } 4. e5! { Now Black is forced to move the knight. The two main options are Ne4 and Nd7. We’ll explore these moves in the following chapter marked with 📙. } *


