3... Bg4 { We’ve reached the final section! Here, we’re diving into the 3...Bg4 Mindeno Variation—the most popular choice at the Master level, and actually the most hardest variation to play against. The idea behind this move is for Black to trade their light-squared bishop for our knight, since, as you’ve seen in previous chapters, Black’s light-squared bishop often gets stuck on c8. However, this comes at the cost of giving us the bishop pair, and Black loses tempo in the process. We'll check out the Mindeno Variation in the upcoming chapters marked with 📓. } *


