6... Qb6 { The second most popular move, and really the only other one to consider. Be7 and Qb6 are pretty much the only moves you’ll ever face. Black develops the queen to an active square, attacking our b2 pawn while also saving it from attack. } { [%csl Rb2] } 7. dxc5! { We respond with this very surprising move, hanging the b2 pawn and allowing Black to set up a battery aiming at f2! } { [%csl Rb2,Rc5][%cal Bf8c5,Yb6f2] } 7... Qxb2? { We'll examine this move in this chapter. Black grabs the 'free' pawn, but it's poisoned! Now, we play a series of forcing moves. } 8. Nb5! { Threatening Nc7 (which also happens to be checkmate.) } { [%csl Bc7][%cal Rb5c7] } 8... Na6 { Covering c7. } { [%csl Rc7][%cal Ra6c7] } (8... Nxe5 9. Nd2! $18 { The queen is trapped! It's +2.0 We have an incredibly active and attacking position. } { [%csl Rd4,Rb1,Rc7,Rb4][%cal Bg5e3,Be3d4,Ba1b1,Rb1b2,Bb5c7,Ga2a3,Ra3b4] }) (8... Qb4+ { Black tries to maneuver the queen to a safe square. } { [%cal Bb4c5,Bc5c6] } 9. c3 { We continue hitting the queen with tempo. } { [%cal Rc3b4] } 9... Qxc5 10. Be3! { [%csl Rc5][%cal Ge3c5] } 10... Qc6 11. Nfd4 { [%csl Rc6][%cal Rd4c6] } 11... Qb6 12. Nxe6 { [%csl Rb6][%cal Re3b6] } 12... Qxe6 13. Nc7+! $18 { [%csl Re6,Re8][%cal Gc7e6,Gc7e8] }) (8... Bxc5 9. Rb1! { Instead of playing Nc7+ immediately, we can throw in this zwischenzug, forcing the queen onto a worse square. } 9... Qxa2 (9... Bb4+ 10. Ke2 Qxa2 11. Rxb4 $18) 10. Nc7+ Kf8 11. Nxa8 $18) 9. Rb1! { Hitting the queen. You'll see the purpose of this move soon. a2 is the only safe square left. } { [%csl Rb2,Ga2][%cal Rb1b2] } 9... Qxa2 10. Ra1 { [%csl Ra6,Ra2][%cal Ra1a6] } 10... Qb2 11. Rxa6! { Sacrificing the rook! Removing the defender of c7. } 11... bxa6 (11... f6 { Blocking our bishop, creating escape squares. But now e6 is left hanging. } { [%csl Rg5][%cal Be8f7,Be8e7] } 12. Rxe6+ $18 { We are completely winning. } { [%csl Rd5,Ge6,Rc1,Gb5,Re8,Rc8,Rd7,Rf8][%cal Bd1d5,Bg5c1,Be5f6] }) (11... Bxc5 { Creating an escape square. } { [%csl Gf8][%cal Ge8f8] } 12. Nc7+! { Taking away Black's castling rights and hitting the rook. We don't win it tho, because our own is still hanging. } 12... Kf8 13. Ra1 $18 { We simply bring the rook back to safety. We have a material advantage, and Black has many weaknesses. Although, you still have to be careful here! For example, if Bb4+, you MUST play Ke2, any other move, and White’s position will crumble. } { [%csl Rf8,Rc8,Rd7,Gc7][%cal Ba1b1] }) 12. Nc7# { Checkmate! } { [%csl Ge8,Yd8,Ye7,Rf8,Rf7,Rd7][%cal Gc7e8,Yg5d8] } *


