{ 🏰 This is the preferred setup we aim for. Notice the solid pawn structure, the strategically placed dark-squared bishop targeting black's kingside, and the queen ready to maneuver to h5 or g4. Additionally, white can potentially perform an artificial rook lift with Rf3-Rh3/Rg3.

🔄 The light-squared bishop (LSB) may often be traded.

We stick to this setup almost every time, making it easy to remember!

🚫 However, there are a few exceptions when we deviate from this plan, and I'll cover those as well. } { [%csl Rf3,Gb2,Ge5,Gg1,Gc2,Gd3,Ge3,Gf4,Yb5][%cal Bd1f3,Bf3g4,Bg4h5,Rf1f3,Rf3h3,Bd1h5,Bd1e1,Be1g3] }
 *


