2. Nf3 g6! { When Black fianchettos their dark-squared bishop, we can't follow our usual setup this time due to potential issues with the a1-h8 diagonal. } 3. g3! { This is the simplest non-complicated way. We just fianchetto too. } 3... Bg7 { [%csl Bg2][%cal Bf1g2] } 4. Bg2 Nf6 { Black gets ready to castle. } 5. O-O { Our king is now brought to safety. } 5... O-O 6. d3! { This move supports a future e4 push and also let's the DSB breathe. } { [%csl Be4][%cal Bd3e4] } 6... c5 7. Qe1! { Qe1 prepares for a future e4 push. It's an equal game, with chances for either side. I won't go more in dept, because that would be way too much to memorize. } { [%csl Be4][%cal Be2e4,Bb1a3,Bc2c3] } *


