2. fxe5! Qh4+?! 3. g3 Be7!? { A nice try from black, but it's bad. This allows white to gain lot's of tempi by kicking the queen away. } 4. d4! { Simply protecting e5, the queen is still under attack. } { [%csl Ge5,Gd4][%cal Gd4e5] } (4. gxh4?? { Yum, a free queen! } 4... Bxh4# { It's checkmate! Over 30,000 players have been the victim of this. :D } { [%csl Ge1,Gf2,Rf1,Re2,Rd2,Rd1][%cal Gh4e1] }) 4... Qe4 (4... Qh5 5. Nh3 { rerouting to f4 } { [%csl Gf4][%cal Gh3f4] } 5... d6 6. Nf4 Qf5 7. Bh3 Qe4 8. Bg2! { We just continue kicking the queen! } 8... Qf5 9. e4 { Another punch! } { [%csl Gf5][%cal Ge4f5] } 9... Qd7 10. Bh3 Qd8 11. e6 fxe6 12. Qh5+ g6 13. Nxg6 Nf6 14. Qh4 $18) 5. Nf3! { A developing move and the only move that saves the rook. } 5... d6 { At this point all white has to do is hit the queen away :) } 6. Nc3 { developing and gaining tempo. } { [%csl Ge4][%cal Gc3e4] } 6... Qg6 (6... Qc6 7. e4 { Again an amazing position for white. } { [%csl Ge4,Gd4,Ge5] }) (6... Qf5 7. e4 { White has a massive center, two horsies developed, and almost ready to castle. } { [%csl Gd4,Ge4,Ge5] }) 7. Nd5 { Throwing another punch. } { [%csl Gc7][%cal Gd5c7] } 7... Na6 { Black's knight is really bad at the rim. } { [%csl Rc7,Ra6][%cal Ra6c7] } (7... Bd8 8. Nf4 Qg4 (8... Qh6 9. e4 g5 10. Nd5 $16 { it's pretty clear white's better :) } { [%csl Ge5,Ge4,Gd4,Gf3][%cal Bf1g2,Be1g1] }) 9. Bh3 { The queen is trapped! } { [%csl Gg4,Gf5,Ge6,Gd7,Yh3,Yh5,Yg6,Rg3,Rh2,Rf4,Bh4,Bg5,Rf3][%cal Gh3c8,Yf4h3,Yf4h5,Yf4g6,Bf3h4,Bf3g5,Re2f3] }) 8. Bg2 { Preparing to castle. It's really hard for black to develop. } { [%csl Bg1][%cal Be1g1] } 8... dxe5 9. Nxe5 Qe6 10. c3 { White's position is wonderful. White can develop really easily, and every piece is well placed. } { [%csl Gc3,Gd4,Gb2,Yd5,Ye5,Bg2,Bg1,Rc8,Ra6,Re8,Re7,Rg8,Re6][%cal Gb2c3,Gc3d4,Be1g1,Be2e4,Bc1f4] } *


