[UTCDate "2024.02.21"]
[UTCTime "09:25:23"]

4... Nf6! { This is pretty much the only good move. There are 2 ways to continue, Nf3 and O-O and you get a great game, or we can play g4! g4 is really great, but if black plays perfectly, much material gets traded off, and black has a comfortable position. So, I recommend to just go for 5. Nf3. } 5. Nf3 e6 (5... Nc6 6. Ng5! { The most trickiest move for black to deal with. } 6... h6?? (6... e6? { A very common mistake. We make use of tactics again. } 7. Bxh7! { [%csl Rh5] } 7... Nxh7 (7... Rxh7 8. Nxh7 Nxh7 9. Qh5+ { A fork! White wins the exchange. } { [%csl Ge8,Gh7][%cal Gh5e8,Gh5h7] }) 8. Qh5+ { Forcing the king to come take a long walk. } { [%csl Rf7,Re8][%cal Bh5f7] } 8... Ke7 { DON'T TAKE THE KNIGHT ON H7, that would be a HUGE throw. } 9. Qf7+! { Simply going for checkmate. } 9... Kd6 10. Ne4+ { Bringing the king closer. } 10... Kd5 $7 11. Nbc3+ { Closer... } { [%csl Ge4,Rd5][%cal Gc3e4,Gc3d5] } 11... Kc4 12. Qh5! { Checkmate is unstoppable. If black does something to block our queen from going to b5, we just go to e2 and checkmate will come at some point. } { [%csl Bb5,Be2][%cal Bh5b5,Bh5e2] }) (6... g6! 7. O-O $13 { You get a good game. } { [%csl Gg1,Gg5,Gd3,Rf7,Re8][%cal Bf4f5,Bg5h7,Bb1c3] }) 7. Bg6# { Checkmate! Many players will actually fall for something very similar to this. } { [%csl Ge8,Gg6][%cal Gg6e8] }) 6. Ng5 Bc5?! { The most popular move, black prepares to castle. Black has missed something though. } (6... Be7?? { Chocking the king. The king hasn't much room to breathe. } { [%csl Re7,Rd8,Rd7] } 7. Bxh7! { making use of tactics again. } { [%csl Rh5,Rf7][%cal Bd1h5] } 7... Rxh7 { Black's sacs the rook for 2 minor pieces. } (7... Nxh7 { Results in mate in 3. } 8. Qh5+ g6 9. Qxg6+ Kf8 10. Qf7# { Checkmate! } { [%csl Gf8,Ge8,Gg8,Bf7,Gg7,Re7][%cal Gf7f8,Gf7e8,Gf7g8,Bg5f7,Gf7g7] }) 8. Nxh7 Nxh7 { Black is temporarily up material, but the black's diagonal is too weak, so we get the classic fork again. } { [%csl Rf7,Rg6,Rh5,Rh7] } 9. Qh5+ $18 { White wins material. } { [%csl Ge8,Gh7][%cal Gh5e8,Gh5h7] }) 7. Nxh7! { Grabbing the free pawn by making use of tactics! } 7... Nxh7? (7... Nc6! { Black just ignores everything. It's the best thing to do. } 8. Bg6+ { Forcing black to bongcloud. } 8... Ke7 $7 9. Ng5 $13 { Sockfish says it's equal, but white's winrate speaks for itself. } { [%csl Re7,Rc8,Rd8] }) 8. Qh5+ { A fork! White again makes use of exposed king. } { [%csl Gc5,Ge8][%cal Gh5c5,Gh5e8] } 8... Kf8 { Make sure NOT TO TAKE the knight on h7. That would be a HUGE mistake. White would just self-pin the queen, which leads to a bunch of bad stuff. } 9. Qxc5+! d6 10. Qh5 { Pinning the knight. } { [%csl Rh7] } 10... Kg8 { Protecting the rook and knight. } 11. Qe2 $16 { Simply retreating. Next up is Nc3-Be3 and O-O-O, then just launch a kingside attack. White has a +1 advantage. } { [%csl Rg7,Rg8,Rh8,Rh7,Bc1][%cal Bb1c3,Bc1e3,Be1c1] } *


