{ Welcome ladies and gentlemen to my newest study! Hi, I'm Bosburp!

Today, we'll continue our 1. e4 repertoire. In this study we're going to learn how to PUNISH the Philidor Defense. I'll share a incredibly FUN, aggressive gambit with sky-high winrates that will make you look forward to facing it!

If you find this study helpful, please give it a heart 💓 under the pinned comment! It helps more players discover this study and adds it to your favorites so you can always find it easily.💓500 likes for the next study! 😉

If you have any questions or feedback, feel free to DM me! 💬

Also, join our team for more awesome studies: https://lichess.org/team/study-creators--friends

Let's start! Play 1. e4! 🚀 }
1. e4 { "Best by test" as Bobby Fisher says. } 1... e5 { Play 2. Nf3 :) } { [%csl Gf3][%cal Gg1f3] } 2. Nf3 d6 { Ok, welcome to the Philidor Defense! It is actually quite a popular opening for Black, the second most played move after 2...Nc6. It's known for being a solid choice for Black, already creating a solid pawn chain. Personally, I have found this opening very annoying to face, and that is why this study was created.
So, I'm gonna show you how to PUNISH it! :D
The study is divided into 3 sections. Remember that when you're done with the study and revisit it in the future, you can look for your desired move by typing it in the magnifying glass next to the a8 square.
Feel free to use the engine and the Lichess database, and don't forget to explore the variations! 🕵
🔥 Get this entire repertoire for FREE in Noctie and practice it through gameplay: https://go.noctie.ai/punish-philidor-full-repertoire 🔥
There’s a lot packed into this study, so don’t worry about memorizing everything. Focus on understanding the key ideas instead. It’s nearly impossible to remember every single line, but I’ve given you almost everything you need. Take what you can, and trust that the ideas will guide you in your games.
LSB = Light-Squared-Bishop
DSB = Dark-Squared-Bishop
P.S. My lines will not always be the absolute top engine move, they are rather based on which one is more comfortable to play as a human and have a decent winrate.
P.P.S. The OGs might remember I made a study on this 2–3 years ago. Yes, you're absolutely right! It didn’t get popular back then (bad timing and all), but this is a better version that’ll hopefully reach more people. 🙂
Hit that space bar! 🚀 } { [%csl Ye5,Yd6,Yc7][%cal Gd6e5,Gc7d6] } *


