5... Be7? { Black intends to get one step closer to castling, the problem with this move is that the queen can now no longer go to e7 or f6 to defend the f7 pawn. } 6. Qb3! { This is the only move that keeps the advantage! white immediately attacks the f7 pawn and there is no way to defend it! } 6... Be6? { The most popular move, but it doesn't really do anything other than leave the b7 pawn undefended too. } 7. Bxe6 fxe6 { At this point 3 pawns are already ready to grab, but we should be patient and play this very IMPORTANT move. } { [%csl Rc3,Re6,Rb7] } 8. Nd4! { Qxe6 would lose all the advantage because after 8...cxb2 9. Bxb2 Qd7! and White has no attack ongoing anymore. White's dream is to have an octopus knight on e6. } { [%csl Ge6][%cal Gd4e6,Gb3e6] } 8... e5 { Saving the e pawn and hitting the knight. } (8... Qd7? 9. Qxb7 $18 { Black just gave away a free rook! } { [%csl Ga8][%cal Gb7a8] }) (8... d5 { The second most popular move. We can go ahead and grab the free pawn on b7 now. } 9. Qxb7 Nd7 10. Nxe6 { A triple fork. } { [%csl Gd8,Gg7,Gc7][%cal Ge6d8,Ge6g7,Ge6c7] } 10... Qc8 11. Nxc7+ Kf8 12. Qxa8 Qxa8 13. Nxa8 $18 { White has an extra rook on the board. }) (8... Bf6 9. Nxe6 { [%csl Gd8][%cal Ge6d8] } 9... Qc8 (9... Qd7 10. Nxc3 $16 { [%cal Be1g1,Bb2c3,Bf2f4] }) 10. Nxc3 Nc6 11. Nd5 { [%csl Gc7,Gf6][%cal Gd5c7,Ge6c7,Gd5f6] } 11... Nd4 12. Nxf6+ Nxf6 13. Nxd4 $18) 9. Ne6! { We hop in here anyway! } { [%csl Gd8,Gc7,Gf8,Gg7][%cal Ge6d8,Ge6c7,Ge6f8,Ge6g7] } 9... Qd7 (9... Qc8 10. Nxg7+ Kf8 11. Ne6+ Ke8 12. Nxc3 $18) 10. Qxb7! { Even better than Nxg7. } { [%csl Ga8,Yg7,Rc3][%cal Ye6g7,Gb7a8] } 10... Qc6 { A common move out of desperation, but every move loses. } (10... Qxe6 11. Qxa8 Qc8 12. Nxc3 $18) 11. Qxa8! { Of course, Nxc7! works just as well, but isn't this more fancier? ;) } 11... Qxa8 12. Nxc7+ { Winning the queen back immediately with a fork, } { [%csl Ga8,Ge8][%cal Gc7a8,Gc7e8] } 12... Kd7 13. Nxa8 cxb2 14. Bxb2 $18 { White is up a rook, with a great position. Black is probably going to win our trapped knight in the corner though. } *


