4... d3?! { Black doesn't want to take c3, because that would allow White's knight to be placed well. This is an attempt to dis coordinate White's pieces. This isn't a great idea, as the bishop is perfectly fine on d3. } 5. Bxd3! { Yup, we just grab it, and we are ready to castle. } { [%csl Bg1][%cal Be1g1] } 5... Nf6 6. O-O! { The king is safe now. } 6... Be7 7. h3 { As I say in a lot of my studies, h3 is almost always a good move. Preventing Bg4, and creating a breathing hole for the king. } { [%csl Rg4] } 7... O-O 8. Bf4 Nc6 9. Nbd2 h6 10. Re1 $16 { A very comfortable setup. Black's bishops don't have any good squares and his central control isn't too strong. White can now expand on the queenside, and Nf1 is also a good developing idea. } { [%csl Gf4,Gf3,Gd3,Re7][%cal Ba2a4,Bd3c2,Bd2f1] } *


