4... Bg4 { The Janowski-Larsen Variation. Black pins the f3 knight. } 5. Bxc4! { Taking the free pawn and getting ready to castle. } 5... e6 { Freeing up the DSB. } { [%csl Gf8] } (5... Bxf3?! 6. Qxf3 $16 { [%csl Gf3,Gc4,Bg1,Rf8,Re8,Rd8,Rb8,Ra8,Rh8][%cal Be1g1,Bb1c3,Bb2b3,Bc1b2] }) (5... c6?? 6. Bxf7+! { Forcing black's king to come forward. } 6... Kxf7 7. Ne5+ { A fork! } { [%csl Gf7][%cal Ge5f7,Bd1g4,Ye5g4] } 7... Ke8 8. Nxg4 Nxg4 9. Qxg4 { White is up a pawn with an amazing position. } { [%csl Gg4] }) 6. O-O { [%csl Gg1] } 6... Be7 7. h3 { Kicking away the bishop. } { [%csl Gg4][%cal Gh3g4] } 7... Bh5 (7... Bxf3?! 8. Qxf3 $16 { The queen is now developed. Next up is Rd1 and push e3-e4. } { [%csl Gf3][%cal Bf1d1,Be3e4,Bb1c3] }) 8. Nc3 { Developing. } { [%csl Gc3] } 8... O-O $14 { Next up is g4, or if you fell uncomfortable with that you can just gain space by expanding on the queenside with a3-b4. } { [%csl Bb4,Ba3,Bg4][%cal Bg2g4,Ba2a3,Bb2b4] } *


