3... c5 { The Gunsberg Defense, it's the 3rd most popular move. } 4. e3 { Attacking c4 and supporting d4. } { [%csl Bd4,Bc4][%cal Be3d4,Bf1c4] } 4... cxd4 (4... Nf6 5. Bxc4 { We just grab this. } 5... Bg4?? (5... cxd4 6. exd4 e6 7. Nc3 Nc6 8. O-O $16 { White has transposed to the same position as mentioned in the variation below. }) 6. Ne5!! { [%csl Rd1,Gg4,Bf7][%cal Ge5g4,Gd1g4,Be5f7,Bc4f7] } 6... Bxd1 { Oh no my queen!! } (6... Be6 7. Qa4+! { [%csl Gd7][%cal Ge5d7] } 7... Nbd7 8. Bxe6 fxe6 9. O-O $18 { White has an amazing position. Black has doubled pawns, and has a lot of trouble developing. } { [%csl Gg1,Ga4,Ge5,Re6,Re7,Rd8,Re8,Rf8,Rd7] }) 7. Bxf7# { Checkmate! } { [%csl Ge8,Gf7,Gd7,Rd8,Re7,Rf8][%cal Gf7e8,Ge5f7,Ge5d7] }) 5. Bxc4 dxe3?? { The MOST popular move! White has a nice way to immediately win the game. The most popular move for white now is Qxd8??, which would just throw the win away. } (5... Nc6 { The second most popular move. Black also protects the queen so that nothing wrong can happen. } { [%csl Gd8][%cal Gc6d8] } 6. exd4 Bg4?? { The most popular move. White has a veryyy beautiful trap now, it start with d5! } (6... e6 7. O-O Nf6 8. Nc3 $14 { We get a good game, Stockfish gives white a 0.5 advantage. White does have an isolated queen's pawn, we usually play d5 at some point. } { [%csl Gg1,Gf3,Gc4,Gc3,Gd4][%cal Bd4d5] }) (6... Nf6? 7. d5 Na5 8. Bb5+ Bd7 9. Qa4 b6 10. Ne5 $16 { [%csl Ge5,Gb5,Ga4,Ra5,Rd7,Rf6,Re8,Rd8,Rf8,Bg5,Bf4][%cal Be1g1,Bb1c3,Bc1g5] }) 7. d5! { Note that Bxf7 would have worked too, but this is a bit better :) } 7... Ne5 { Played 54% of the time! It looks like white is in a bit of trouble. White can't take the knight on e5 because our knight is pinned........ or can we? } { [%csl Rd1,Rf3][%cal Rg4d1] } (7... Bxf3 8. Qxf3 Ne5 9. Bb5+ Nd7 10. O-O $18 { White has an amazing position. } { [%csl Rd8,Rd7,Re8,Rg8,Rf8,Rh8,Ra8,Gf3,Gd5,Gb5,Gg1] }) 8. Nxe5!! Bxd1 (8... Qa5+ 9. Bd2! $18 { [%csl Rg4,Ra5][%cal Gd2a5] }) 9. Bb5+! { White dominates the d7 square, the only legal move for black is Qd7. } { [%csl Ge8,Gd7][%cal Gb5e8,Ge5d7] } 9... Qd7 10. Bxd7+ Kd8 11. Kxd1 $18 { It's +10 for white. } { [%csl Rf7,Rh8][%cal Be5f7,Bf7h8] }) 6. Bxf7+!! { The only winning move! White simply forces the black king to leave his queen unprotected. } 6... Kxf7 $7 { The only legal move. } 7. Qxd8 $18 { White can happily grab that queen, it's time for black to resign ;D } { [%csl Gd8,Rc8,Ra8,Rb8,Rg8,Rf8,Rh8,Rf7] } *


