3... a6 { A much more rarer move online, but it is important to note that this is the second most popular move in the master's database. :) Black prepares to play b5 at some point, or just prevent any piece from white getting to b5. } { [%csl Bb5][%cal Ra6b5,Bb7b5] } 4. e3 { Opening the LSB } { [%csl Gf1,Rc4] } 4... b5?! { The most popular move online, it's not really great because of our response. } { [%csl Bb5,Bc4,Ba6] } (4... Nf6 { The best move. } 5. Bxc4 { We grab the free pawn. } 5... b5 (5... e6 6. O-O { [%csl Gd4,Ge3,Gf2][%cal Gf2e3,Ge3d4] }) 6. Be2 Bb7 7. a4! { Gaining space on the queenside. White gets a good game. }) (4... Bg4 5. h3 Bh5 6. Bxc4 $16 { White gets a good game. } { [%csl Bg1,Gc4,Rh5,Ra8,Rb8,Rd8,Rf8,Re8,Rg8,Rh8,Yf2,Ye3,Yd4,Gf3,Ba3,Bb2][%cal Be1g1,Yf2e3,Ye3d4,Bb2b3,Bc1a3,Bc1b2,Bb1d2,Bb1c3] }) (4... e6 5. Bxc4 $16 { [%csl Gf3,Gc4,Bg1,Ra8,Rb8,Rc8,Rd8,Re8,Rf8,Rg8,Rh8][%cal Be1g1] }) 5. a4! { gaining space on the queenside. Black's queenside is now weakened. } { [%csl Ga4,Rb5,Rc4] } 5... Bb7 (5... Bd7? 6. Ne5! { Getting rid of the LSB. } 6... c6 (6... Bc6 7. Nxc6 Nxc6 8. Qf3! { Hitting the knight. } 8... Nb4 9. axb5! Nc2+ 10. Kd1 Nxa1 11. Qc6+! { Forcing the queen away from the rook. } 11... Qd7 12. Qxa8+) 7. axb5 { axb5 loses the rook. } 7... cxb5 8. Qf3! { Threatening mate and hitting the rook. } { [%csl Rf7,Ga8][%cal Bf3f7,Re5f7,Gf3a8] } 8... f6 9. Qh5+! g6 10. Nxg6 $18 { A completely winning position for white. }) (5... c6 6. axb5 cxb5 7. b3! $16 { White wins back the sacrificed pawn in all lines. } { [%csl Bc4,Bb3,Ra8,Rb8,Rc8,Rd8,Rf8,Re8,Rg8,Rh8][%cal Bd1a4,Ba4c4,Ba4e8] }) 6. b3! { White wins back the sacrificed pawn in all lines. Stockfish gives white a 0.6 advantage. White has a 53% winrate. } *


