3... b5 { This move is a pretty bad choice, the Slav Gambit. Black is trying to really hang on to the pawn. } 4. a4! { White attacks Black's pawn structure on the queenside. } 4... c6 { Defending. } (4... b4 { [%csl Gd3] } 5. e4! { White controls the center. Black has 2 weak pawns to worry about. } { [%csl Ge4,Gd4,Gf3,Rc4,Rb4][%cal Bf1c4] }) (4... Bd7? 5. axb5 Bxb5 6. Nc3 c6 7. d5 Qb6 8. e4 $16 { [%csl Ge4,Gd5,Gc3,Gf3,Rb5,Rb6,Rc6,Rc4,Ga1] }) 5. axb5 { Opening up the rook. } 5... cxb5 { [%csl Ga1] } 6. Nc3 { White develops a knight, putting pressure on the b5 pawn. } 6... Bd7?! { Black defends with Bd7. This is the most popular move, but we have a nice response. } (6... Qb6 { Protecting b5. This is the only move that doesn't give black a huge advantage. } 7. b3! { White is slightly better. } { [%csl Rc4,Rb5,Ga1][%cal Be2e4] }) (6... b4?? 7. Qa4+! Bd7 8. Qxb4 { White is obviously better. } { [%csl Gb4,Ga1,Gf3,Gc3,Rc4,Ra8,Rb8,Rd8,Re8,Rf8,Rg8,Rh8,Rd7][%cal Be2e4] }) (6... a6?? { An attempt to hang on to b5, but it fails. } 7. Nxb5 $16 { Black can't take the knight because of the pin. } { [%csl Rb5,Ba8][%cal Ra6b5,Ba1a8] }) 7. Ne5! { Trying to get rid of the LSB, which is defending b5. } 7... e6 (7... Nc6 8. Nxd7 { Trading the bishop. } 8... Qxd7 9. Nxb5 $16 { White has a nice position. } { [%csl Gb5,Rc4][%cal Be2e3,Bf1c4] }) 8. e3 { White prepares to play Qf3. } { [%csl Bf3][%cal Bd1f3] } 8... Bb4?? { The most popular move by a huge margin. It's a blunder because of our response. } (8... Nf6?? { The second most popular move. } 9. Qf3 $18 { White wins a piece in all lines, black can resign. } { [%csl Be5,Ra8,Rc6][%cal Be5c6,Rf3a8] }) (8... a6 9. Qf3! $18 { [%csl Ga8,Gf7][%cal Gf3a8,Gf3f7] }) 9. Qf3! { It's pretty much over at this point. White threatens mate in uno on f7 and hits the undefended rook in the corner. } { [%csl Ra8,Rf7] } 9... Bxc3+ 10. bxc3 f6 (10... Nf6 11. Qxa8 $18) 11. Qh5+ g6 (11... Ke7 { Leads to mate. } 12. Ba3+ { [%csl Ge7][%cal Ga3e7] } 12... b4 13. Bxb4# { Checkmate! } { [%csl Gf8,Ge7,Gd6,Be8,Rf6,Re6,Rd8,Rd7,Bf7][%cal Gb4f8,Bh5e8] }) 12. Nxg6 { Exploiting the pin. } { [%cal Rh7g6,Bh5h8] } 12... hxg6 13. Qxh8 $18 { White's completely winning. } *


