3... Be7 { This is the Charousek Variation or also known as the Alatortsev Variation. } 4. cxd5 { Exchanging the pawns. } 4... exd5 5. Bf4 { Developing, getting the DSB out before we build the pawn chain with e3. } { [%csl Gf4] } 5... c6 { Keeping everything solid. } { [%csl Gd5,Gc6,Gb7][%cal Gb7c6,Gc6d5] } 6. e3 { [%csl Ge3,Gd4][%cal Gf2e3,Ge3d4] } 6... Bf5 7. g4! { The best move! kicking away the bishop and also if black were to play Nf6 we would push the g pawn further. } { [%cal Bg4g5,Bg4f5] } 7... Bg6?! { We have an amazing response! } (7... Be6 8. Bd3 { Developing. } 8... Nf6?! (8... Nd7 9. h3 { Keeping everything intact. It's an equal game. } { [%csl Gg4,Gh3,Ge3,Gd4,Gf2][%cal Gh3g4,Gf2e3,Ge3d4] }) (8... h5 9. Qb3! { Hitting b7. } { [%csl Gb7][%cal Gb3b7] } 9... Qb6 10. g5 { saving the g pawn. } 10... Qxb3 11. axb3 { We now have an open file for the rook. } { [%csl Ga1] } 11... Nd7 12. Nf3 $16 { [%csl Gf3,Gc3,Gf4,Ga1,Bh4,Rb3,Rb2,Re7,Rd7,Rg8,Re6][%cal Bh2h4] }) 9. g5! { Pushing further, gaining space. } 9... Nfd7 10. h4 $16 { We have a great position. White has plenty of space on the kingside and a very solid structure, black's pieces are all cramped up together. } { [%csl Rd7,Re7,Re6,Re8,Rd8,Rb8,Gf4,Gd3,Ye3,Yd4,Yf2,Yg5,Yh4,Gc3][%cal Yf2e3,Ye3d4,Yh4g5] }) 8. h4!! { Threatening to trap the bishop, if black takes it then... } { [%cal Bh4h5] } 8... Bxh4? 9. Qb3! { The only winning move! } { [%csl Rb7,Rd8][%cal Gb3b7] } 9... b6 { Any move that defends b6 is bad. } (9... b5 { This line is pretty much the same. } 10. Rxh4 Qxh4 11. Nxb5 cxb5 12. Bxb5+ Nd7 13. Bxd7+ Kxd7 14. Qxd5+ { [%csl Gf4,Rd7,Ra8][%cal Gd5a8,Gd5d7] }) (9... Be7 10. Qxb7 Nd7 { White is completely dominating this game. } { [%csl Gf4,Gb7,Gh1,Rd7,Rd8,Re8,Re7,Ra8,Rg6,Rg8] }) 10. Rxh4!! { Luring the queen out! } 10... Qxh4 11. Nxd5!! { Sacrificing the next piece! } 11... cxd5 12. Bb5+! { A deadly punch! Black has no good way to block the check. } 12... Nd7 (12... Kf8 13. Qxd5 { Hitting the rook } { [%csl Ra8] } 13... Nc6 { The only way to "save" it. } 14. Bd6+! Nge7 15. Qxc6 { Exploiting the pin. } { [%csl Gf8][%cal Rd6f8] } 15... Rd8 16. Qc7 { [%csl Gd8][%cal Gc7d8] } 16... Ra8 17. Bc6 { The rook is trapped. Black's position will surely crumble very soon. } { [%csl Ga8,Ge8,Bb8,Bd8,Bc8,Rf8,Re7][%cal Gc6a8,Gc6e8,Bc7d8,Bc7b8,Bc7c8,Rd6f8] }) 13. Bxd7+ Kxd7 { The king is now out in the open. } 14. Qxd5+ $18 { The attack is way too strong and black's king is completely out in the open. } { [%csl Ga8,Rd7,Gf4][%cal Gd5a8,Gd5d7,Ba1c1] } *


