3... dxc4?! { Black changes their mind and decides to take c4 anyway \(._.)/ } 4. e4 { Taking the center. } { [%csl Ge4,Gd4] } 4... Nf6 (4... e5 5. Nf3 { Two of black's pawn's are left hanging } { [%csl Re5,Rc4][%cal Gf3e5,Gf1c4] } 5... exd4 6. Nxd4 Bc5 7. Be3 Nf6 8. Bxc4 O-O 9. f3 $16 { All white's pieces are developed, black's queenside is still undeveloped. } { [%csl Yf3,Ye4,Yg2,Bg1,Ge3,Gd4,Gc4,Gc3,Ra8,Rb8,Rc8,Rd8][%cal Yg2f3,Yf3e4,Be1g1] }) (4... Bb4 5. Bxc4 $16 { White is doing very well. } { [%csl Gc4,Gd4,Ge4,Bg1][%cal Bg1f3,Be1g1] }) 5. Bxc4 Bb4 6. e5! { White pushes the e5 pawn, gaining space and hitting the knight on f6. } { [%cal Ge5f6] } 6... Nd5 { Black defends the knight with Nd5. } 7. Ne2 $16 { Supporting the c3 knight. Stockfish gives +1 for white. White can castle on the next move and start an attack on the kingside with f4, or start gaining some sapce on the queenside with h3-b4. } { [%csl Gc3,Gc4,Bg1,Bf4,Ye5,Yd4,Ra8,Rb8,Rc8,Rd8,Bg8][%cal Be1g1,Bf2f4,Bc1d2,Ba2a3,Yd4e5,Be8g8] } *


