5... Bg4 { The Steiner Variation. } 6. Ne5 { Hitting the bishop, usually black wants to keep it. } { [%csl Rg4] } 6... Bh5 7. g3 { f3, also works, but it leads to very long and doubled-edged lines. This is the most safe and non-complicated move. We just try to castle as soon as possible. } { [%csl Bg2][%cal Bf1g2] } 7... e6 (7... Nbd7 8. Nxc4! $14 { We get a good game! } { [%csl Gc4,Gc3,Bg2][%cal Bf1g2] }) (7... Na6 8. Bg2 { Next is O-O. or take the c pawn at some point. } { [%csl Bg1][%cal Be1g1] }) 8. Bg2 { Preparing to castle. } { [%csl Bg1][%cal Be1g1] } 8... Bb4 (8... a5 9. Nxc4 Bb4 10. O-O $14 { [%csl Gc4,Gc3,Gg2] }) 9. Nxc4 { We get a good game. The position is about equal. } { [%csl Gc4,Gc3,Bg1][%cal Be1g1] } *


