5... e6 { Black wants to open up the DSB, the big downside of this move is that the LSB is now sad. } { [%csl Rc8,Gf8,Re6] } 6. e4! { Taking the center, freeing the LSB, attacking c4, and not locking up the DSB. } { [%csl Gd4,Ge4,Gf1,Gc1] } 6... Bb4 { The best move, all other moves give white a +1 advantage. Black pins the knight, meaning the e4 pawn is left undefended. } { [%csl Rc3,Re4][%cal Rb4e1] } 7. e5 { Kicking away the knight. } 7... Nd5 (7... Ne4 8. Qc2 Nxc3 9. bxc3 Be7 10. Bxc4 { Black just helped us build this nice pawnchain! We can castle on the next move, and we get a great game! } { [%csl Gc3,Gd4,Ge5,Bg1,Re7,Rd8,Rc8,Rb8,Ra8,Gf3,Gc4,Gc2][%cal Gc3d4,Gd4e5,Be1g1] }) 8. Bd2 $10 { White is doing great! The position is equal, but white's the one with a 54% winrate! Black's LSB and b8 knight are a bit stuck. } { [%csl Rc4,Bg1,Gf3,Rc8,Rb8][%cal Be1g1,Bf1c4] } *


