5... Na6?! { The Smyslov Variation, it doesn't really do much. } 6. e4 { Taking the center and getting ready to grab c4. } { [%csl Ge4,Gd4,Rc4] } 6... Bg4 { Pinning the knight. } 7. Bxc4 e6 (7... Bxf3 8. gxf3 { Keeping the d pawn protected. Qxf3 is totally playable though. } 8... e6 9. O-O { White has a great position, the doubled f pawns really aren't that bad, black doesn't have a LSB to take advantage of it. White can use the open g file for good after black castles. This position has been reached 26 times in the masters database and white has a 62% winrate! } { [%csl Gc4,Gd4,Ge4,Gf3,Gc3,Ra6,Rd8,Re8,Rf8][%cal Gf3e4] }) 8. Bxa6! { It's not good to exchange bishops for knights on the rim, but it's great now because it gives white a bunch of advantages! } 8... bxa6 $16 { Black has doubled isolated a pawns and a single isolated c pawn. White has the center, and is ready to castle. } { [%csl Ra6,Ra7,Rc6,Ge4,Gd4,Gc3,Gf3,Bg1][%cal Be1g1] } *


