3... Bf5?! { Black wants to get the bishop out before closing the door with e6. This is not so great because of white's next 2 moves. } 4. cxd5! cxd5 (4... Qxd5 5. Nc3 { Gaining tempo. } 5... Qa5 6. Bd2 e6 7. e4 $18 { [%csl Ge4,Gd4,Gf3,Gc3,Gd2,Rf5,Ra5,Re8,Rf8,Rg8,Rh8,Rb8,Ra8] }) 5. Qb3! { White already has a 66% winrate at this point. White aims at the weak b7 pawn. } { [%csl Rb7] } 5... b6?? (5... Qc8?! { Make sure not to hang the bishop! } { [%csl Rc1] } 6. Nc3 e6 7. Bf4 Nc6 (7... Na6?? 8. e4 dxe4 9. Bb5+ Kd8 10. Ne5 $18) 8. Nb5 $18 { Black can't stop Nc7. } { [%csl Bc7][%cal Bb5c7] }) (5... Bc8 6. e4 dxe4 7. Bb5+ Bd7 8. Ng5 e6 9. d5 Qa5+ 10. Nc3 Bxb5 11. dxe6! $16 { [%csl Rb5,Rf7] }) 6. e4!! { Sacrificing the pawn to make way for the LSB to join! } 6... Bxe4 7. Bb5+! Nd7 { More or less forced. } 8. Ne5 { At this point white just adds pressure to d7. It's +4.7 btw. } 8... Nf6 { The only way to protect d7. } 9. Nc3! { Attacking the bishop, it's hanging because if the pawn recaptures it's mate, and the knight can't leave d7. } { [%csl Re4,Rf7,Rd7,Rf6] } 9... Bxg2 (9... e6 10. Nxe4 Nxe4 (10... dxe4 11. Bg5 Be7 12. Bxf6 Bxf6 13. Nxd7) 11. Bxd7+) (9... Bf5 10. Nxd5 Nxd5 11. Qxd5 $18) 10. Rg1 { Saving the rook. } 10... Bh3 { [%csl Gd7,Gf6][%cal Gh3d7] } (10... Be4 11. Nxe4 Nxe4 (11... dxe4 12. Qxf7#) 12. Bxd7+ Qxd7 13. Nxd7) 11. Nxd5 { The rest is pretty straightforward. } 11... Be6 (11... Nxd5 12. Qxd5 Be6 13. Bxd7+ Bxd7 14. Qxf7#) 12. Nxf6+ exf6 13. d5 fxe5 14. dxe6 fxe6 15. Qxe6+ Qe7 (15... Be7 16. Rxg7 Rf8 17. Bg5 e4 18. Rxe7+ Qxe7 19. Qxe7#) 16. Bxd7+ Kd8 17. Bg5 { Mate will follow very soon, in fact with perfect play it's #7 } { [%csl Re7,Rd8] } *


