4... Bf5?! { Black wants to get the LSB before black closes the fortress with e6. } 5. Qb3! { Hitting b7. } { [%csl Rb7,Rd5] } 5... Qb6 (5... b6?? { Next comes a nice sequence. } 6. cxd5 cxd5 (6... Nxd5 7. e4 { [%csl Gd5,Gf5][%cal Ge4d5,Ge4f5] } 7... Nxc3 8. exf5 Nd5 9. Bd3 $16 { White's doing great! White has a 72% winrate. } { [%csl Bg1,Gf3,Gd3][%cal Be1g1] }) 7. e4! { Freeing up the LSB. } { [%csl Gf1] } 7... dxe4 8. Ne5 { Taking away these crucial squares and threatening mate in 1. } { [%csl Rc6,Rd7,Rf7][%cal Be5c6,Be5d7,Be5f7,Rb3f7] } 8... e6 (8... Be6 9. d5! Nxd5 10. Bb5+ Nd7 11. Nxd5 $18 { White is completely winning, it's +7 } { [%csl Rd8,Rd7,Re6,Re8,Rf8,Gd5,Ge5,Gb5,Gb3] }) 9. Bb5+! Nbd7 (9... Nfd7 10. g4! Bg6 11. h4 $18 { White is completely winning. h5/h6 lose due to Nxg6 fxg6, Qxe6. } { [%csl Rg6][%cal Be5g6,Bh4h5] }) 10. g4 Bxg4 11. Nxe4 $18 { White wins a piece in all lines. The f6 knight cannot leave the d7 knight undefended. } { [%csl Rd7,Rf6,Rg4,Rd8,Re8,Gb5,Gb3] }) (5... Qc7? 6. cxd5 cxd5 7. Bf4! { e4 is probably more accurate, but this is more simple. } 7... Qxf4 (7... Qb6 8. e3 { "To take is a mistake!", well, it's not that horrible in this position, but this is much better. } 8... Qxb3 9. axb3 e6 10. Bxb8 Rxb8 11. Bb5+ Kd8 { Nd7 loses due to Ne5. } 12. Ne5 $16 { White is just crushing black. } { [%csl Gb5,Ge5,Rf7,Rd8,Ga1,Bg1][%cal Be1g1] }) (7... Qd7?? 8. Bxb8! { Getting rid of any piece that can go to c6. } 8... Rxb8 9. e4!! { Clearing a way for Bb5. } { [%csl Bb5][%cal Bf1b5] } 9... dxe4 10. Bb5 exf3 11. gxf3 $18) 8. Qxb7 $18 { White wins the exchange and gets a great position. } { [%csl Ga8][%cal Gb7a8] }) 6. c5 Qxb3 7. axb3 $16 { White enjoys the open file. There are many options for white to do next, the arrows show them. } { [%csl Ga1,Be5][%cal Bb3b4,Be2e3,Bh2h3,Bg2g4,Bf3e5] } *


