5... Be7 { The most popular move online. Black simple blocks the pin. } 6. e3 { Making a solid pawn chain. } { [%csl Ge3,Gd4,Gf2][%cal Gf2e3,Ge3d4] } 6... O-O 7. Qc2 h6 { Kicking the bishop, we'll just leave it there. } 8. h4! { The classic fishing pole. } 8... hxg5?? { This allows white to get the open h file. } (8... Nbd7! { Developing! } 9. a3! $10 { Avoiding any annoying Bb4 or future pawn storm. The position is equal. } { [%csl Bc1,Bd3][%cal Be1c1,Bf1d3,Bc4d5,Bc4c5] }) 9. hxg5 { [%csl Rf6,Bh8][%cal Rg5f6,Bh1h8] } 9... Ne4 (9... g6 { Top-engine move. } 10. gxf6 Bxf6 11. Bd3! { Setting up a sneaky trap! Any random move like Na6/Nd7/Bd7/Be7/b7 is a blunder. } 11... Na6?? (11... Kg7 12. g4! $18 { White is much better. We can simply castle queenside and continue attacking on the kingside. } { [%csl Bc1][%cal Be1c1] }) 12. Bxg6! { Tearing down black's fortress! } 12... fxg6 13. Qxg6+ Bg7 $18 { It's mate in 11. }) 10. Nxe4 dxe4 11. Qxe4 f5 (11... g6 12. Qh4 { The mate is unstoppable. } { [%csl Bh8][%cal Bh1h8] }) 12. Qh4 $18 { There's no way black's gonna survive this without sacrificing. The only way would be to sacrifice a bunch of material and then white can easily win. } { [%csl Re5,Rh7,Rh8][%cal Yh1h8,Bg5g6,Rf3e5,Yh1h7] } *


