3... e6 { The Semi-Slav can be reached many different ways, some first play Nf6, some play e3 immediately. } 4. Nc3 { Bringing out the second knight. } { [%csl Gf3,Gc3] } 4... dxc4 { The Noteboom Variation. Since the Noteboom variation is quite complicated and has a lot of theory, we'll play g3! } 5. g3! { This is the Anti-Noteboom Gambit. White keeps things simple. } { [%cal Bf1g2,Be1g1] } 5... b5 (5... Nf6 6. Bg2 b5 7. O-O { Transposing. }) 6. Bg2 { Just continuing the plan. } 6... Nf6 { Black develops, we just castle. } 7. O-O Bb7 8. Ne5 { Placing the knight on a nice outpost in the center. } { [%csl Ge5,Gg2] } 8... a6 9. b3 $10 { It's an equal game. White's king is safely castled, and we have a fianchettoed LSB. b4 is always met with Na4. White has a 52% winrate. } { [%csl Gg1,Gg2,Ge5][%cal Bc1b2] } *


