2... e5!? { The Albin Countergambit! It rarely gets played at master level OTB, but it's actually quite an interesting weapon. The first advantage black gets immediately is that many QG players haven't prepared against this. If you are a QG player, you should definitely take some time to study this. } 3. dxe5 d4 { Black takes the c3 square from white. } { [%csl Rc3][%cal Rd4c3] } 4. Nf3! { White stays out of any trouble. } (4. e3? { Black's already better. I'll show a trap that many many players have fallen for. } 4... Bb4+! 5. Bd2 dxe3!! 6. Bxb4 { Wow, a free bishop! Sadly, no, white can resign now. } 6... exf2+! { If white takes the pawn, black wins the queen. } 7. Ke2 fxg1=N+!! { A brilliant move! This is actually the only move that wins on the spot. } 8. Rxg1 Bg4+ { White loses the lady. This is the Lasker Trap. }) 4... Nc6 5. g3! { The Fianchetto Variation. White avoids any tricks from black and keeps things simple. } { [%cal Bf1g2,Be1g1] } 5... Nge7 { Rerouting to g6. } { [%cal Be7g6] } (5... Be6?! { Black wants to castle queenside. } 6. Nbd2 { Keeping c4 protected. } { [%csl Gc4][%cal Gd2c4] } 6... Qd7 7. Bg2 { [%csl Gg2] } 7... O-O-O 8. O-O $16 { White has a 61% winrate. White has a solid kingside, and we can now start launching some pawns at the queenside. } { [%csl Gg1,Gg2,Gf3,Gd2,Ye5,Yc4,Yh2,Yg3,Yf2][%cal Yf2g3,Yh2g3,Bb2b4,Ba2a4,Bb4b5,Ba4a5] }) 6. Bg2 { We just continue developing. } 6... Ng6 7. O-O! { White's king is safe and we have a fianchetto'd LSB. Meanwhile, black for the last moves has just wasted time trying to win the e5 pawn back. } { [%csl Gg1,Gg2,Gf3,Rc8,Rd8,Re8,Rf8,Rg6] } 7... Ngxe5 8. Nxe5 Nxe5 9. Bf4 { Setting up a quick trap. } { [%csl Yc4] } 9... Nc6 (9... Nxc4?? { A nice trap you'll probably get if your opponent's not really paying attention. } 10. Qa4+ { [%csl Gc4,Ge8][%cal Ga4c4,Ga4e8] } 10... Bd7 11. Qxc4 { White's simply up a piece. } { [%csl Rb7,Rd4,Rc7,Gf4,Gg2,Gc4] }) (9... Ng6 10. Bc1 { It may seem awkward to do this, but the bishop is best placed here. } 10... Be7 11. b3 { [%csl Bb2,Gg2][%cal Bc1b2,Bb1d2,Be2e3,Bf2f4] }) 10. e3! dxe3 (10... Bc5 11. Bxc6+ bxc6 12. Qf3 { [%csl Rc7,Rc6,Gf3] } 12... Bd7 13. exd4 Bxd4 14. Re1+ Kf8 15. Nc3 $16 { White has a +2.6 advantage. }) 11. Qh5! { Sacrificing a pawn, for a ton of compensation! } 11... exf2+ 12. Rxf2 { White's pieces are all well placed, ready to attack the black king. White may be down a pawn, but has the open d,e, and f files for attack. } { [%csl Gf2,Gh5,Rf7,Re8,Rd8,Rc8,Rf8,Gg2,Gf4,Bf1,Be1,Gg1][%cal Bb1c3,Ba1f1,Ba1e1] } *


