2... Nc6?! { The Chigorin Defense. By playing 2...Nc6, Black doesn't back up the central d5 pawn but brings out a piece for a more uneven game. } 3. Nc3 dxc4 { The most popular move, white can now start kicking the knight around, gaining tempi. } (3... Nf6 4. Nf3 { We just continue developing. } 4... dxc4 { The Modern Gambit, this leads to a very sharp line. } 5. d5 { [%csl Rc6][%cal Gd5c6] } 5... Na5 6. Qa4+ { Forking, but we don't win the knight. } { [%csl Ge8,Ga5][%cal Ga4e8,Ga4a5] } 6... c6 { [%csl Ga5][%cal Gd8a5] } 7. b4! b5! { The only good move. } 8. Qxa5 Qxa5 9. bxa5 b4 10. dxc6 (10. Nd1?! cxd5 $10 { Black actually has full compensation for the knight. } { [%csl Gc4,Gb4,Gd5,Ra5,Ra2] }) 10... bxc3 $13 { A very sharp position. You can analyze further if you want, but I'll stop here. } { [%csl Rc3,Rc4,Rc6,Ra5,Ra2] }) (3... e6 { The more solid approach. } 4. Nf3 Nf6 5. Bg5 Be7 6. e3 O-O 7. h4 $14 { You get a good game. }) (3... e5 { The Tartakower Gambit. We'll get 9 consecutive captures in a row! } 4. cxd5 exd4 (4... Nxd4 5. e3 Nf5 6. e4 Nd4 (6... Nfe7 7. Bb5+ Bd7 8. Qb3 $16 { [%csl Gc3,Gb3,Gb5,Ye4,Yd5,Rd7,Re7,Re8,Rd8,Rf8,Rg8,Rh8,Re5][%cal Ye4d5] }) 7. f4 $16 { White gets a great game. Stockfish gives +1.2 } { [%csl Gf4,Ge4,Gd5,Rd4,Re5,Gc3] }) 5. dxc6 dxc3 6. Qxd8+ Kxd8 7. cxb7 Bxb7 8. bxc3 $16 { White's up a pawn. Black doesn't have any compensation for it. } { [%csl Rc7,Ra7,Ra2,Rc3,Ge2] }) 4. d5! { [%csl Rc6][%cal Gd5c6] } 4... Ne5 (4... Nb4?? { A blunder played over 215,000 times. } 5. Qa4+! { GG } { [%csl Ge8,Gb4][%cal Ga4e8,Ga4b4] }) (4... Nb8 5. e4 $16 { [%csl Rc4,Yd5,Ye4][%cal Ye4d5,Bg1f3,Bf2f4] }) 5. f4! { [%csl Re5][%cal Gf4e5] } 5... Ng6 6. e4! $16 { White completely dominates the center and has very easy development. White has a 60% winrate. } { [%csl Gf1,Yf4,Ye4,Yd5,Rc4,Rg6,Rg8,Rf8,Re8,Rd8,Rc8,Rh8,Ra8][%cal Ye4d5,Bg1f3] } *


