2... c5!? { The Austrian Defense. Black creates tension and tries to disturb White's center, stopping White from taking control by copying their moves. } 3. cxd5 Qxd5 (3... cxd4?! 4. Qxd4 $16 { White is simply up a pawn! :D } { [%csl Gd4,Gd5] }) (3... Nf6! { The Gusev Countergambit. It only gets played 6% of the time, but it's the best move! } 4. e4! { An interesting move. White can't stop black from winning back the pawn, but we can give black this pawn instead of the d pawn, which leads to black's knight being worst placed. } { [%csl Gd5][%cal Ge4d5] } 4... Nxe4 5. dxc5 Nxc5 (5... Qa5+ 6. Bd2 Nxd2 7. Qxd2 Qxd2+ (7... Qxc5 8. Nc3 $16 { White has easy development, black has a queen that can potentially become a target. } { [%csl Gc3,Gd2,Bb5][%cal Bf1b5,Bg1f3] }) 8. Nxd2 $16 { White is still up a pawn. }) 6. Nc3 { White is up a pawn and has easy development. } { [%csl Gd5,Bb5,Bc4,Be3][%cal Gc3d5,Bg1f3,Bf1c4,Bc4b5,Bc1e3] }) 4. Nf3 cxd4 5. Nc3! { A cool looking move that hits the queen. } { [%csl Bd5][%cal Rd4c3,Yd1d4,Bd1d5,Gc3d5] } 5... Qd8 (5... Qa5 6. Nxd4 $16 { White gets a good game. } { [%csl Gd4,Gc3,Gd1][%cal Be2e4] }) 6. Qxd4 Qxd4 7. Nxd4 $16 { White has the two knights developed, black has none. White has a 61% winrate. } { [%csl Gd4,Gc3,Ra8,Rb8,Rc8,Re8,Rf8,Rg8,Rh8] } *


