2... Nf6 { The Marshall Defense. It's actually not that bad, but most Black players mess up real quick. } 3. cxd5! { The absolute best move! } 3... Nxd5 (3... c6! { The Tan Gambit. It gets played 2% of the time... This is actually one of the better options for black. } 4. Bf4!? (4. dxc6 Nxc6 { Black has a lead in development. The Tan Gambit is extremely sharp and double-edged, even though often the queen's are traded off. I recommend just developing with Bf4, it avoids all the complications. }) 4... cxd5 5. Nc3 Nc6 6. e3 { We just develop. } 6... a6 { Back avoids any Bb5/Nb5. } { [%csl Rb5][%cal Ra6b5] } 7. Be2 Bf5 8. Nf3 e6 9. Qb3! $14 { White's pieces are all placed nicely. You get a good game. White has a 65% winrate. } { [%csl Bg1,Rb7][%cal Be1g1,Bh2h3,Bg2g4,Bf3e5,Ba1c1] }) (3... c5! { Another good option for black, it's pretty much the same thing as the Tan. } 4. Nf3 Nxd5? (4... cxd4 5. Nxd4 Nxd5 6. e4 Nf6 7. Bb5+ Bd7 8. Nc3 $14) (4... Qxd5?! { This allows white to kick the queen around. } 5. Nc3 Qd8 6. d5 e6 7. e4 $16 { White controls the center and has easy development. } { [%csl Gc3,Gf3,Bd5,Be4,Ba4,Bb3,Bc4,Bb5,Bg5][%cal Be4d5,Bd1a4,Bd1b3,Bf1c4,Bc4b5,Bc1g5] }) 5. e4 Nf6 6. d5 Nxe4?? (6... e6 7. Nc3 $16 { White has avoided complications, got black out of prep, and has a good position. White has a 59% winrate. } { [%csl Ge4,Gd5,Gc3,Gf3] }) 7. Qa4+ $18 { White wins a free piece. } { [%csl Ge8,Ge4][%cal Ga4e8,Ga4e4] }) 4. Nf3! { At this point white already has a whopping 60% winrate! } 4... e6 5. e4 { Gaining tempi and taking the center. } 5... Nf6 6. Nc3 { Keeping everything protected. } { [%csl Ge4,Gf3][%cal Gc3e4] } 6... Bb4 7. Bd3 O-O?? { Played over 75,000 times. There's even 1 game in the master's database like this: https://lichess.org/9yMV5bQg#29 This leads to a classic tactic... } (7... c5 8. a3 cxd4 { A symphony of exchanges. } 9. axb4 dxc3 10. bxc3 $16 { O-O leads to a Greek Gift again. :D
It's really hard for black to find a way to continue. } { [%csl Re8,Rd8,Rc8,Rb8,Ra8,Rh8,Be3,Bg5][%cal Re8g8,Bb4b5,Be4e5,Be1g1,Bc1a3,Bc1e3,Be3g5] }) (7... Nc6 8. O-O O-O?? (8... Nxd4?? { We win on the spot. } 9. Nxd4 Qxd4 10. Bb5+ { [%csl Gb5,Rd4,Re8][%cal Bd1d4] }) 9. e5 { A Greek Gift again... }) (7... Bxc3+ 8. bxc3 O-O 9. e5 { Greek Gift...again }) 8. e5! { First white clears the diagonal for the LSB. } { [%csl Gd3] } 8... Nd5 9. Bxh7+!! { the iconic Greek Gift! } 9... Kxh7 10. Ng5+! { Giving a check and freeing the queen. } { [%csl Bh5][%cal Bd1h5] } 10... Kg8 (10... Kg6 { Another attempt to survive. But it's over. } 11. h4 { [%csl Gg5][%cal Bh4h5,Gh4g5] } 11... Nxc3 (11... f5 12. h5+! { DON'T PLAY En' Passent!! } 12... Kh6 $7 { Forced. } 13. Nxe6+ { [%csl Gd8][%cal Ge6d8] } 13... Kh7 14. Nxd8 Rxd8 $18 { White has a great position and is up a queen. }) 12. Qg4 Ne4+ 13. Kf1 Nxg5 14. hxg5 { Checkmate is impossible to stop. }) 11. Qh5 $18 { Checkmate is impossible to stop without sacrificing the queen by taking g5. } { [%csl Gh7][%cal Gh5h7] } *


