2... Bf5?! { The Baltic Defense, a much more rarer move. It's not that great, because that bishop will definitely become a target, rather than a strength. Already, white's winrates are looking pretty good. } 3. cxd5! { We exchange these pawns. } 3... Qxd5?? { The most popular move. We have a nice sequence. } (3... Nf6 4. Nf3 Nxd5 5. Nbd2 { Threatening e4. } { [%csl Re4][%cal Re2e4] } 5... Bg6 (5... Nf6 6. g3 { White gets a great game. } { [%csl Bg2][%cal Bf1g2,Be1g1,Bd1b3] }) (5... Nb6 6. e4! { [%csl Ge4,Gd4] } 6... Bg6 7. h4 $16 { White is obviously better. } { [%csl Gh4,Ge4,Gd4,Gf3,Gd2,Rb6,Rg6] }) 6. h4 $16 { White's position is great. } { [%cal Bh4h5,Be2e4,Bd1b3] }) (3... Bxb1 { Trading a bishop for an undeveloped knight is not that great for black. } 4. Qa4+! { We throw in a quick check. } 4... c6 5. dxc6 Nxc6 { The Argentinian Gambit. } (5... Be4?? { Loses due to the discovered check. } 6. c7+ $18) 6. Rxb1 Qxd4 7. Qxd4 Nxd4 8. e3 $16 { We get an interesting game where either side hasn't developed. Stockfish gives 0.8 for white though. White has a 59% winrate. } { [%cal Bf1b5] }) 4. Nc3! { Not only kicking the queen, but also getting ready to strike with e4! } { [%csl Gd5][%cal Gc3d5] } 4... Qd8 { The most popular move. } 5. e4! { Grabbing the center. } 5... Bg6 6. h4! { We immediately go after that LSB. Threatening h5, trapping it. } { [%csl Bh5][%cal Bh4h5] } 6... h5 (6... h6 7. h5 Bh7 { The only safe square. Notice that until now, black hasn't left the 7th rank, except the h6 pawn. } { [%csl Rh7,Rh8,Rg8,Rf8,Re8,Rd8,Ra8,Rb8,Gh5,Gh1,Gd4,Ge4,Gc3] } 8. Qb3! { Hitting the b6 pawn. } { [%csl Gb7][%cal Gb3b7] } 8... b6 9. d5 { Controlling c6. } { [%csl Rc6] } 9... Nf6 (9... Nd7 10. Bb5 $18 { Black is completely stuck. Black's in a bit of a zugzwang, every move makes black's position worst. } { [%csl Rd8,Re8,Rf8,Rg8,Rh8,Rh7,Rd7] }) 10. Nf3 Nxe4 11. Bb5+ Nd7 { The only move that doesn't lose material instantly. } 12. Nxe4 Bxe4 13. Ne5! { Maximizing pressure on the d7 knight. The only way to protect it for a while is Bf5. } { [%csl Rd7] } 13... Bf5 14. Qf3! $18 { Black's position crumbles instantly. There's nothing black can do to survive. } { [%csl Rd7,Rf5,Rf7] }) 7. Qb3! { Hitting b7. } { [%csl Bb7][%cal Bb3b7] } 7... b6? 8. Nf3 { Protecting d4 and getting ready to jump to e5 in the future. } { [%csl Gd4][%cal Bf3e5] } 8... e6 (8... Nf6 9. Ne5 $18 { [%csl Rg6,Rf7][%cal Ge5g6] }) 9. Ne5 { Black can't allow us to take the bishop, e6 would be hanging and everything would crumble. So, actually there's nothing black can do to survive. } { [%csl Rg6,Re6,Rf7] } 9... Bh7 (9... Ne7 10. Bg5! { Pinning the knight, the same threat remains. } { [%csl Re7,Rg6] }) 10. Bb5+! $18 { A deadly check! Black's forced to bongcloud, and then it's over soon. White is completely winning. It's +6.4. } *


