[Event "CRUSH the Sicilian! 2...d6: 📗 4...Nf6"]
[Date "2025.09.11"]
[Result "*"]
[Variant "Standard"]
[ECO "?"]
[Opening "?"]
[StudyName "CRUSH the Sicilian! 2...d6"]
[ChapterName "📗 4...Nf6"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/Vpb6r3Wq/olievSER"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/Bosburp"]
[FEN "rnbqkbnr/pp3ppp/3pp3/2p5/2B1P3/5N2/PPPP1PPP/RNBQK2R w KQkq - 0 4"]
[SetUp "1"]
[UTCDate "2025.09.11"]
[UTCTime "13:27:12"]

4. Qe2! { We’ll be playing the same ultra-rare move again! Most of the time, we'll simply transpose into the positions we studied in the previous section. And even when Black avoids the transposition, we still get very nice setups, it's a nice positional slow game then as beautiful chess is meant to be. } 4... Nf6 { The most popular move. We just play the same idea. } 5. e5 { We’re getting our knight to e5. Here, dxe5 isn’t forced, but almost all the time players will take it. } 5... dxe5 (5... Nfd7 { Very rare, but we'll quickly cover it anyway. } 6. exd6 { We can take it. } 6... Bxd6 7. d4 $10 { Striking the center! From here White develops normally. Castling is not urgent, I would recommend focusing on development first. And later you can decide whenever castling queenside or kingside is best. Most of the time, Black will castle kingside, then you castle queenside and launch a kingside pawn storm. } { [%cal Bb1c3,Be1c1,Bh2h4,Ba2a3,Bb2b4] }) (5... d5!? { Counter attacking our bishop. Quite playable. } 6. exf6 dxc4 7. fxg7 Bxg7 8. Qxc4 { Again, it's best to delay castling until the position is more clear. Castling kingside right away is very bad, as Black now has a half open g-file which he'll use to attack our king. With the extra pawn, this is a bit easier to play as White. } { [%csl Rc5,Gg8,Gg7][%cal Bd2d3,Bb1c3,Yd1c1,Ye1c1,Ye1g1,Gh8g8] }) (5... Nd5 6. exd6 { Setting up a trap. If Bxd6, we win a full knight after Bxe5, the e pawn is pinned. } 6... Qxd6 (6... Bxd6?? 7. Bxd5 $18) 7. d4 { Normal development. It's a good game. } { [%cal Be1g1,Bb1c3,Bc1g5,Be1c1] }) 6. Nxe5 $36 { Now we've transposed into our beloved lines. :) } *


