1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. Bc4 Nc6 { Next we're going to look at this move very briefly, as we'll just be following basic ideas. We'll get similar setups pretty much all the time.
I didn't think it worth it to create a new section for some very rare sidelines, so those are included in this section too. } *


