{ [EDIT]: Thank you all for 800 ❤'s! :)

A study by https://lichess.org/@/Bosburp

🔶 [NEW STUDY] Most Beautiful Checkmates: lichess.org/study/Bu4LEk6w 🔶

Welcome, fellow chess aficionados! 🌟I haven't made a study for black before, so here you go! In this study we'll explore the Nimzowitsch Defense (1. e4 1. Nc6). Named after the legendary chess theorist Aron Nimzowitsch, this defense offers a refreshing alternative to more conventional responses to 1. e4.

Before you start, please consider supporting our team: https://lichess.org/team/study-creators--friends

🎊 Come hang out with us on our lively Discord server: https://discord.gg/dxf6tuFH3a

If you find this study useful, please heart it and share it with any friends!

Click the space-bar! 🚀 }
1. e4 { Play Nc6! } { [%csl Gc6][%cal Gb8c6] } 1... Nc6! { Good!🌟 This move is remarkably rare, accounting for only 1% of games played. As a result, your opponents are often caught off guard, leaving them unprepared to face this unexpected choice.
In the upcoming chapters, we'll delve into the two main responses from white:
White takes the center with 2. d4
White plays 2. Nf3
These all also have sub-sections :)
Feel free to utilize the engine and the Lichess database, and don't forget to explore the variations! 🕵️
Note: my lines will not always be the absolute top engine move, they are rather based on which one is more comfortable to play as a human and have a decent winrate.
Let's move on to the next chapter and explore these responses in detail! 🚀 } *


