5. Bc4 { The second most popular move. White wants to castle on the next move. } 5... Nf6 { Bringing another piece into the game. } 6. O-O Bg4 { Out usual move. } 7. h3 { Kicking away the bishop, trying to do something about the pin. } (7. d3? { A critical mistake. White didn't do anything about our f3 pin. This blocks the LSB from returning. } 7... Nd4! { Black's winrate is at a whopping 70%! } 8. Bd2 (8. Be3 Nxf3+ { Damaging White's pawn structure and kingside. } 9. gxf3 Bh5 $17 { Black is better because of the white's weak kingside. } { [%csl Rf3,Rf2,Ga5,Bc8,Rg1,Rg2][%cal Be8c8] }) 8... Qh5! $19 { Delaying taking f3, White's position completely collapses, there's nothing White can do to stop us from taking f3. The only move for white to survive a bit longer is sacrificing the queen by Nxd4. }) (7. d4? { Actually loses a pawn by force. } 7... O-O-O 8. Be3 (8. Nb5 e5! 9. c3 a6 $19) 8... e5! { Striking the center and attacking d4. } { [%cal Re5d4,Re5e4] } 9. d5 e4 $19 { Black wins a pawn after Qc1. Other moves lead to Black winning more material. }) 7... Bh5 { We keep the pressure. } 8. g4 { There's 2 options here for black, both are equally good: retreat the bishop to g6 and you get an okay game, or sac the knight for 2 pawns and get a huge kingside attack (Stockfish's prefered option). } (8. d3?! { Nd4 doesn't actually work here anymore because of 9. g4!, losing a piece for black. } 8... O-O-O { Controlling the d file. } 9. Bd2 Qf5! { Going out of the way from the DSB and luring white into giving us a fork (I know that sounds really weird, but it's true). } 10. g4 { Actually the best move, but } 10... Nxg4 11. hxg4?? (11. Nh4 Qd7! 12. hxg4 Bxg4 13. f3 Bh5 $17) 11... Qxg4+ 12. Kh2 Nd4! 13. Nxd4 Qh4+ 14. Kg2 Bxd1 $19) (8. Be2 { Unpinning the knight. } 8... O-O-O $15 { Both players are castled on opposite sides. Black has a more active and attacking position tho, White's in a more defensive mode. Next you can just try a kingside pawn storm at the right moment, also play e6/e5 on the next move. } { [%csl Gd8,Ga5,Gc6,Gf6,Gh5][%cal Bh7h6,Bg7g5,Be7e5,Be7e6] }) 8... Nxg4! { The bishop is stronger, we'll keep it on the board. } 9. hxg4 Bxg4 $13 { It's about equal, but most people will find it easier to play as Black (just check the winrates :)), especially in blitz, this is almost impossible to survive as white. We're only down 1 point in material, but we have an insane amount of compensation. The king is completely exposed, we can just keep bringing more pieces into the attack. Example O-O-O, and then get a rooklift with Rd6 and bring it over to the kingside. } { [%csl Rg1,Rh1,Rh2,Rg2,Bc8,Ga5][%cal Be8c8] } *


