3. Nc3!? { Much rarer, but you'll definitely face it regularly. The bad thing about this move is that it allows Black to gain some tempi with d4, so we'll play that. } 3... d4 { Hitting the knight. } { [%csl Rc3][%cal Rd4c3] } 4. Ne2 e5! { Taking the center, supporting d4 and opening up the DSB. } { [%csl Yd4][%cal Ye5d4] } 5. Ng3 { Now it's funny, because we're actually kinda playing a reverse Nimzowitsch :D } 5... h5! { The same move we feared in the Linksspringer Variation. The winrates sink from 57/4/39 to 43/4/53!! We're already threatening h4. } { [%csl Rh4][%cal Bh5h4] } 6. h4 { Stopping an h4 pawn advance. } (6. Bb5? { Ignores our initial threat. } 6... h4! { We start throwing series of very painful punches, starting with h4, kicking the knight. } 7. Bxc6+ { The most popular move, because what else was that bishop doing there? } 7... bxc6 8. Ne2 (8. Nf1 h3 $17 { Same thing. }) 8... h3! { Breaking open white' kingside1! } 9. gxh3 (9. g3 Qf6! 10. Neg1 Bg4! $19 { White's absolutely terrible. The horses each can't move, the rook is stuck, and that means there's no way of white's king ever castling kingside. Black's very comfortable. Even though material is equal, because of white's horrible piece placement Black has a 2.1 advantage. } { [%csl Rg1,Rh1,Rf3,Re1,Rd1,Rc1,Ge5,Gd4,Gf6,Gh8][%cal Ba8b8,Bf8b4] }) 9... Bxh3 10. Nxe5 { Doesn't actually win a pawn. } 10... Qe7 11. Nxc6?? (11. Nc4 Qxe4 12. Rg1 O-O-O $19 { Black gets all the fun! There's even a bunch of cool artificial rook lifts with the h8 rook. White's pieces are all cramped up, and can't do anything. } { [%csl Re1,Re2,Rd1,Rc1,Rc4,Rg1,Gd4,Ge4,Gd8,Gh3,Gh8][%cal Bh8h6,Bh6h5,Bh5h4] }) 11... Qxe4 { Wins material. } { [%csl Rh1,Rc6][%cal Re4h1,Re4c6] }) (6. Bc4 h4 7. Nf1 h3 $17 { Leads to similar postions }) 6... Bg4! { Pinning the knight and getting one step closer to castling. } 7. Bc4 { It doesn't actually matter what White does, we just have the same idea: } (7. Bb5 { Doesn't change black's plans. } 7... Ne7! { Supporting the other knight. } 8. d3 a6 { Doesn't matter where the bishop goes. } 9. Ba4 Ng6 $17 { Black has an amazing position. Next we'll castle queenside by Qd7 followed by O-O-O and then solidify everything with a nice f6. Same stuff as before. } { [%csl Bc8][%cal Bd8d7,Be8c8,Bf7f6] }) 7... Qd7! { Preparing to castle queenside. } 8. d3 Nge7 $17 { Whatever White does, just play Ng6. Then follow that up with f6, solidifying, and O-O-O, bring the king to safety. } { [%csl Bc8][%cal Be7g6,Bf7f6,Be8c8] } *


