3. dxe5 { Now recapturing the e pawn is possible, but we'll just get kick with f4 and white gets a nice space advantage. Instead I recommend playing something much more fun and tricky for white to deal with. } 3... d6!? { de Smet Gambit! We'll be looking at this move in the next few chapters marked with 📙. De Smet Gambit can also be reached in the Englund Gambit against 1. d4: 1. d4 e5 2. dxe5 Nc6 3. e4 d6. } *


