{ Playing the Nimzowitsch Defense has a problem because White can easily switch to other openings like the Scotch Game, Four Knights, or Vienna Game. When this happens, it's often smart for Black to follow suit. However, to keep our focus clear, we won't dive deep into these other openings here. Instead, in the next chapters, I'll share some links where you can learn how to handle them effectively as Black. }
 *


