5... Nf6 6. e5!? { An interesting move with a clever idea! } 6... dxe5?! { Black has now opened up the d file. } 7. Bxf7+! { Black cannot take the bishop, because otherwise the king will lose his wife. } 7... Ke7 (7... Kxf7 8. Qxd8 $18) 8. Qb3! { Keeping the bishop defended and refusing a queen trade. } 8... Nc6 9. bxc3! { White opens up the DSB. } { [%csl Ga3][%cal Gc1a3] } 9... Na5?? { This is the 2nd most popular move. } (9... Qd3 { the best move for black. } 10. Ng5! h6?? 11. Ba3+ Kd8 12. Bc4! { Preparing to put the knight on f7. } { [%csl Yf7][%cal Yg5f7,Bc4d3] } 12... Qg6 13. Nf7+ Ke8 14. Nxh8 Qxg2 15. Rf1 Qe4+ 16. Be2 $18) (9... Qd6?? { For some reason this is the most popular move, it blunders away the queen. } 10. Ba3 $19 { [%csl Ge7,Gd6][%cal Ga3e7] }) 10. Ba3+! Kd7 (10... c5 11. Bxc5+! { Just take it! } 11... Kd7 12. Qe6+ Kc7 $7 13. Qxe5+ Bd6 14. Bxd6+ Qxd6 15. Qxa5+ b6 16. Qe5 $18 { White has an extra horse and will also get the queens of the board, eliminating any counter-play for black. }) 11. Nxe5# { [%csl Gd7,Ye8,Ye6,Be7,Bd6,Rc7,Rd8,Rc8,Gc6][%cal Ge5d7,Yf7e8,Yf7e6,Ba3e7,Ge5c6] } *


