4... Nf6 5. Qc2 { This is probably the most simple and non-complicated line for white. } { [%csl Ge4][%cal Gc2e4] } 5... dxc3 6. Nxc3 Be7 { Black prepares to castle. } { [%csl Bg8][%cal Be8g8] } 7. Be3 { White prepares to castle queenside. } 7... O-O 8. O-O-O! { the king is now brought to safety. } 8... Nc6 9. h3 { This is the kind of setup we play pretty much every time, whatever black plays. The point of h3 is to support a future g4. } { [%csl Bg4][%cal Bg2g4,Bh3g4] } 9... Be6 10. a3 { We won't let black place a knight on b4, it's just unnecessarily annoying. } { [%csl Bb4][%cal Ba3b4] } 10... a6 11. g4 $10 { This position is equal, but tbh I would definitely prefer being white here. } *


