4... Nc6?! { This move allows white to capture d4 and control the center. } 5. cxd4! { [%csl Gf3,Gd5,Gc5,Ge5,Gf5,Rc6][%cal Gd4c5,Ge4d5,Gd4e5,Ge4f5] } 5... Bg4 (5... Nf6 6. Nc3 Be7 7. h3! { White avoids any annoying Bg4/Ng4. } 7... O-O 8. Bd3 h6 9. O-O Bd7 10. Be3 $16 { [%csl Gc3,Gf3,Ge4,Gd4,Gd3,Ge3,Gd1] }) 6. Nc3 { White just continues developing. } 6... Nf6 7. Bb5 { Pinning the knight } { [%csl Ge8,Rc6][%cal Gb5e8] } 7... a6 8. Ba4 b5 9. Bc2! { supporting e4 } { [%csl Ge4][%cal Gc2e4] } 9... Be7 10. O-O $16 { White has a big white center, everything is pretty much developed, and the king is safe. } { [%csl Gd4,Ge4,Gf3,Gc3] } *


