3... Nd7 { This is known as the Hanham variation. Black supports e5. } 4. Bc4! { This is the most aggressive approach, white immediately aims f7. } 4... Be7?? { Black develops and gets one step closer to castling, it is a blunder due to the following sequence. } (4... c6 5. O-O Be7 6. dxe5 dxe5 7. Ng5! { It might look at first like we are sacrificing a knight but we win it back immediately } { [%cal Bg5f7,Yc4f7] } 7... Bxg5 8. Qh5! { We win back the sacrificed piece. } { [%csl Gg5,Gf7][%cal Gh5g5,Gh5f7] } 8... Qe7 9. Qxg5 Qxg5 10. Bxg5 Ngf6 11. f3 O-O 12. Nd2 $16 { White's pieces are way better placed than black's. The engine gives white a +2.1 advantage. } { [%csl Gc4,Gg5,Gd2,Rc8,Rd7] }) (4... h6 { Black prevents any Bg5/Ng5 } { [%csl Rg5][%cal Rh6g5] } 5. dxe5 dxe5?? { A huge blunder! It gets played 82% of the time! } 6. Bxf7+!! Kxf7 7. Nxe5+!! { Exploiting the pin. } { [%csl Re5,Bd8][%cal Rd7e5,Bd1d8] } 7... Kf6 8. Nc3!! { The only move that wins. } 8... Kxe5 9. Qd5+ Kf6 10. Qf5+ Ke7 11. Nd5+ Kd6 12. Bf4+ Kc6 13. Qe6+ Bd6 14. Nb4+! Kb6 15. Bxd6 Ndf6 16. Bc5+ Kxc5 17. Nd3+ Qxd3 18. Qe5+ Kc6 19. cxd3) (4... Ngf6?? { A blunder, it allows us to win the important f pawn by force. } 5. dxe5! { Opening the d file. } 5... Nxe5 6. Nxe5 dxe5 7. Bxf7+! { It is important to note that white doesn't win the queen because after 7...Kxf7 8. Qxd8 Bb4+ and black wins the queen back. White is much better though because white has just won the important f pawn. } 7... Ke7 (7... Kxf7 8. Qxd8 Bb4+ 9. Qd2 Bxd2+ 10. Nxd2) 8. Qxd8+ Kxd8 9. f3 $18 { We're gonna break Ben Finegold's rule and play f3. It solidify s everything, 9. Nc3, and we would have to deal with an annoying Bb4 pin. }) 5. dxe5 dxe5 (5... Nxe5 6. Nxe5 dxe5 7. Qh5! { The only good move! White simply forks the e and f pawn. } { [%csl Gf7,Ge5][%cal Gh5f7,Gh5e5] } 7... g6 8. Qxe5 Nf6 9. Bh6! { Preventing black from castling. } 9... Qd6 10. Qxd6 cxd6 11. Nc3 Be6 12. Bb5+ Bd7 13. O-O-O $18 { White is up a clean pawn. Also black has a very weak d pawn that we will be able to put some pressure on. } { [%csl Rd6] }) 6. Qd5! { We threaten mate in 1 on f7 and black has no way to defend the f pawn without losing material. The move 4...Be7 has blocked the queen from coming out. } { [%csl Gf7][%cal Gc4f7] } 6... Nh6 7. Bxh6 { It's free! } 7... O-O 8. Be3 $18 { White has an extra knight on the board. } { [%csl Gc4,Re5,Gf3,Ge3,Gd5,Gb1,Bg1,Rc8,Rd8,Re7,Rd7][%cal Be1g1] } *


