[Event "10 Traps in the London System: Trap 1: nice checkmate!"]
[Date "2025.07.25"]
[Result "*"]
[Variant "Standard"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/Bosburp"]
[ECO "D00"]
[Opening "Queen's Pawn Game: Accelerated London System"]
[StudyName "10 Traps in the London Stystem"]
[ChapterName "10 Traps in the London System: Trap 1: nice checkmate!"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/dOtynhuN/aFPPLfdQ"]
[UTCDate "2025.07.25"]
[UTCTime "08:15:44"]

1. d4 { Hello! welcome to this study. This study will be about traps in the London system, they will be for white and black (go to chapter 9 for traps for black). Let's start! } 1... d5 2. Bf4 Nf6 3. e3 c5 4. c3 { we have a nice pawn pyramid. } { [%csl Gc3,Ge3,Gd4,Gf2,Gb2][%cal Gb2c3,Gc3d4,Ge3d4,Gf2e3,Ge3f4] } 4... e6 5. Nf3 Nc6 6. Nbd2 Bd6 { here it is not good to take black's bishop, because then black's queen is already developed } 7. Bg3 (7. Bxd6?! Qxd6) 7... O-O (7... Bxg3 8. hxg3) 8. Bd3 Qe7 9. Ne5 Nd7 10. Nxd7 Bxd7?! 11. Bxd6 Qxd6 12. dxc5 { [%cal Gc5d6] } 12... Qxc5? 13. Bxh7+ Kxh7 14. Qh5+ Kg8 15. Ne4 { the pawn cannot take the knight because the white takes blacks queen } { [%csl Gc5][%cal Ge4c5,Rd5e4,Gh5c5] } 15... Qe7 (15... g6 16. Nxc5 gxh5 17. Nxd7 Rfc8 18. Nf6+ Kf8 19. Nxh5 { you won 2 pawns! }) (15... Qc4 16. Ng5 Rfd8 17. Qxf7+ Kh8 18. Qh5+ Kg8 19. Rd1 e5 20. Qf7+ Kh8 21. e4) 16. Ng5 Rfe8 (16... Qxg5 17. Qxg5) 17. Qh7+ Kf8 18. Qh8# { Over 600 people fell for this trap! } *


[Event "10 Traps in the London System: Trap 2: Greek gift"]
[Date "2025.07.25"]
[Result "*"]
[Variant "Standard"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/Bosburp"]
[ECO "D00"]
[Opening "Queen's Pawn Game: Accelerated London System"]
[StudyName "10 Traps in the London Stystem"]
[ChapterName "10 Traps in the London System: Trap 2: Greek gift"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/dOtynhuN/LmZzzxvA"]
[UTCDate "2025.07.25"]
[UTCTime "08:15:57"]

1. d4 d5 2. Bf4 Nf6 3. e3 c5 4. c3 Nc6 { [%csl Gb2,Gc3,Gd4,Ge3,Gf2][%cal Gf2e3,Ge3d4,Gc3d4,Gb2c3] } 5. Nd2 e6 6. Ngf3 Bd6 { we don't want to take the black bishop, because otherwise black's queen is developed } { [%csl Rf4][%cal Rd6f4] } 7. Bg3 O-O 8. Bd3 { this bishop is aiming at the h7 pawn } { [%csl Gh7][%cal Gd3h7] } 8... b6 { black forms a pawn chain } { [%csl Gc5,Gb6,Ga7][%cal Gb6c5,Gd6c5,Ga7b6] } 9. e4 { now we start our trap setting! most people here would take the pawn } { [%cal Re4e5,Re5f6,Re5d6] } 9... dxe4?! 10. Nxe4 Nxe4 11. Bxe4 { we are attacking black's knight } { [%csl Gc6][%cal Ge4c6] } 11... Bb7 { here the dark squared bishop can be attacked thrice } { [%csl Gb7,Gh7,Gd6] } 12. dxc5 { [%csl Gd6][%cal Gc5d6,Gg3d6,Gd1d6] } 12... Bxc5 13. Qa4 { now the knight is attacked, so black needs to protect it } { [%csl Gc6][%cal Ga4c6,Ge4c6] } 13... Qc8?? { [%csl Gc6][%cal Gc8c6,Gb7c6] } (13... Rc8 14. Rd1 Qe8?? 15. Bxh7+ Kxh7 16. Qh4+ Kg8 17. Ng5 Bxf2+ 18. Kxf2 b5 19. Qh7#) 14. Bxh7+ Kxh7 15. Qh4+ Kg8 16. Ng5 Rd8 17. Qh7+ Kf8 18. Qh8+ Ke7 19. Qxg7 { [%csl Gf7][%cal Gg5f7,Gg7f7] } 19... Rf8 20. O-O-O $18 { we have a +5.0 advantage! white's position is great } { [%csl Gf7][%cal Gd1d8,Gg7f7,Gg5f7] } *


