1. e4 d5 2. f3?! { With this f3 move, White is weakening their king a lot, and we will take advantage of that. } 2... e5 3. exd5 Nf6 { After this, White is already pretty bad because of this f pawn move, and White has a lot of difficulties defending his d5 pawn, if they defend it: } { Black also has his knight developed and threatening to take the pawn. } { [%csl Rd5] } 4. c4?! { Here, we have no choice but to gambit the pawn: } 4... c6 (4... Bc5 5. Ne2 c6 6. dxc6 Nxc6 (6... Qb6 7. cxb7 (7. d4 exd4 8. cxb7 Bxb7))) 5. dxc6 Nxc6 { Black has a obvious advantage by his already developed knights, and development is very fast, but White is very bad because of these multiple pawn moves and this f pawn move harden the development of this knight, even thought he's a pawn up, Black has enough compensation for it, and Bc5 is coming to disallow short-side castling } { [%csl Bf2][%cal Bf8c5,Bc5f2,Re5f4,Re5d4,Yg1e2,Yg1f3] } 6. Nc3 Bc5 7. Nge2 *


