{ This is a gambit against the Scandi for white that can Win Blacks Queen. This is the line, and in the next chapter, We will show you how to not blunder the queen, and punish white at the same time! }
1. e4 d5 2. Nf3? { [%cal Rd5e4,Rf3g5] } 2... dxe4 3. Ng5 Nf6 4. d3 exd3 5. Bxd3 h6 { It looks like you are up a pawn and fine in the position, But white has a dynamite Strike that will win them the game! } 6. Nxf7 { Boom! a piece sacrifice! The best move is to accept it... } 6... Kxf7 { Whites king is weak, and he is about to lose his wife. } { [%cal Rd3g6,Bd1d8,Gf7g6] } 7. Bg6+ { KABOOM! and white sacrifices another piece, but will win the queen! } { [%cal Bd1d8,Gf7g6] } 7... Kxg6 8. Qxd8 { This is the trap, that has punished thousands of people.
Go to the next chapter to see how you can beat it! } 8... e5 { When seeing this move, castle or something to prevent that discovered check. } 9. Qxc8? Bb4+ { And all of a sudden, after that big exchange, you just lost your queen so DON'T TAKE THAT BISHOP please or just castle before that. } 10. c3 Bxc3+ 11. Nxc3 Rxc8 *


