4. e4 d5 5. Nf3? { This move nf3, starts up a dubious gambit for white that could potentially win YOUR queen! This is how to defend against it. } { [%csl Ge4][%cal Rf3g5,Gd5e4] } 5... dxe4 { Take the pawn! } 6. Ng5 Nf6 { Defend the pawn! } (6... Bf5 7. Nc3 Nf6 { Your pawn is defended enough now, and if they insist on recapturing it: } 8. Qe2? Nc6! 9. Ngxe4 { Very common at my level } 9... Nd4 { [%csl Bc2,Ge2][%cal Bd4c2,Bf5c2,Gd4e2] } 10. Nxf6+?? gxf6 11. Qh5 Bg6 { [%csl Gh5,Be1,Ba1][%cal Gg6h5,Yd4f5,Gf5g6,Bd4c2,Bc2e1,Bc2a1] }) 7. d3? { The idea of d3, is to develope the bishop fast if you take. The best move here is bg4, attacking the queen. } (7. Bc4) 7... Bg4 (7... exd3 8. Bxd3) 8. Qd2 $19 { Whites best move is queen to d2, And Black simply has a -2.1 Advantage! } (8. f3 exf3 9. gxf3 Bh5) *


