1. e4 { If you are a aggressive player then this is the opening for you!
Blackmar Diemer Gambit is one of the hottest gambits in chess. White sacrifice pawn and in return he gets 3,4 free move. And you can imagine the situation when you castled and your opponent’s king is still in the center. This is the situation where you must win because if your opponent castles then all your advantages will vanish. } 1... d5 2. d4 dxe4 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. f3 exf3 5. Qxf3 Qxd4 6. Be3 { [%csl Gd4][%cal Ge3d4] } 6... Qb4? { [%csl Gb2][%cal Gb4b2] } 7. O-O-O Bg4?? { This is the move white is waiting for. This big blunder has been
played on lichess over 1,700 times! } (7... c6 8. a3 Qa5 9. Qg3) 8. Nb5!! Bxf3? (8... Na6 9. Qxb7 Bxd1 10. Qxa8+ Kd7 11. Nxa7 Bg4 12. Bb5+ Ke6) (8... c6 9. Nc7#) 9. Nxc7# { [%csl Yd8,Yd7,Ge8,Rf8,Rf7,Re7][%cal Yd1d8,Gc7e8] } *


