1. e4 d5 2. exd5 Qxd5 3. Nc3 Qa5 4. d4 Nc6 5. d5 Nb4?? 6. a3 Bf5? { Black develops his bishop, because he thinks the pawn is pinned anyway. } (6... Na6 7. Bb5+ Bd7 8. Bxd7+ Kxd7 9. Be3) 7. Bb5+ c6 (7... Kd8 8. Ba4 Nf6 9. axb4 Qxb4 10. Nf3 { we're up a piece and a huge initiative advantage, we will hunt down the king } { [%csl Bh1,Gf3,Gc3,Ga4,Gd5,Be3,Bf4,Bg5,Rf8,Rd8][%cal Be1h1,Ga1a8,Gd1d5,Bc1e3,Be3f4,Bf4g5] }) 8. axb4 Qxa1 9. dxc6 { Black cannot stop a new queen on the board } { [%csl Gd8,Gd7,Re8,Bb7][%cal Gd1d8,Rb5e8,Bc6b7] } 9... Rd8 (9... bxc6 10. Bxc6+ Bd7 11. Qxd7#) 10. cxb7+ Bd7 11. Qxd7+! Rxd7 12. b8=R# { a nice finish! } { [%csl Rd7,Ge8,Bd8,Bc8][%cal Gb5e8,Bb8e8] } *


