1. e4 d5 2. exd5 Nf6 3. c4?! { No choice but to gambit the pawn: } 3... c6 4. dxc6 Nxc6 { This is the Algerian gambit as I like to call it, because you've a lead in development and this king will die very soon! } { [%csl Gc6,Gf6,Re1] } 5. Nf3 e5 { You're threatening to push e4 and trap the knight. } 6. Nc3? e4 7. Ng5?? (7. Ng1?? { This is disgusting, you just continue your development and White will struggle with castling! }) (7. Nh4?? g5) 7... Bf5 8. Qe2?? { trying to attack the pawn one more time to save the knight } 8... Nd4 { [%csl Ge2,Gc2][%cal Gd4e2,Gd4c2] } (8... Bb4) 9. Qd1 h6 { Stockfish is suggesting to sac the knight for the pawn lol } 10. Ngxe4 Bxe4 11. Nxe4 Nxe4 *


