[Event "40 TRAPS in the Scandinavian Defense: Trap 4: How to demolish the White camp"]
[Date "2023.06.27"]
[Result "*"]
[Variant "Standard"]
[ECO "B01"]
[Opening "Scandinavian Defense: Modern Variation"]
[StudyName "40 TRAPS in the Scandinavian Defense"]
[ChapterName "Trap 4: How to demolish the White camp"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/g29gizvW/5FgMTwbj"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/Bosburp"]
[UTCDate "2023.06.27"]
[UTCTime "06:12:58"]

1. e4 d5 2. exd5 Nf6 3. Nf3 { Here, I suggest you to not take the pawn yet, to let them a chance to transpose to the Algerian gambit } 3... Bf5 { To play this trap, we need that bishop staring at that weakness of the White position } 4. d4 (4. c4 c6 5. dxc6 Nxc6 { This is a transposition to the Algerian gambit }) (4. Nc3 Nxd5 5. Nxd5 Qxd5 { Transposition to the main variation }) 4... Nxd5 5. c4?! { This is the inaccuracy that costs White victory } 5... Nb4 { [%csl Gc2][%cal Gb4c2,Gf5c2] } 6. Qa4+ { This is where it gets tricky } (6. Na3 e6) 6... N8c6 7. d5?? { [%csl Ge8,Gc6,Gc2][%cal Gd5c6,Ga4e8,Gb4c2] } 7... Nc2+ { [%csl Gd1,Gd2][%cal Ge1d2,Ge1d1,Gd8d1] } 8. Kd1 { The d pawn is pinned, so White cannot take the knight yet! } { [%csl Gd5,Gd1][%cal Gd8d1,Gd5c6] } (8. Ke2?? { This seems to not let the d pawn pinned and threaten to capture the knight on the next move! Here, there are 2 moves that are very good: Qd7 and Nxa1 } 8... Nxa1 { White SHOULD NOT TAKE THE KNIGHT or else... } (8... Qd7 { The rook is dead, it will not escape! } 9. dxc6? Qd3# { [%csl Ge1,Gd3,Gd1,Ge2,Gd2,Ge3][%cal Gc2e1,Gd3d1,Gd3e2,Gd3e3,Gd2d1,Gf5d3] }) 9. dxc6? Qd3+ 10. Ke1 Nc2+ { no choice for him but to capture the knight with the queen! } 11. Qxc2 Qxc2 { I can't give you better than a queen and a rook for 2 knights! (maybe mate? It's already covered) } { [%csl Gb1,Gc1][%cal Gc2c1,Gc2b1] }) 8... Nxa1 { [%csl Gb1][%cal Gf5b1] } 9. Nd4?? (9. Nc3 Bc2+ { [%csl Ga4,Gd1][%cal Gc2d1,Gd1a4] }) 9... Bxb1 10. Nxc6 (10. dxc6 Qxd4+) 10... Qd7 { Black is completely winning here, there is no hope for White EXCEPT if you play: bxc6 } (10... bxc6?? 11. Qxc6+ Qd7 12. Qxa8+ { I said this trap is very tricky, and a little sippet of mistake and everything is over! } 12... Qd8 13. Qc6+ Qd7 14. Qa8+ Qd8 15. Qc6+ Qd7 16. Qa8+ Qd8 17. Qc6+ { Threefold Repetition - Draw lol }) *


