1. e4 d5 2. exd5 Nf6 3. d4 Nxd5 4. c4 Nb4 { this is the Kiel variation, it is a bit dubious, but very fun! } 5. Qa4+ { [%csl Gb4,Ge8][%cal Ga4b4,Ga4e8] } 5... N8c6 6. d5? { [%csl Gc6,Ge8][%cal Gd5c6,Ga4e8] } 6... b5! { the only winning move! } 7. cxb5 (7. Qxb5 Nc2+ 8. Kd1 Bd7! { there is no need to take the rook right away } { [%csl Gb5,Gc2,Gd4][%cal Gd7b5,Gc6d4,Gd4c2,Gd4b5] } 9. Kxc2 (9. dxc6 Bg4+ { [%csl Gd1][%cal Gd8d1,Gg4d1] } 10. Kxc2 Qd1+ 11. Kc3 Qxc1+ 12. Kb4 Qxb2+ 13. Ka5 Qxa1) 9... Nd4+ { [%csl Gb5,Gc2][%cal Gd4b5,Gd4c2] }) 7... Bf5 (7... Nd4 { is another possible move. See chapter 41 }) 8. Na3 { [%csl Bc2][%cal Ga3c2,Rb4c2,Rf5c2] } (8. dxc6 Bc2 { [%csl Ga4,Gd1][%cal Gc2a4,Gc2d1,Gd8d1] } 9. Nc3 { [%csl Gd1][%cal Gc3d1] } 9... Bxa4 10. Nxa4 Nc2+ { [%csl Ge1,Ga1][%cal Rc2e1,Rc2a1] }) (8. bxc6 Nc2+ 9. Ke2 Qxd5 10. Nc3 (10. Qb3 Qe5+ { [%csl Gd1,Re1][%cal Ge2d1,Re5e1] } 11. Qe3 Nxe3 12. fxe3 { Hunt the king with the bishop pair and the dragon } { [%csl Rf8,Ra8,Rf5,Re5] }) 10... Qd3#) 8... Qxd5 9. bxc6?? Qe4+ { You will see something similar in chapter 41 } { [%csl Ra4,Bb4][%cal Re4a4] } 10. Kd2 (10. Ne2 Nd3+ { [%csl Ra4,Re1][%cal Re4a4,Rd3e1] }) (10. Be2 Nd3+ { [%csl Re1,Ga4][%cal Rd3e1,Re4a4] }) (10. Be3 Nd3+ 11. Bxd3 Qxa4 12. Bxf5 Qa5+ { never 3 pieces vs queen } { [%csl Re1,Rf5][%cal Ra5e1,Ra5f5] }) (10. Kd1 Rd8+ 11. Bd2 Rxd2+ 12. Kxd2 Qd4+ { [%csl Re1,Rc1,Rd3,Ba4][%cal Rb4d3,Rd3e1,Rd3c1,Bd4a4] } 13. Ke2 (13. Ke1 Nd3+ { [%csl Ge1,Ga4][%cal Gd3e1,Gd4a4] } 14. Bxd3 Qxa4 15. Bxf5 Qa5+ { [%csl Ge1,Gf5][%cal Ga5e1,Ga5f5] }) 13... Qxb2+ { [%csl Ra3,Ra1,Re2][%cal Rb2a3,Rb2a1,Rb2e2] }) 10... Rd8+ 11. Kc3 e5 { Black to play, mate in 7 } *


