1. e4 d5 2. exd5 Nf6 3. d4 Nxd5 4. c4 Nb4 5. Qa4+ N8c6 6. d5 b5 7. cxb5 Nd4 { This is an alternative to Bf5, and leads to absolute wildness too } 8. Na3 e5 9. dxe6 Bxe6 10. Be3 (10. Bd2 Qh4 { Same thing, win the queen by sacing both horseys } { [%csl Ra4,Bb4,Bd4][%cal Rh4a4] } 11. Bxb4 (11. b6+ c6 12. b7 Rb8 13. Qxa7 Bd6 { [%csl Gb8][%cal Gd6b8] } 14. Rc1 O-O 15. Nf3 Nxf3+ 16. gxf3 Bd5 17. Be2 Nd3+!! 18. Bxd3 Bxf3 { We will hunt down this king stuck in the middle } { [%csl Gh1][%cal Gf3h1] } 19. Rg1 Rfe8+ 20. Be3 Bb4+ 21. Rc3 Rxb7 { This is savage engine prep, you look like you're up a piece, and then you sac a rook to deflect the queen from the bishop } { [%csl Rb6,Rc5,Rd4,Ra7,Be1,Bd1,Ye3][%cal Gb7a7,Gb7b6,Gb4c5,Gh4d4,Ge3d4,Gd4c5,Gc5b6,Gb6a7,Ge8e1,Bb4e1,Bf3d1,Ya7e3] } 22. Qxb7 Rxe3+ 23. Kd2 Qxf2+ 24. Kc1 Qxg1+ 25. Bf1 Qxf1+ 26. Kd2 Rd3+ { [%csl Rd2][%cal Gc3d3,Rb4d2] } 27. Kc2 Qd1#) 11... Bxb4+ 12. Qxb4 Nf3+ { [%csl Gb4][%cal Gh4b4] }) (10. b6+?? Bd7 11. bxc7 (11. b7 Bxa4 12. bxa8=Q Qxa8) (11. Qd1 Bf5 12. Qa4+ c6 { [%csl Gc2][%cal Gd4c2,Gb4c2,Gf5c2] } 13. b7 Rb8 { [%csl Gc2] }) 11... Qxc7 { [%csl Gc2,Ga1,Ge1][%cal Gc7c2,Gd4c2,Gb4c2,Gc2e1,Gc2a1] } 12. Bb5 Nxb5 13. Nxb5 Qe5+ { [%csl Ge1,Gb5][%cal Ge5e1,Ge5b5] }) 10... Qh4 { We need the king to be on a dark square so we win the queen } { [%csl Ra4,Bb4,Bd4][%cal Rh4a4] } 11. O-O-O Ne2+! { One more sacrifice to win the queen! } 12. Kb1 Bf5+ { [%csl Rb1,Rc1,Rc2,Ga1][%cal Gb1a1] } 13. Ka1 Nc2+ 14. Qxc2 Bxc2 15. Nxc2 Nxg1 16. Rxg1 { Queen vs 2 pieces is winning } *


