1. e4 d5 2. exd5 Nf6 3. d4 c6 4. dxc6 e5!? { this is the Kadas gambit, I don't recommend this opening for long time controls because it is quite dubious } 5. dxe5 Qxd1+ 6. Kxd1 Ng4 { [%csl Gf2,Ge5,Gc6][%cal Gg4f2,Gg4e5,Gb8c6] } 7. Nh3? { [%csl Gf2][%cal Gh3f2] } 7... Nxc6 8. f4 { [%csl Ge5][%cal Gf4e5] } 8... Bf5 { [%csl Bc8][%cal Be8c8] } 9. Bd3 O-O-O { [%csl Rd3,Rd1][%cal Gd8d3,Gd3d1] } 10. Ke2? Nd4+ 11. Kd2 Nxc2! 12. Kxc2 Rxd3! { white's position will crumble very soon! } { The king is trapped and cannot escape a discovered attack. } { [%csl Gc2,Rb3,Rd1,Rd2,Rc3,Bh3][%cal Gf5c2,Rd3b3,Rd3d1,Bd3h3] } *


