1. e4 d5 2. exd5 Qxd5 3. d4 Nf6 4. c4 Qe4+ 5. Be3 e5 6. Nc3 Bb4 { [%csl Ge1,Gc3][%cal Gb4e1] } 7. Qa4+?! { [%csl Gb4,Ge8][%cal Ga4b4,Ga4e8] } 7... Nc6 { in this position black already has a 73% winrate! } { [%csl Gb4][%cal Gc6b4] } 8. d5?? { This move looks strong but is a huge blunder! } { [%csl Gc6,Ge8][%cal Gd5c6,Ga4e8] } 8... Bxc3+ 9. bxc3 Nxd5! { The pawn is pinned!! } { [%csl Gd5,Ga4][%cal Gc4d5,Ge4a4] } 10. Be2 (10. cxd5 Qxa4 11. dxc6 Qxc6) 10... Nxe3 11. fxe3 Qxe3 { [%csl Rc4,Rc3,Re2,Re1,Rg1,Bg8,Bf5,Be6,Bc8][%cal Be8g8,Bc8f5,Ba8d8,Bd8d1,Be8c8] } 12. Qc2 { We are up 2 pawns and have a great position! Stockfish gives black a 7.9 advantage } *


