1. e4 d5 2. exd5 Nf6 3. Nc3 Nxd5 4. Nxd5 Qxd5 5. Nf3 Nc6 6. d4 Nb4!? { An interesting move, I won several games with this simple move at 1900 level. Against any of the highlighted moves, the trick is going to work } { [%cal Gc3c4,Gd2f4,Ra1b1,Ra2a3,Ra2a4,Rb2b3,Rc2c3,Rc2c4,Rc1d2,Rc1f4,Rg2g3,Rh2h3] } 7. c3? Qe4+ { However they block the check, Nc2+ wins the rook } 8. Kd2 { You can repeat moves and it's fine, if you need a quick draw } (8. Be3 Nc2+ { [%csl Re1,Ra1][%cal Rc2e1,Rc2a1] }) (8. Be2 Nc2+ { [%csl Re1,Ra1][%cal Rc2e1,Rc2a1] }) (8. Qe2 Nc2+ { [%csl Re1,Ra1][%cal Rc2e1,Rc2a1] }) 8... Qf4+ 9. Ke2 (9. Ke1 Qe4+ 10. Kd2 Qf4+ 11. Ke1 Qe4+ 12. Kd2 Qf4+ 13. Ke1) 9... Qe4+ 10. Be3 Nc2 11. Rc1 Nxe3 12. fxe3 g6 $15 { Simple plan: just develop and get your queen to safety } { [%csl Bf5,Bh6][%cal Bc8f5,Bf8h6,Be8c8] } *


