1. e4 { first we will start with traps for white, if you want to see traps for black go to chapter 30. } 1... c6 2. Ne2 d5 { This is called the Bohemian Attack, it is a pretty rare opening } 3. e5 Bf5 4. Nd4 Bg6 5. e6 c5?? 6. Bb5+ { white will take whatever black blocks the check with. } { [%csl Ge8,Yc6,Rd7][%cal Gb5e8,Yd4c6,Re6d7] } 6... Nc6 7. Nxc6 { It is important to take with the knight instead of the bishop } (7. Bxc6+?? bxc6 8. Nxc6 Qc7 { the knight is trapped } { [%csl Gc6,Ga5,Ge5,Yb4,Yd4][%cal Gc7c6,Gc7a5,Gc7e5,Yc5b4,Yc5d4] }) 7... bxc6 8. Bxc6+ { [%csl Ga8,Ge8,Yd7][%cal Gc6a8,Gc6e8,Ye6d7] } 8... Qd7 9. exd7+ Kd8 10. Bxa8 { White is up 15 points in material! sample game I played: https://lichess.org/NKVOXsB4 } *


