1. e4 c6 2. Ne2 d5 3. e5 Bf5 4. Nd4 { [%csl Gf5][%cal Gd4f5] } 4... Bg6 5. e6 c5?? { [%csl Rd4][%cal Rc5d4] } 6. Bb5+ { [%csl Ge8,Rc6,Yd7][%cal Gb5e8,Rd4c6,Ye6d7] } 6... Nc6 7. Nxc6 Qb6 { black thinks white cannot save both pieces } { [%csl Gc6,Gb5][%cal Gb6c6,Gb6b5] } 8. Nc3! { we simply protect the bishop } { [%csl Gb5][%cal Gc3b5] } (8. Nd4+?? Kd8 { [%csl Rd4,Rb5][%cal Rc5d4,Rb6b5] } 9. Nf3 Qxb5 { don't fall for this! }) 8... bxc6 9. Nxd5! { [%csl Gc7,Ga8,Ge8,Gb5][%cal Gd5c7,Gc7a8,Gc7e8,Gc7b5] } 9... Qb7 (9... Qxb5 10. Nc7+ { a triple fork! } 10... Kd8 11. Nxb5) (9... cxb5 10. Nxb6) 10. Ba6 { [%csl Ga6,Ge8][%cal Gd5c7,Gc7a6,Gc7e8] } 10... Qb8 11. Ne3 fxe6 { Black has a horrible pawn structure, and it is very hard to develop for black. Stockfish give white a +5.7 advantage. } { [%csl Re6,Re7,Rc6,Rc5,Ra8,Rb8,Re8,Rf8,Rg8,Bb3,Bg1,Bf3,Bd3,Bd4][%cal Bb2b3,Bc1b2,Be1g1,Bd1f3,Bd2d3,Bd2d4] } *


