1. e4 { [%clk 0:01:00] } 1... c6 { [%clk 0:01:00] } 2. Nf3 { [%clk 0:00:58] } 2... d5 { [%clk 0:01:00] } 3. Nc3 { this is the Two Knight's Attack. } { [%clk 0:00:58] } 3... dxe4 { [%clk 0:00:57] } 4. Nxe4 { [%clk 0:00:58] } 4... Bf5?! { [%csl Ge4][%cal Gf5e4] [%clk 0:00:57] } 5. Ng3 { [%csl Gf5][%cal Gg3f5] [%clk 0:00:58] } 5... Bg6 { [%clk 0:00:57] } 6. h4 { threatening to trap the bishop with h5 } { [%csl Gh5][%cal Gh4h5] [%clk 0:00:57] } 6... h6 { [%csl Gh7][%cal Gg6h7] [%clk 0:00:56] } 7. Ne5 { [%csl Gg6][%cal Ge5g6] [%clk 0:00:56] } 7... Bh7? { this has been played over 160,000 times. This leads to a very nice combination from white. } { [%clk 0:00:53] } 8. Qh5 { threatening checkmate on f7 } { [%csl Gf7][%cal Gh5f7,Ge5f7] [%clk 0:00:55] } 8... g6 { [%cal Gg6h5] [%clk 0:00:51] } 9. Bc4 { Oh no my queen! We are threatening checkmate again on f7 and developing the bishop while gaining tempo. } { [%csl Gf7,Gd7][%cal Gc4f7,Ge5f7,Ge5d7] [%clk 0:00:54] } 9... e6 { this move blocks the bishop } { [%csl Ge6,Rf7][%cal Rc4f7] [%clk 0:00:49] } (9... gxh5 10. Bxf7#) 10. Qe2! { This is a very tricky move. Almost every natural move loses. Bg7, Nf3, Nd7, Bd6, Ne7, Be7, and Bc5 all lose. In this position white already has a 87% winrate! } { [%clk 0:00:53] } 10... Bg7 { [%clk 0:00:47] } (10... Be7 11. Nxf7 Kxf7 12. Qxe6+ Ke8 13. Ne4 Qd7 14. Qe5 Qf5 15. Nd6+ Kd7 16. Nxf5) (10... Nf6 11. Nxf7 Kxf7 12. Qxe6+ Kg7 13. Qf7#) (10... Nd7 11. Nxf7 Kxf7 12. Qxe6+ Kg7 13. Qf7#) (10... Bc5 11. Nxf7 Kxf7 12. Qxe6+ Kf8 13. Qf7#) (10... Ne7 11. Nxf7 Kxf7 12. Qxe6+ Ke8 13. Ne4 { [%csl Gf6,Gd6][%cal Ge4f6,Ge4d6] } 13... Bg7 14. Qf7+ Kd7 15. Qxg7) 11. Nxf7!! { [%csl Gd8,Gh8][%cal Gf7d8,Gf7h8] [%clk 0:00:51] } 11... Kxf7 { [%clk 0:00:46] } 12. Qxe6+ { [%csl Gf7][%cal Ge6f7] [%clk 0:00:51] } 12... Kf8 { the only legal move } { [%clk 0:00:46] } 13. Qf7# { 1-0 White wins by checkmate. } { [%csl Gf8,Yf7,Ge8,Ge7,Rg8,Bg7][%cal Gf7f8,Yc4f7,Gf7e8,Gf7e7] [%clk 0:00:50] } 1-0


