1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. f3 { This is the Fantasy Variation or also known as the Maroczy Variation } 3... dxe4 { [%csl Ge4][%cal Gf3e4] } 4. fxe4 e5 5. Nf3 (5. dxe5? { don't fall for this! } 5... Qh4+ 6. g3 (6. Kd2 Qf4+ 7. Ke1 Qxe4+ 8. Qe2 Qg6) 6... Qxe4+ 7. Be2 Qxh1) 5... exd4 6. Bc4 { we are aiming at the f7 pawn } { [%csl Gf7][%cal Gc4f7] } 6... Nf6 7. O-O Bc5 (7... Be7 8. Ng5 O-O 9. Nxf7! Rxf7 10. Bxf7+ Kxf7 11. e5 { [%csl Rf6,Gf7][%cal Re5f6,Gf1f7] } 11... Kg8 12. exf6 Bxf6 13. Nd2 Be6 14. Ne4 { Stockfish gives white a +3.6 advantage }) (7... Bb4 8. e5 Nd5 9. Ng5 { [%csl Gf7][%cal Gf1f7,Gg5f7] } 9... O-O 10. Qh5 { [%csl Gf7,Gh7][%cal Gh5f7,Gh5h7,Yg5f7,Yg5h7] } 10... h6 11. Ne4 b5 12. Nf6+! gxf6 13. Bxh6 { Checkmate can almost not be stopped, since the king is way to exposed. our plan now is to try to get the rook over. } { [%csl Gf3,Gg8,Gg3][%cal Gf1f3,Gf3g3,Gg3g8] } 13... bxc4 14. Rf3 fxe5 15. Rg3+ Bg4 16. Rxg4+ Qg5 17. Rxg5+ Kh8 18. Bxf8#) 8. Ng5 O-O 9. Nxf7! Rxf7? 10. Bxf7+ Kxf7 11. Qh5+! { [%csl Yh5,Gf7,Gc5][%cal Rf1f7,Yf6h5,Gh5f7,Gh5c5] } (11. e5 { also a playable move. } 11... d3+ 12. Kh1 Nd7 13. exf6) 11... Kg8 12. Qxc5 $18 { we are up an exchange! } *


