1. e4 { I got this trap from @Sack_o_Potatoes you can check his study about the Fantasy Variation here: https://lichess.org/study/kVwoBhiw } 1... c6 2. d4 d5 3. f3 { [%csl Ge4][%cal Gf3e4] } 3... dxe4 4. fxe4 Nf6? 5. e5 { [%csl Rf6][%cal Re5f6] } 5... Nd5 6. Bd3 Nd7? { this is the third most played move in the database } 7. e6 { [%csl Gd7,Gf7][%cal Ge6d7,Ge6f7] } 7... fxe6 (7... N7f6 8. exf7+ Kxf7 9. Nf3 { black's king has lost it's castling rights. we can maybe later on also attack along the f file. } { [%csl Bg1,Bf8,Bf7,Bc4,Bg5][%cal Be1g1,Bf1f8,Bc2c4,Bc1g5] } 9... Bg4?? 10. Ne5+ Ke8 11. Nxg4 Nxg4 12. Qxg4) 8. Qh5+ g6 9. Qxg6+! (9. Bxg6+ hxg6 10. Qxg6# { also possible, but isn't sacrificing the queen cooler? }) 9... hxg6 10. Bxg6# { Checkmate! } { [%csl Ge8,Gf7,Rd7,Yd8,Rf8,Be7][%cal Gg6e8] } *


