1. e4 c6 2. Nf3 d5 3. exd5 cxd5 4. Ne5! { This is called the Apocalypse Attack. It is a very underrated but powerful opening. It is very rare, so you can surprise your opponents with it!
I learned about this opening from @WassimBerbar, who makes great studies. Go check them out here: https://lichess.org/study/by/WassimBerbar } 4... Nc6 { [%csl Ge5][%cal Gc6e5] } 5. d4 { [%csl Ge5][%cal Gd4e5] } 5... Bf5 6. Qf3 { [%csl Gf5][%cal Gf3f5] } 6... Nxd4?? { now black is protecting the bishop, attacking the queen and wanting to fork the king and rook. } { [%csl Gf3,Gf5,Gc2][%cal Gd4f3,Gd4f5,Gd4c2] } 7. Qxf5!! { This is the only winning move! we are threatening mate and we just took the bishop. } { [%csl Gf7][%cal Gf5f7,Ye5f7] } 7... Nxf5 8. Bb5+! { black cannot block the check without giving away the queen! } { [%csl Ge8,Re5,Rd7][%cal Gb5e8,Re5d7] } 8... Qd7 9. Bxd7+ Kd8 10. Bxf5 $18 { White is up 5 points in material, black's king is unsafe, and black hasn't developed any pieces yet. } { [%csl Bg1,Bc3,Bf4,Bd1,Rf8,Rd8][%cal Be1g1,Bb1c3,Bc1f4,Ba1d1] } (10. Nxf7+? Kxd7 11. Nxh8 { this is still winning, but now we also have the burden of trying to save that knight. }) *


