1. e4 c6 2. c4 d5 3. cxd5 cxd5 4. Bb5+?! Bd7 5. Qa4? dxe4 6. Bxd7+ Nxd7 7. Qxe4? Nc5 { [%csl Gd3,Ge4][%cal Gc5e4,Gc5d3] } 8. Qc4 Nd3+ (8... Rc8 9. Qb5+ Rc6) 9. Ke2 { [%cal Ge2d3,Gc4d3,Ge2f2] } (9. Kd1?? Nxf2+ 10. Ke1 Nxh1 { we are up a rook and a pawn }) 9... Rc8 { [%cal Gc8c1,Gd3c1] } 10. Qxd3?? (10. Qb5+ Rc6 11. Nc3 Nf6 12. Nf3 a6 13. Qxd3 Re6+ 14. Qe3 Rxe3+ 15. dxe3 Qc7 16. Rd1 e5 17. h3 e4 18. Ng5 h6 19. Ngxe4 Nxe4 20. Nxe4 Qc4+ 21. Kf3 Qc6 22. Bd2 f5 23. Ke2 Qc4+ 24. Ke1 Qxe4) 10... Qxd3+ 11. Kxd3 Rxc1 $19 { white has an misplaced king and white cannot move any knights because otherwise we take the rook. Even though the material is equal, stockfish gives black a -6.1 advantage! } { [%csl Ya1,Yh1,Rf3,Rh3,Rc3,Ra3,Be5,Bc5,Bg8,Bf6,Rd3][%cal Yc1h1,Yc1a1,Rg1f3,Rg1h3,Rb1c3,Rb1a3,Be7e5,Bf8c5,Bg8f6,Be8g8] } *


