1. e4 c6 2. Nf3 d5 3. Nc3 Bg4 4. h3 { we are pinning the knight. } { [%csl Gd1,Gf3][%cal Gg4d1] } 4... Bxf3 5. Qxf3 e6 { we're making a pyramid } { [%csl Gc6,Gd5,Ge6,Gf7,Gb7][%cal Gb7c6,Gc6d5,Ge6d5,Gf7e6] } 6. d3 Bb4 { the knight is pinned and we are threatening d4 } { [%csl Ge1,Gc3,Gd4][%cal Gb4e1,Gd5d4] } 7. Qg3 { [%csl Gg7][%cal Gg3g7] } 7... Nf6! 8. Qxg7? Rg8 { [%csl Gg7][%cal Gg8g7] } 9. Qh6 { this is the only safe square for the queen } 9... d4 { [%csl Gc3,Re1][%cal Gd4c3,Rb4e1] } 10. a3 { [%csl Rb4][%cal Ra3b4] } 10... Bf8 { [%csl Gh6,Gc3][%cal Gf8h6,Gd4c3] } 11. Qh4 dxc3 $19 12. bxc3 { Black has an open file, a knight for two pawns, and white has doubled pawns. Stockfish gives black a -3.6 advantage! } *


