1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 dxe4 4. Nxe4 Nd7 5. Bd3 Ngf6 { [%csl Ge4][%cal Gf6e4] } 6. Ng5 e6 7. N1f3 Bd6 8. Qe2 h6 { [%csl Gg5][%cal Gh6g5] } 9. Ne4 Nxe4 10. Qxe4 Nf6 { [%csl Ge4][%cal Gf6e4] } 11. Qh4 Rg8 { This move sets up a little trap } 12. O-O?? { this natural move is actually a blunder } 12... g5! { [%csl Gh4][%cal Gg5h4] } 13. Qxh6 (13. Qh3 g4 14. Qxh6 gxf3) 13... Bf8 { [%csl Gh6][%cal Gf8h6] } 14. Qh3 g4 { [%csl Gh3,Gf3][%cal Gg4h3,Gg4f3] } 15. Qg3 (15. Qh4 gxf3) 15... gxf3 16. Qxf3 Qxd4 { we are up a knight and have a nice file for the rook. Stockfish give black a -5.5 advantage. } { [%csl Gg2,Gg1][%cal Gg8g2] } *


