{ New much improved and expanded version: https://lichess.org/study/55CPbtmd I highly recommend checking that one instead to improve your learning experience.

Hello everyone! Welcome to my new study about how to crush the Sicilian Defense. I will show you a very rare, but extremely powerful, opening called the Porthsmouth Gambit. Even Magnus Carlsen has played this opening quite a few times. It is full of traps and because it is so rare, you can surprise your opponents with it.

Feel free to use the engine and the Lichess database, and don't forget to look at the variations :)

Let's start!

play 1.e4 }
1. e4 c5 { This is the Sicilian Defense.
play 2. Nf3 } { [%csl Gf3][%cal Gg1f3] } 2. Nf3 Nc6 { Ok, now we can hit black with a rarer move, play b4! } 3. b4! { This is the start of the Porthsmouth Gambit. We can only play this if black plays 2....Nc6, which is the most popular move. Black has three options here: capture the pawn with c5, capture with the knight, or just ignore it and play some other move.
Go to the next chapter :) } *


