1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. b4 cxb4 4. d4 d5 5. exd5 Qxd5 6. c4 { [%csl Gd5][%cal Gc4d5] } 6... Qe4+? { Black doesn't feel safe taking the pawn. } { [%csl Ge1][%cal Ge4e1] } 7. Be3 Bg4? { [%csl Gd1,Gf3][%cal Gg4d1] } (7... e5 8. Bd3 Qg4 9. h3! Qxg2 10. Rh2 { the queen } { [%csl Rg6,Yg5,Gg4,Gg3,Bf2,Bg2,Gg1][%cal Rd3g6,Ye3g5,Gh3g4,Gf2g3,Bh2f2,Gf3g1] } (10. Rg1?? { Don't make this mistake! } 10... Qxh3)) (7... Bf5 { [%csl Ge4][%cal Gd2e4] } 8. Nbd2 Qc2 9. Qxc2 Bxc2 10. d5 Na5 11. c5 O-O-O 12. Nd4 { [%csl Gc2][%cal Gd4c2] } 12... Ba4 (12... Bg6 13. N2b3 Nxb3 14. axb3 $16 { [%csl Ga8,Ga7][%cal Ga1a8] }) 13. N4b3 Nxb3 14. axb3 { [%csl Ga4][%cal Gb3a4] } 14... Be8 15. Rxa7 Kb8 16. Ra5 Rxd5 17. Bc4 $16) (7... e6 8. Bd3 Qg4 9. d5 exd5 10. cxd5 Nb8 11. O-O { even though white isn't up in material, white is almost completely developed. All black's pieces are still on the back rank, except the queen. Stockfish gives white a +6 advantage. } { [%csl Gg1,Ge3,Gd3,Gf3,Gd5,Ra8,Rb8,Rc8,Re8,Rf8,Rg8,Rh8] }) 8. Bd3 { [%csl Ge4][%cal Gd3e4] } 8... Bxf3 9. gxf3 { [%csl Ge4][%cal Gf3e4] } 9... Qh4 10. d5 Ne5 11. Qa4+ Nd7 { almost all black's pieces are undeveloped and blacks queen is on vacation on the other side of the board. } { [%csl Re8,Rf8,Rg8,Rh8,Ra8,Rh4] } 12. c5 { [%csl Gc6][%cal Gc5c6] } 12... Nf6 (12... e6 13. Bb5 { [%csl Gd7][%cal Gb5d7] } 13... Nf6 { white try to trade the knight on f6. } { [%csl Gc3,Ge4,Gf6][%cal Gb1c3,Gc3e4,Ge4f6] } 14. Nc3! { white develops their knight, the pawn can't take because it is pinned. } { [%csl Rc3,Gh4][%cal Rb4c3,Ga4h4] } 14... Be7 (14... bxc3 15. Qxh4) 15. d6 Bd8 16. Ne4 { white has get rid of the knight on f6, which is protecting d7. } { [%csl Gf6,Gd7][%cal Ge4f6,Gb5d7] } 16... O-O 17. Bxd7 Nxe4 18. fxe4 Qxe4 19. Rg1 { white still has to be careful here. white's king might seem too exposed, but black doesn't really have anything to attack it. } { [%csl Gg8,Gg7][%cal Gg1g8] }) 13. c6 { [%csl Gd7][%cal Gc6d7] } 13... bxc6 14. dxc6 { [%csl Gd7][%cal Gc6d7] } 14... Ne5 15. c7+ Nfd7 16. Qxa7! { White's past c pawn is impossible to stop without sacrificing insanely large amounts of material. } { [%csl Ga8][%cal Ga7a8] } 16... Rxa7 (16... Nxd3+ 17. Kd2 Rc8 18. Qb7 { [%csl Gc8][%cal Gb7c8] }) 17. c8=R# { [%csl Ge8][%cal Gc8e8] } *


