1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. b4! Nxb4 4. c3 { [%csl Gb4][%cal Gc3b4] } 4... Nc6 5. d4 cxd4 6. cxd4 e6! { here white cannot play d5, because of Qf6 and there is no c pawn to block the queen. } 7. Bd3! { here I recommend Bd3 because there are still a lot of traps after this move. White also has a 56% winrate here. } (7. d5? Qf6! 8. dxc6 Qxa1 9. cxd7+ Bxd7 $17 { white is down an exchange, and this time white doesn't have any compensation for it. }) 7... Bb4+ { this is the most popular move. } { [%csl Ge1][%cal Gb4e1] } (7... d5 8. e5 Bb4+ (8... Nb4! { [%csl Gd3][%cal Gb4d3] } 9. O-O Nxd3 10. Qxd3 $15 { the game goes on. }) 9. Nbd2 Nge7 { [%csl Gg8][%cal Ge8g8] } 10. O-O O-O? 11. Bxh7+ Kxh7 12. Ng5+ Kg6 13. Ndf3 { the only move that survives is Rh8 } { [%csl Gg5,Gd3][%cal Gf3g5,Gd1d3] } 13... f6 (13... Rh8 14. a3 { [%csl Gb4][%cal Ga3b4] } 14... Ba5 15. Qd3+ Nf5 16. g4 { [%csl Gf5][%cal Gg4f5] } 16... f6 17. gxf5+ exf5 18. Kh1! { this move frees up the g1 square for the rook. } 18... fxg5 19. Nxg5 Rh5 20. Rg1 { [%csl Gg6][%cal Gg1g6] } 20... Qh8 { [%csl Gh2][%cal Gh5h2] } 21. Bf4 { [%csl Gh2][%cal Gf4h2] } 21... Bd8 { [%csl Gg5][%cal Gd8g5] } 22. Ne6+ Kf7 23. Nxg7 { [%csl Gh5][%cal Gg7h5] } 23... Rh4 24. e6+ Bxe6 25. Nxe6 Kxe6 26. Rae1+ Ne5 27. Rxe5+ Kd7 28. Qb5+ Kc7 29. Re7+ Kc8 30. Qxb7#) 14. Qd3+ f5 15. Nh4+ Kh5 16. g4+ Kxg4 17. Qf3+ Kxh4 18. Qh3#) (7... Nb4 8. O-O Nxd3 9. Qxd3 Nf6 10. Nc3 $10 Bb4? 11. e5 Bxc3?? 12. exf6! Bxa1 13. fxg7 Rg8 { [%cal Gh7g8] } 14. Qxh7 { [%csl Gg8][%cal Gh7g8] } 14... Ke7 15. Bd2 { [%csl Ga1][%cal Gf1a1] } 15... Bb2 { [%cal Gb1b2] } 16. Rb1 { [%csl Gb2] } 16... Ba3 { [%cal Gb3a3] } 17. Rb3 { [%csl Ga3] } 17... Bd6 18. Ne5 Bxe5 19. dxe5 $18 d6 20. Bg5+ f6 21. Bxf6+ Kd7 22. Bxd8 Kxd8 23. Qxg8+ Kd7 24. Qf8) 8. Bd2 { [%csl Gb4][%cal Gd2b4] } 8... Bxd2+ (8... Qa5 9. O-O) 9. Nbxd2 Nge7 { black is preparing to castle. } 10. e5 { this sneaky move opens up the bishop. } { [%csl Gh7][%cal Gd3h7] } 10... O-O?? (10... Qb6?? 11. Nc4 { [%csl Gb6,Gd6][%cal Gc4b6,Gc4d6] } 11... Qb4+ 12. Kf1! { [%csl Gd6][%cal Gc4d6] } 12... O-O?? (12... Nd5 13. a3 Qe7 14. Nd6+ Kd8) 13. Rb1 { [%csl Gb6,Gb5,Gb4,Gb3,Gb2,Ba3,Ba5,Ya4,Rc5,Rd6][%cal Gb1b6,Bc4a3,Bc4a5,Yd1a4,Rd4c5,Re5d6] } 13... Qc3 { this is the only "safe" square for the queen } 14. Rb3 { the queen is trapped! } 14... Qxb3 15. Qxb3 $18) 11. Bxh7+! { a Greek Gift! } { [%csl Gg5,Bh5][%cal Gf3g5,Bd1h5] } 11... Kxh7?? (11... Kh8) 12. Ng5+ { [%csl Gh7][%cal Gg5h7] } 12... Kh8 (12... Kg8 13. Qh5 { [%csl Gh7][%cal Gh5h7] } 13... Re8 14. Qxf7+ Kh8 15. Nde4! { [%csl Gf6][%cal Ge4f6] } 15... Nxe5 (15... a6 16. Qh5+ Kg8 17. Nf6+ gxf6 18. Qf7+ Kh8 19. Qh7#) (15... Qa5+ 16. Kf1 Qa6+ 17. Kg1 Qe2 { [%csl Gh5][%cal Ge2h5] } 18. Nf6 gxf6 (18... Qf1+ 19. Rxf1 Ng6 20. Qxe8+ Nf8 21. Qxf8#) 19. Qh7#) 16. dxe5 Qa5+ 17. Kf1 Qa6+ 18. Kg1 Ng8 19. Qg6 { [%csl Gh7][%cal Gg6h7] } 19... Nf6 20. Nxf6 Qf1+ 21. Rxf1 a6 22. Qh7# { [%csl Gh8,Bh7,Bg8,Rg7][%cal Gh7h8,Bf6h7,Bf6g8] }) (12... Kg6 13. Qg4 { the queen is lining up with the black king. } { [%csl Gg6,Re6][%cal Gg4g6,Rg5e6] } 13... f5 14. exf6! { En Passent! This is the only winning move for white. } 14... Rxf6 15. Nxe6+ { [%csl Gd8,Bg6][%cal Ge6d8,Bg4g6] } 15... Kf7 16. Nxd8+ Nxd8 $18 { Stockfish gives white a +8.5 advantage. }) (12... Kh6 13. Qg4! { the only winning move! } { [%csl Gh4,Gh3][%cal Gg4h4,Gg4h3] } 13... Nf5 { [%csl Gh4][%cal Gf5h4] } 14. Ndf3 { we are protecting the knight. } { [%csl Gg5][%cal Gf3g5] } 14... g6 (14... Rh8 15. Nxf7+ Kh7 16. Nxd8 Rxd8) (14... Qxg5 15. Nxg5) 15. Qh3+ Kg7 16. Qh7#) 13. Qh5+ Kg8 14. Qh7# { 1-0 White wins by checkmate. } *


