{ Hello everyone! Welcome to my new study about how to crush with the Vienna Game! It is a very aggressive and tricky opening. It can be played at any level, beginner or master.

Feel free to use the engine and the Lichess database, and don't forget to look at the variations :)

Let's start!

play 1.e4 }
1. e4 e5 { Now play 2. Nc3 } { [%csl Gc3][%cal Gb1c3] } 2. Nc3 { This is the Vienna Game! The point of the move Nc3 is to keep the option open to play f4, and try to get a open f file.
There are many moves here for black, but hopefully I covered most of them. :)
Note: my lines will not always be the absolute top engine move, they are rather based on which one is more comfortable to play as a human and have a decent winrate.
Engines used in the making of this study:
-Stockfish 14+ (default Lichess engine)
-Leela Chess Zero
Go to the next chapter :) } *


