1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. Bc4 { Here you can play f4, but personally I really like Bc4, and usually play f4 later on in the game. } 3... Nf6 4. d3 Bc5 5. f4! d6 6. Nf3 Bg4 7. Na4! { all other moves will make black's position very comfortable. } { [%csl Gc5][%cal Ga4c5] } 7... Nd4?! { the most common move! } 8. c3 { [%csl Gd4][%cal Gc3d4] } 8... Nxf3+ 9. gxf3 { [%csl Gg4][%cal Gf3g4] } 9... Bh3?! (9... Bh5 10. Nxc5 dxc5 11. fxe5 Nd7 12. Bf4 Qe7 13. Rg1 $14 { We have a pretty decent position, we are probably going to lose the e5 pawn though. } { [%csl Gd3,Gc4,Ge5,Ge4,Gf4,Gf3,Gc3,Bb3,Ba4,Bg5,Bc1][%cal Gd3e4,Gf3e4,Gb2c3,Bd1b3,Ba2a4,Bg1g5,Be1c1] }) 10. Nxc5 dxc5 11. Rg1 { we have to bring this rook into the game! It is now dominating the g file } { [%csl Gg7][%cal Gg1g7] } 11... Nh5 { [%csl Gg7][%cal Gh5g7] } (11... g6? 12. fxe5 { [%csl Gf6][%cal Ge5f6] } 12... Nh5 13. Bg5 Qd7 14. Qb3 $16 { White is so much better here } { [%csl Gf7,Gb7][%cal Gb3f7,Gb3b7] }) 12. Rg5 { [%csl Ge5,Gh5][%cal Gg5e5,Gg5h5] } 12... Nxf4?? (12... g6 13. Rxe5+ Kf8 14. Qd2! $16 { preparing to play f5 and activate the queen }) 13. Rxe5+ Ne6 14. Rh5 Bg2 { only safe square } 15. Kf2 { we can't win the bishop if we aren't gonna attack it! } { [%csl Gg2][%cal Gf2g2] } 15... g6 { no problemo, we just slide the rook over to d5 or h6. } { [%csl Gh5][%cal Gg6h5] } 16. Rh6 Bh1 17. Kg1 { the bishop is trapped in the enemy king's corner! } 17... Bxf3 18. Qxf3 $18 *


