1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Nf6 4. d3 Bc5 5. f4 d6 6. Nf3 Ng4? { Many players will see this knight fork, don't panic we have an amazing move to counter it! } { [%csl Gd1,Gf2,Gh1][%cal Gg4f2,Gf2d1,Gf2h1] } 7. Ng5! { [%csl Gf7][%cal Gg5f7] } 7... O-O 8. f5! { We cut off the LSB, now the knight is unprotected. } 8... Nf2?? { the most popular move! It fails miserably because of the following sequence: } (8... Bf2+ 9. Kf1 Ne3+ 10. Bxe3 Bxe3 11. h4 Bxg5 12. hxg5 Qxg5 13. Rh5 Qf4+ 14. Kg1 Nd4 15. Nd5 { [%csl Gf4][%cal Gd5f4] } 15... Qg3 16. Ne7+ Kh8 17. Rxh7+! { a arabian mate! } 17... Kxh7 18. Qh5# { [%csl Gh8,Gh7,Gh6,Yg8,Yg6,Rg7][%cal Gh5h8,Ye7g8,Ye7g6] }) 9. Qh5! { threatening mate on h7, and we have 3 attackers attacking f7. } { [%csl Bh7,Bf7][%cal Gh5h7,Gh5f7,Yg5h7,Yc4f7] } 9... h6 10. Nxf7 Qf6 (10... Rxf7 11. Qxf7+ Kh8 12. f6 { [%csl Gg7][%cal Gf6g7,Gf7g7] } 12... Qxf6 (12... gxf6 13. Bxh6 Nxd3+ 14. Kf1 { [%csl Gg7][%cal Gf7g7] } 14... Qg8 (14... Qf8 15. Qxf8+ Kh7 16. Qg7#) 15. Qxg8#) 13. Qg8#) (10... Qe7 11. Nxh6+ { [%csl Bg8][%cal Gc4g8,Yh6g8] } 11... Kh8 12. Ng4# { [%csl Gh8,Yg8,Gh7,Gh6,Rg7][%cal Gh5h8,Yc4g8] }) 11. Nxh6+ { double check! } { [%csl Bg8][%cal Gc4g8,Yh6g8] } 11... Kh8 (11... Kh7 12. Nf7+ { [%csl Gh7][%cal Gh5h7] } 12... Kg8 (12... Qh6 13. Bxh6 gxh6 14. Qg6#) 13. Qh8#) 12. Nf7+ { again double check! } { [%csl Gh8][%cal Gf7h8,Yh5h8] } 12... Kg8 13. Qh8# { A beautiful checkmate! } { [%csl Gg8,Rf8,Rg7,Gh7,Bf7][%cal Gh8g8,Gh8h7,Yc4f7] } *


