1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Bc5 { This is also known as the copycat variation } 4. Qg4 Qf6?! (4... g6 5. Qf3 Nf6 6. Nge2 d6 7. h3 { preventing any Bg4 or Ng4. } { [%csl Gg4][%cal Gh3g4] } 7... Be6 8. d3 Bxc4?? 9. Bg5 { [%csl Gf6][%cal Gg5f6] } 9... Nd4 10. Nxd4 exd4 11. Bxf6 { [%csl Gd8,Gh8][%cal Gf6d8,Gf6h8] } 11... Qd7 12. Bxh8 dxc3 13. dxc4 cxb2 14. Bxb2) 5. Nd5! { sacrificing the f pawn! } { [%csl Gf6,Gc7][%cal Gd5f6,Gd5c7] } 5... Qxf2+ 6. Kd1 $7 { Now black has to deal with two threats: Qxg7 and Nxc7. there is only 1 move that survives, it is Kf8 but it is only played 9% of the time! } { [%csl Gg7,Gc7][%cal Gg4g7,Gd5c7] } 6... d6?? { surprisingly, the most popular move. It simply hangs the g pawn. } (6... g6?? 7. Nh3 { [%csl Gf2][%cal Gh3f2] } 7... Qd4 8. d3 { [%csl Gc5,Gd4][%cal Gc1e3,Ge3c5] } 8... d6 9. Qh4 Bxh3 10. Qxh3 Qf2 (10... Bb6 11. Rf1 { [%csl Gf7][%cal Gf1f7] } 11... Nge7 12. Nf6+ Kd8 (12... Kf8 13. Bh6# { [%csl Gf8,Gg7][%cal Gh6f8] }) 13. Qd7#) 11. Nxc7+ Kd8 12. Nxa8 $19 { we are up 5 points in material }) (6... Nf6?? 7. Qxg7 { [%csl Gh8,Gf6][%cal Gg7h8,Gg7f6,Gd5f6] } 7... Rg8 8. Nxf6+ Ke7 9. Nxg8+ Kd6 10. Qh6+ f6 11. Qf8+ Ne7 12. Nxe7 Qxg2 13. Qxf6#) (6... Bb6 7. Qxg7 d6 8. Nxb6 axb6 9. Nf3 { [%cal Gh1f1] } 9... Be6 10. Rf1 { [%csl Gf2][%cal Gf1f2] } 10... Qc5 11. Bxe6 fxe6 12. Qxh8) (6... Kf8! 7. Nh3 { Now we have to try to put our rook to good use by placing it on the f file } { [%csl Gf2][%cal Gh3f2] } 7... Qd4?? { Black puts their own queen in a cage!! } { [%csl Gc4][%cal Gd4c4] } 8. d3 { we just have to bring a bishop to e3 and we will win the queen } { [%csl Gc4,Ge4,Gd5,Gd3,Gc2][%cal Gd3c4,Gd3e4,Ge4d5,Gc4d5,Gc2d3] } 8... Nf6 (8... d6 9. Qh4 Bxh3 10. Qxh3 Qf2 11. Bd2 Nd4 12. c3 Qe2+ 13. Kc1 Ne6 14. Re1 Qf2 15. d4 exd4 16. Rf1) 9. Nxf6 gxf6 10. Qh5 { [%csl Gf7][%cal Gh5f7] } 10... Nd8 11. Rf1 { [%csl Gf6,Gf7,Gf8][%cal Gf1f6,Gc1h6,Gh6f8] } 11... Be7 12. Ng5 fxg5 13. Rxf7+ Nxf7 14. Qxf7#) 7. Qxg7 { black is going to lose the rook } { [%csl Gh8][%cal Gg7h8] } 7... Be6 8. Nh3 { attacking the queen and also making room for the rook to get to f1 } { [%csl Gf2][%cal Gh3f2] } 8... Bxh3 9. Rf1 Qxg2 10. Qxf7+ Kd8 11. Qf8+ { just keep on checking } 11... Kd7 12. Rf7+ Nce7 13. Rxe7+ Nxe7 14. Qxe7+ Kc6 15. Qxc7# { Checkmate! } { [%csl Gc6,Gd7,Yc7,Yb6,Bb5,Bd5,Rc5,Rd6,Rb7][%cal Gc7c6,Yd5c7,Gc7d7,Yd5b6,Bc4b5,Bc4d5] } *


