1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Bc5 4. Qg4 { [%csl Gg7][%cal Gg4g7] } 4... g6 5. Qf3 { threatening mate in 1 } { [%csl Gf7][%cal Gf3f7,Gc4f7] } 5... Nf6 (5... Qf6? 6. Nd5 { [%csl Gc7,Gf6][%cal Gd5c7,Gd5f6] } 6... Qxf3 7. Nxf3 Bb6 (7... Bd6 8. b3 Nge7 9. Nf6+ Kf8 10. d4 { threatening mate in 1, } { [%csl Gh6][%cal Gc1h6] } 10... Kg7 11. Ng4 exd4 (11... Nxd4 12. Bh6+ Kg8 13. Nf6#)) 8. a4 { [%csl Ga5][%cal Ga4a5] } 8... a5 9. Nxb6 cxb6 10. d4 Nxd4 11. Nxd4 exd4 12. Bf4 $18 { black's structure is just really bad, after white castles queenside, black will have to many things to defend. Stockfish gives white a +6.5 advantage. } { [%csl Gc4,Gf4,Rd7,Rb7,Rb6,Rc8,Rf7,Re8,Ra8,Rd4,Bc1][%cal Be1c1] }) 6. Nge2 d6 7. h3! { avoiding any annoying Bg4/Ng4 } { [%csl Gg4][%cal Gh3g4] } 7... Be6 { DON'T take that bishop, black will enjoy the half open f file. } 8. d3! Bxc4?? { The most popular move! it loses immediately after Bg5! } 9. Bg5! { we are threatening to take f6 with a deadly fork! } { [%csl Bf6,Gc4][%cal Gg5f6,Yf3f6,Gd3c4] } 9... Nd4 { no problem, just take it } { [%csl Gf3][%cal Gd4f3] } 10. Nxd4 exd4 11. Bxf6 { [%csl Gd8,Gh8][%cal Gf6d8,Gf6h8] } 11... Qd7 12. Bxh8 dxc3 13. dxc4 cxb2 14. Bxb2 $18 { we are up a full rook! } *


