1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 d6 3. f4 exf4 4. Qf3! { This is Mr. Fish's favorite move, it is also rare so your opponents will probably be caught off guard } { [%csl Gf4][%cal Gf3f4] } 4... g5?! { black insists on keeping the f pawn, we now have to strike with h4! } 5. h4! f6?? { this is the most popular move (seriously). It just opens up the e8-h5 diagonal. } { [%csl Gh5,Gg6,Gf7,Ge8][%cal Gf3h5] } (5... Nc6 6. d3 (6. Bb5 Bg7 7. Nge2 h6 8. d4 Bd7 9. Bxc6 Bxc6 10. hxg5 hxg5 11. Rxh8 Bxh8 12. g3 fxg3 13. Qxg3 $10 { it's 100% equal }) 6... Nd4 7. Qf2 Bg7 8. hxg5 Qxg5 9. Nd5 { [%csl Gc7][%cal Gd5c7] } 9... Qg3 10. Qxg3 fxg3 11. Nxc7+ Kd8 12. Nxa8 Nxc2+ 13. Kd1 Nxa1) (5... Be7 6. d4 { [%csl Gd4,Ge4,Gc5,Gd5,Ge5,Gf5][%cal Gd4c5,Ge4d5,Gd4e5,Ge4f5] } 6... Nc6 7. Bb5 Bd7 8. Bxc6 Bxc6 9. Nge2 $16) 6. Qh5+ { [%csl Ge8][%cal Gh5e8] } 6... Kd7 7. Nf3 { [%csl Gg5][%cal Gf3g5,Gh4g5] } 7... Qe8 { a nice try from black, but it fails miserably. (black wants to exchange queens, because you can't attack without material.) } 8. Qxe8+ Kxe8 9. hxg5 fxg5 10. Nd5! { threatening to fork. } { [%csl Gc7][%cal Gd5c7] } 10... Kd8 (10... Na6 11. Bxa6 bxa6) 11. Nxg5 { again threatening to fork. } { [%csl Gf7][%cal Gg5f7] } 11... Nh6 12. Rxh6! Bxh6 13. Nf7+ $18 { a triple fork ending black } { [%csl Gh6,Gh8,Gd8][%cal Gf7h6,Gf7h8,Gf7d8] } *


