1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 d6 3. f4 exf4 { [%csl Gf3][%cal Gd1f3] } 4. Nf3!? { Stockfish doesn't really like this move, but it's actually playable } { [%csl Gd4][%cal Gd2d4] } 4... Nf6?! 5. d4 { we take the center and open up the bishop } { [%csl Gd4,Ge4,Yf4][%cal Yc1f4] } 5... Be7 6. Bxf4 O-O 7. Bd3 { [%csl Gh4,Gg4,Gd2,Gc1][%cal Gh2h4,Gh4h5,Gg3g4,Gd1d2,Ge1b1] } 7... Bg4 8. h3 Bh5 9. g4! { just expanding the kingside, white hasn't castled kingside, so this is very good. } 9... Bg6 { [%csl Gh4][%cal Gh3h4] } 10. Qe2 { [%csl Gc1,Ge4][%cal Ge1c1,Gc3d3] } 10... Nc6 11. O-O-O Nb4 12. Kb1 { [%csl Ga2,Gc2,Gb2][%cal Gb1a2,Gb1c2,Gb1b2] } 12... Nxd3 13. cxd3 { always capture toward the center! } { [%csl Ge4,Gd4][%cal Gd3e4] } 13... c6 14. Rdg1 { patiently improving our position bit by bit. } 14... a5 { [%csl Gb1][%cal Gf4c1] } 15. h4 { [%csl Gg5,Gh5][%cal Gg4g5,Gh4h5] } 15... h5 16. gxh5 Bxh5 { [%csl Ge2,Gf3][%cal Gh5e2] } 17. Rg5 { [%csl Gh5][%cal Gg5h5] } 17... Bg6 { [%cal Gh5g6] } 18. h5 { [%csl Gg6] } 18... Bh7 19. Rhg1 g6 (19... Ne8 { [%csl Gg7][%cal Ge8g7] } 20. Rxg7+ Nxg7 21. Qg2 { [%csl Gg7][%cal Gg2g7] } 21... Bf6 { [%csl Gg7][%cal Gf6g7] } 22. Bh6 Bg6 { the only move that survives a bit longer. } 23. hxg6 fxg6 24. Qxg6 Rf7 25. e5 dxe5 26. dxe5 Bxe5 27. Nxe5 Qf6 28. Qxf7+ Qxf7 29. Nxf7 Kxf7 30. Rxg7+ Ke6 31. Rxb7 $18) 20. Qg2 { there is nothing black can do to stop white from taking g6 } 20... a4 21. hxg6 fxg6 22. Rxg6+ Bxg6 23. Qxg6+ Kh8 24. Qg7# { [%csl Gh8,Gg8,Gh7][%cal Gg7h8,Gg7g8,Gg7h7] } *


