1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 d6 3. f4 exf4 4. Nf3 g5 5. d4 g4 6. Bxf4! { the only good move! after any other move will just be bad. For instance Nd2?? and white get brutally punished with Qh4+!. This move actually transposes to the Quade Gambit in the King's Gambit. Also white has a pretty sweet winrate of 54%. } 6... gxf3 7. Qxf3 Nc6 8. O-O-O Bg7?! (8... Nf6? 9. h3 { [%csl Yg4][%cal Bg2g4,Gh3g4] } 9... Bd7 10. e5 dxe5 11. dxe5 Ng8? 12. e6 fxe6 13. Qh5+ Ke7 14. Bg5+ { [%csl Gd8,Ge7][%cal Gg5d8] } 14... Nf6 15. Bxf6+ Kxf6 16. Ne4+ { [%csl Gf6][%cal Ge4f6] } 16... Ke7 17. Bc4 { freeing a space for the rook. There is no way to stop this, black can resign. } { [%csl Gf7][%cal Gh1f1,Gf1f7,Gh5f7] } 17... Qe8 18. Qg5+ Kf7 19. Rdf1#) 9. Qg3 { [%csl Gg7][%cal Gg3g7] } 9... Bxd4? 10. Bb5 { [%csl Ge8,Gc6][%cal Gb5e8] } 10... Bxc3 11. Qxc3 { [%csl Gh8][%cal Gc3h8] } 11... f6 (11... Nf6?? 12. Bg5 { There is no way for black to save the knight. } { [%csl Gd8,Gf6,Gh8][%cal Gg5d8,Gc3h8] }) 12. e5! fxe5 (12... dxe5?? 13. Rxd8+ Kxd8 14. Bxc6 bxc6 15. Qxc6) 13. Bxe5 { [%csl Gh8][%cal Gc3h8] } 13... Qg5+ { [%csl Gc1,Ge5][%cal Gg5c1,Gg5e5] } 14. Kb1 dxe5 { now black may have saved the h8 rook, but now white wins the a8 rook! } (14... Qxe5?? 15. Rhe1 { bye bye queen! } { [%csl Ge8,Ge5][%cal Ge1e8] }) 15. Bxc6+ bxc6 { [%cal Gc6e8] } 16. Qxc6+ { [%csl Ge8,Ga8][%cal Gc6a8,Gc6e8] } 16... Kf7 17. Qxa8 $18 *


