[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/Bosburp"]
[UTCDate "2023.09.25"]
[UTCTime "06:44:29"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Bc5 { not really sideline, but I decided to add it to this section because we will usually transpose to similar positions as the Max Lange Defense. } 3. f4 (3. Na4 Bxf2+!? $10 $36 { a funny line worth checking out. It is called the Immortal Draw, some masters play this line if they have prearranged a draw. Sample game: https://lichess.org/IFThpdK9#36 }) (3. Bc4 Nc6 4. Qg4 { We have transposed to the same position as chapter 12. }) 3... exf4 (3... d6 4. Nf3 Nf6 5. Bc4 Nc6 6. d3 { we have transposed to the same position as in chapter 10. }) 4. Nf3 { [%csl Gh4][%cal Gf3h4] } 4... d6?! 5. d4 Bb6 6. Bxf4 $16 { white is obviously better. } { [%csl Gf5,Ge5,Gd5,Gc5,Gf4,Gf3,Gc3,Bc4,Bd2,Bc1,Rb6,Rb8,Ra8,Rc8,Re8,Rd8,Rg8,Rh8][%cal Ge4f5,Gd4e5,Ge4d5,Gd4c5,Bf1c4,Bd1d2,Be1c1] } *


