1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Bb4 { the point of this move is to get rid of the c3 knight. } { [%csl Gc3][%cal Gb4c3] } 3. f4! Bxc3 4. bxc3 { always capture toward the center! } 4... exf4 5. Qg4! { [%csl Gf4,Gg7][%cal Gg4f4,Gg4g7] } 5... Qf6 { black really tries to hang on to all their pawn, the disadvantage of this move is that black won't be able to move the d pawn. } { [%csl Gf4,Gg7][%cal Gf6f4,Gf6g7] } 6. Ne2 { keep attacking that pawn } { [%csl Gf4][%cal Ge2f4] } 6... g5? { [%csl Gf4][%cal Gg5f4] } 7. h4 gxh4 8. Nxf4 { now we have an insanely good knight on f4. } { [%csl Gd5,Gh5,Gf4][%cal Gf4d5,Gf4h5] } 8... Nc6?? 9. Nd5 { [%csl Gf6,Gc7][%cal Gd5f6,Gd5c7] } 9... Qd6 (9... Qd8 10. Qg7 { same thing } { [%csl Gh8][%cal Gg7h8] }) 10. Qg7 $18 { there is no way for black to hold on to their rook. } { [%csl Gh8][%cal Gg7h8] } *


