[UTCTime "06:44:29"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 g6? { this doesn't quite work because after 3. d4 exd4 4. Qxd4 and black won't be able to fianchetto the bishop. } 3. d4 exd4 4. Qxd4 Qf6? { the most popular move! } (4... Nf6?? { the second most popular move, which is a game losing blunder. } 5. Bg5 { [%csl Gd8,Gf6][%cal Gg5d8] } 5... Bg7 (5... Be7 6. Nd5 Nc6 7. Nxf6+ Bxf6 8. Qxf6 Qxf6 9. Bxf6) 6. e5 { good knight, knight. } { [%csl Gf6,Yd8][%cal Ge5f6,Yg5d8] }) (4... f6 { This ugly move is actually the best move. Black just has a really uncomfortable position, just play Be3 and O-O-O. } { [%csl Rf6,Rf8,Rg8,Rh8,Re8,Rd8,Rc8,Rb8,Ra8,Be3,Bc1,Bc4,Bf3,Bb5][%cal Bc1e3,Be1c1,Bf1c4,Bg1f3,Bc4b5] }) 5. Qxf6 Nxf6 6. e5 Ng4 7. Nd5 { [%csl Gc7][%cal Gd5c7] } 7... Kd8 8. h3 Nxe5 (8... Nh6 9. Bg5+ Be7 10. Bxe7+ Ke8 11. Bf6 { [%csl Gh8][%cal Gf6h8] } 11... Rg8 12. Nxc7+ Kf8 13. Nxa8 $18) 9. Bg5+ Be7 10. Bxe7+ Ke8 11. Bf6 { [%csl Gh8,Ge5][%cal Gf6h8,Gf6e5] } 11... Rg8 12. Nxc7+ Kf8 13. Bxe5 { [%csl Ga8][%cal Gc7a8] } 13... Na6 14. Nxa8 $18 { white is up 11 points in material. } *


[Event "CRUSH with the Vienna!: 2...c6?!"]
[Date "2023.10.04"]
[Result "*"]
[Variant "Standard"]
[ECO "C25"]
[Opening "Vienna Game"]
[StudyName "CRUSH with the Vienna!"]
[ChapterName "2...c6?!"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/nq1GGbNO/bsNqbktI"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/Bosburp"]
[UTCDate "2023.10.04"]
[UTCTime "07:57:15"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 c6?! { This move is played 3% of the the time. It's not really good tough, because black isn't developing any pieces, and c6 is a perfect square for the knight. } 3. d4! { Breaking thorough the center immediately! } 3... exd4? { This is a mistake because it allows us to develop the queen. Usually black would kick us away with Nc6, but now there is the c pawn in the way. } 4. Qxd4 Nf6?! { The most common move. } (4... d6 5. Bf4 Nf6 6. O-O-O c5 7. Qe3 Be7 8. Nf3 $18 { [%csl Gf3,Gf4,Ge4,Ge3,Gc3,Gc1,Gf1,Gd1,Re8,Rd8,Rc8,Rb8,Ra8,Rh8,Re7] }) (4... Qf6?! 5. e5 { [%cal Ge5f6] } 5... Qe6 6. Be3 d5 7. exd6 Qxd6 8. O-O-O Qxd4 9. Bxd4 Be6 10. Re1 $16 { [%csl Rf8,Rg8,Rh8,Re8,Rb8,Ra8][%cal Bf1d3,Bg1f3] }) 5. e5 { Black has wasted a move, the knight has to go back to it's starting square. } { [%cal Ge5f6] } 5... Ng8 (5... Nh5?? 6. g4 { The knight is trapped } { [%csl Gh5][%cal Gg4h5] }) (5... Nd5 6. Nxd5 cxd5 7. Qxd5 Nc6 8. Bf4 $18 { White is almost fully developed, meanwhile black's only developed piece is the knight on c6. Next up is castling queenside, and white is dominating the center. The engine-o-meter gives white a +3.8 advantage. } { [%csl Ge5,Gd5,Gf4,Rf8,Rd8,Rc8,Re8][%cal Be1c1,Bf1c4,Bc4b5,Bg1f3] }) (5... Qe7? 6. Be3! { White just breaks the pin while preparing to castle. Now black's knight has to move anyway. } 6... Ng8 7. O-O-O $18 { None of black's pieces have crossed the sixth rank. It is also really hard for black to develop: the knights have no square to develop, and the bishops are stuck. We can now take advantage of the fact that black's king is still stuck in the center.There is no way black's gonna survive this. } { [%csl Gd4,Gd1,Ge5,Ge3,Ra8,Rb8,Rc8,Re8,Re7,Rf8,Rg8,Rh8,Gc3][%cal Bf1e2,Be2d3,Bd3c4,Bg1f3,Bc3e4,Ge5d6,Ge5f6] }) (5... c5?? 6. Qf4! { Very simply moving the queen to a safe square. } 6... Nh5 7. Qe4 Nc6 (7... g6 { Preparing a retreat square for the knight. } { [%csl Gg7][%cal Gh5g7] } 8. Nf3 Nc6 9. Bc4 Be7 10. Bh6 $18 { White is completely crushing here. Next up is O-O-O and break open the center. } { [%csl Rf8,Rg7,Re8,Rd8,Rc8,Re7][%cal Be1c1,Rh6f8,Rh6g7] }) 8. g4 $18 { [%cal Gg4h5] }) 6. Ne4! { [%cal Ge4d6] } 6... b6?? { Note: after g6, a6, h6, Na6... we have the same idea. } 7. Bg5! { This allows white to hop the knight into d6, no matter what black plays. } { [%cal Gg5d8] } 7... Be7 (7... Ne7 8. Nd6# { Smothered mate! } { [%csl Ge8][%cal Gd6e8] }) (7... Qc7 8. Nd6+ { [%csl Ge8][%cal Gd6e8] } 8... Bxd6 { [%cal Gd6c7] } 9. exd6 { Even though we don't have a knight in the center anymore, we now have a insanely strong pawn controlling the important e7 square. } { [%csl Gd6][%cal Gd6c7,Gd6e7] } 9... Qb7 10. Qe5+ { [%csl Ge8][%cal Ge5e8] } 10... Kf8 11. Be7+ Ke8 12. Bf6+ Ne7 13. Qxe7#) 8. Nd6+! { [%csl Ge8,Yd8][%cal Gd6e8,Yg5d8,Re7d6] } 8... Kf8 9. Bxe7+! Nxe7 (9... Qxe7 { This hangs the bishop. } 10. Nxc8 $18) (9... Kxe7 10. Bc4! { We bring the next piece into action! white threatens to take the f7 pawn. Black's position is hopeless at this point } { [%csl Bf7,Re7][%cal Gc4f7,Yd6f7] } 10... Nh6 11. Qh4+ { [%csl Ge7][%cal Gh4e7] } 11... f6 12. exf6+ Kxd6 13. Qg3+ Kc5 14. O-O-O { [%csl Gd6,Gd5,Gd4][%cal Gd1d6] } 14... Kxc4 15. Qb3+ Kc5 16. Qa3+ Kb5 17. Rd4 { [%csl Gb4][%cal Ga3b4,Gd4b4] } 17... a5 { [%cal Ga5b4] } 18. Qd3+ Kc5 19. Qc4#) 10. Qf4 $18 { White threatens mate on f7 and there is absolutely no way to stop it without sacrificing tons of material! } { [%csl Bf7][%cal Gf4f7,Yd6f7] } *


