1. e4 { Here is an example of why the Trash Variation is total trash } 1... e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. f4 Nc6?? { Blunder. d5 was best. } { black didn't make any mistakes after this move, black just got punished for playing trash. } (3... d5 4. fxe5 Nxe4 5. Qf3 Nc6 6. Bb5 Nxc3 7. dxc3 a6 8. Bxc6+) 4. fxe5 Nxe5 5. d4 Nc6 6. e5 Ng8 7. Nf3 d5 8. Be2?! { Inaccuracy. Bb5 was best. } (8. Bb5 Ne7 9. O-O h6 10. Ne2 g6 11. c3 Bg7 12. Nf4 O-O) 8... Be6 9. O-O Nge7 10. Ng5 Nf5?! { Inaccuracy. Qd7 was best. } (10... Qd7 11. Bb5 a6 12. Nxe6 fxe6 13. Ba4 b5 14. Bb3 Na5 15. Ne2 c5 16. c3 Nxb3 17. axb3) 11. Nxf7!! Kxf7 12. g4 { [%csl Gf7,Yf5][%cal Gf1f7,Yg4f5] } 12... g6 13. gxf5 Bxf5 14. Bg4 Ne7 15. Bg5 Rg8 16. Kh1! { white avoids any future checks when the g file will be opened up. } 16... Qd7 17. Bxe7 Kxe7 18. Bxf5 gxf5 19. Qh5?! { Inaccuracy. e6 was best. } (19. e6 Qd6 20. Rxf5 Re8 21. Rxd5 Qxe6 22. Re5 Kd8 23. Rxe6 Rxe6 24. Qf3 Bd6 25. Qxb7 Reg6) 19... Rg7?! { Inaccuracy. Kd8 was best. } (19... Kd8 20. Rxf5 c6 21. Raf1 Be7 22. Rf7 Qg4 23. Qxg4 Rxg4 24. Rxh7 Kd7 25. Rff7 Re8 26. Ne2) 20. Rxf5 Qe6 21. Raf1 Qg8 22. e6 { 1-0 Black resigns. } { black resigned, because white will bring the rook over to f7 and the only way to stop this is with Qxe5 and after Re5 black loses the queen. } 1-0


