1. e4 Nf6 2. e5 Nd5 3. d4 (3. c4 Nb6 4. d4 Nc6? 5. d5 { [%csl Gc6][%cal Gd5c6] } 5... Nxe5 6. c5 { [%csl Gb6][%cal Gc5b6] } 6... Nbc4 7. Qd4 { this transposes to the same position. } { [%csl Gc4][%cal Gf1c4,Gd4c4] } 7... b5 (7... d6 8. Bxc4 Nxc4 9. Qxc4) 8. cxb6 Ba6 9. Nd2 Nxd2 10. Bxa6 Ndf3+ 11. Nxf3 Nxf3+ 12. gxf3 { White has a extra bishop! }) 3... Nc6 { white has a +3.3 advantage, but only if white can find the right continuation, which most players failed to do. } 4. c4 Nb6 5. d5 Nxe5 6. c5 Nbc4 7. Qd4 { black cannot move either of his knights because they are protecting each other. } { [%csl Gc4][%cal Gd4c4,Gf1c4] } 7... b5 (7... d6 8. Bxc4) 8. cxb6 Ba6 9. Nd2 Nxd2 10. Bxa6 { [%csl Gd2,Ge5][%cal Gc1d2,Gd4e5] } 10... Ndf3+ 11. Nxf3 Nxf3+ 12. gxf3 { white has an extra bishop! } *


