[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/Bosburp"]
[UTCDate "2022.03.12"]
[UTCTime "08:48:44"]

1. e4 e5 2. f4 { This is the King's Gambit } 2... Bc5 { black prevents white from castling } { [%csl Gg1][%cal Gc5g1] } 3. Nf3 { [%csl Rh4,Ge5][%cal Gf3h4,Rd8h4,Rh4e1,Gf3e5] } (3. fxe5 Qh4+ 4. g3 Qxe4+ 5. Qe2 Qxh1 { this is why white should not grab the pawn }) 3... d6 { [%csl Ge5][%cal Gd6e5] } 4. c3 { this supports d4 } { [%csl Gd4][%cal Gc3d4,Gd2d4] } 4... Qe7 { black is indirectly attacking e4 } 5. d4 { [%csl Gc5][%cal Gd4c5] } 5... exd4 6. cxd4 { [%csl Gc5][%cal Gd4c5] } 6... Qxe4+?? 7. Kf2!! { black needs to save his bishop } 7... Bb6 (7... Nf6 8. dxc5) (7... Bb4 8. a3 Ba5 (8... Be1+ 9. Qxe1 Qxe1+ 10. Kg1 (10. Nxe1))) 8. Bb5+! Kd8 (8... c6 9. Re1 { the queen is lost } 9... Qe7 10. Rxe7+ Nxe7 11. Bd3) (8... Nc6 9. Re1 f5 10. a4 a5 11. Ng5 Nf6 12. Nc3 O-O 13. Ncxe4 fxe4 14. Nxe4 Nxe4+ 15. Rxe4) 9. Re1 Qf5 10. Re8# { a brutal mate! } *


