1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 { [%csl Gb5][%cal Ga6b5] } 4. Ba4 d6 { [%csl Gg4,Ge6][%cal Gc8g4] } 5. d4?! b5 { [%csl Ga4][%cal Gb5a4] } 6. Bb3 Nxd4 7. Nxd4 exd4 8. Qxd4?? { this looks like a natural move but it is actually a blunder. } 8... c5 { [%csl Gd4,Gc4][%cal Gc5d4,Gc5c4,Gc4b3] } 9. Qd5 { [%csl Ga8][%cal Gd5a8] } 9... Be6 { [%csl Gd5][%cal Ge6d5] } 10. Qc6+ Bd7 11. Qd5 c4 { [%csl Gb3][%cal Gc4b3] } 12. Bxc4 bxc4 13. Qxc4 { black has an -5.0 advantage } 13... Be7 { [%csl Bf6,Bg8][%cal Be8g8,Bg8f6,Ba8c8,Bd8a5,Bd7b5] } *


